Title: FTS Systems Titan Series Cold Traps Instructions
Desc: The Titan Trap™ is a mechanically refrigerated cold trap designed to trap corrosive and non-corrosive vapor streams within vacuum systems. The Titan Trap is the first cold trap to incorporate a titanium helical coil design. The coil, located inside a Teflon™ coated reservoir, increases efficiency by increasing the surface area available for trapping corrosives. Depending on the model, it can cool to a low temperature of -100°C with a trapping rate up to five liters per hour. The microprocessor option allows for an automated operation which includes automatic vacuum pump activation, automatic defrost/shut down routine, and power-fail recovery routine. The revolutionary design of the Titan Trap eliminates the need for a glass liner and heat transfer fluid, as required with standard traps, when trapping most corrosive vapor streams.

Title: B/R Instrument Corporation B/R Models 24T or 36T Spinning Band Distillation Systems
Desc: The B/R Instrument Corporation's B/R Models 24T or 36T Spinning Band Distillation Systems have a motor driven band of metal or Teflon, whose sole function is to promote vapor liquid contact.  As the band is rotated rapidly it combs through the layers of liquid on the still walls continuously forming vapor to liquid mixing (contact) in each small cross section of the column.  In addition, the band is designed and rotated such that it continuously pumps the liquid condensate downward.  This net effect is to force the higher boiling more condensable liquids down without flooding the column and allowing the less volatile not so condensable vapors to pass up and over to the head for collection.  Thus B/R spinning band units are capable of separating complex mixtures of narrow boiling range with high efficiency distillation, or of high throughputs with less efficient distillation; depending on what the operator deems necessary.

Title: Altex Model 420 Microprocessor Controller/Programmer

The instrument analyzes electronic pulse inputs derived from a particle suspension and presents the particle size distribution by number in 64, 128 or 256 channels, the information being displayed in graphical form and printed in numerical and graphical form.

Title: Canberra Series 7300 Si(Li) Detector System
Desc: The Canberra Series 7300 Si(Li) Detector System is a lithium-drifted silicon detector, which is the heart of this spectrometer system, is a carefully silicon diode with a p-i-n structure.  The manufacturing process involved the diffusion lithium into one surface of a disc of p-type silicon to form a p-n junction.  Then, under carefully controlled conditions, lithium atoms from the n-type diffused layer are made to migrate, or "drift", through the silicon disc, taking up positions within the material so as to compensate for the original p-type impurities.  If done properly, the result within the drifted region is a net dopant of intrinsic proportions.  Finally, the original p-type contact is replaced by a thin gold surface barrier contact which is transparent to soft X-rays.  Under conditions of reverse bias, a photon interacting within the intrinsic region frees electrons and holes (charge carriers) which are swept by the electric field to their respective collecting electrodes.  The charge thus collected is one electronic charge for every 3.5eV of incident photon energy.

Title: Canberra X-Ray Spectroscopy Amplifier Model 1713
Desc: The Canberra Model 1713 X-Ray Spectroscopy Amplifier is designed to optimize energy resolution in spectroscopy applications with Si(Li) detectors operating at count rates up to 80% duty cycle.  Because the amplifier response is symmetrical to signal inputs of either polarity, it is ideal for use with pulsed optical feedback preamplifiers such as the Model 1708.

Title: Canberra X-Ray Spectrum Enhancer Model 1764
Desc: The Canberra Model 1764 Spectrum Enhancer is designed specifically to operate with the Canberra Model 1713 X-Ray Spectroscopy Amplifier, Model 1708 Pulsed Optical Feedback Si(Li) Preamplifier and Canberra's line of cryogenically cooled lithium-drifted silicon X-Ray detectors.  It converts the amplifier's linear output pulse, independent of the time constant of the amplifier, into a standardized signal for optimum processing by analog to digital converters used with multi-channel analyzers.  The signal gain is unity.

Title: Canberra Bragg/Beam Scanner Model 1740
Desc: The Model 1740 Bragg/Beam Scanner is a totally new tool for use with SEM's or microprobes, in X-ray diffraction or fluorescence, and for general spectroscopy applications.  It operates with the Canberra Model 8100 Multichannel Analyzer to very accurately take and display data as a function of position.

Title: Canberra Digitizer Model 6271
Desc: The Canberra Model 6271 Digitizer is a highly accurate and stable solid-state DC to frequency converter with an ultra-sensitive, protected FET input.  The output frequency is directly proportional to the input signal and continuously varies with the input.  By counting the output pulses per unit of time, integration of the input signal may be obtained over the counting duration.  The very high (1 MHz full scale) output frequency provides exceptional resolution at short counting periods.  Longer periods of integration are accommodated by up to three decades of switch selected frequency division.  The Model 6271 Digitizer accepts either current or voltage inputs over four ranges as selected by front panel switches.  A front panel meter monitors the input, its full scale deflection controlled by the range selected.

Title: Canberra Preamplifier Model 1708
Desc: The Canberra Model 1708 Preamplifier is a cooled input FET charge sensitive amplifier which employs pulsed-optical feedback to enhance the low noise performance required for high resolution detector systems.  The Model 1708 is normally used with a pulse shaping amplifier such as the Canberra Model 1713.  Preamplifier power (+/- 12V, +/- 24V), detector bias, test input, preamplifier output, and preamplifier reset signals are available through a rear panel 15-pin connector.  A 15-foot cable is supplied with the preamplifier to connect it with a Canberra Model 1713 Amplifier, which routes power and the test input signal to the Model 1708 and accepts the output signals from the Model 1708 for further processing.

Title: Carle Models 111, 211 and 311 Analytical Gas Chromatographs
Desc: The Carle Analytical Gas Chromatographs are compact, convenient instruments designed to give high quantitative accuracy with years of trouble-free service.  Model 111 is provided with a filament or thermistor thermal conductivity detector.  Model 211 comes with a flame ionization detector and a high sensitivity electrometer.  Model 311 combines the thermal conductivity detector of the Model 111 and the flame ionization detector of the Model 211.

Title: Carle Models 111, 211 and 311 Analytical Gas Chromatographs

Title: Carle Micro Volume Valves - All Models
Desc: The Carle Micro Volume sampling and Switching Valves are designed and constructed to meet the need in chromatography for a rugged, reliable valve for routine and high efficiency analyses.  All models of Carle Micro Volume Valves utilize the same basic design providing a family of valves with various porting configurations to handle almost any GC valving application.  The unique kinematic loading principle allows the valve to operate leak-free over a wide range of pressure and temperature conditions.  Materials of construction provide long valve life.  All valve parts contacting sample are made of corrosion-resistant type 316 stainless steel or a glass and ceramic filled Teflon which is resistant to almost all types of samples.

Title: Carle Series-S Valve Programmer
Desc: The Carle Series-S Valve Programmer automatically times the sequential actuation of valves to perform the complex analysis of a mixture of gases in a simple manner.  The operation is based on a drum programmer driven by a stepper motor.  the drum programmer allows simple, repeatable programming and visual indication of the total sequence.  In addition, the adjustable event markers allow quick, front panel changes to an event time or complete reprogramming of the entire sequence.  The programmer was designed to provide independent manual operation of the individual valves to assist in determining the appropriate switching times during the analysis.

Title: Carle Mini Volume Valves Series 5500
Desc: Carle Mini Volume Valves Series 5500 have been designed to meet valving needs in the field of chromatography where compact size, operation over a wide range of temperatures and pressure, and leak-free performance are required.  The valves are also constructed to have freedom from dead volume, small internal volume, and to be available at moderate cost.

Title: Corning Model 320 pH meter
Desc: The Corning Model 320 pH meter uses a sensing electrode and a reference electrode in combination.  The sensing (pH) electrode or element has an internal buffer solution with a constant pH value and develops a potential (difference between inner and outer ionic charge) when placed in a solution.  This is caused by the activity (concentration) of H+ in the solution.  The reference electrode or element has a defined, stable potential irrespective of the H+ activity in the sample.  The 320 measures and converts the resulting minute electrode voltages into a pH reading.  The response of the pH electrode is defined by the Nernst equation.

Ozone is generated on-site, eliminating the need to store toxic and corrosive chemicals.  The corona discharge method is the most efficient way to produce large amounts of ozone.

Title: Berghof Laboratory Autoclaves with 75 to 250 ml capacity
Desc: Berghof Laboratory Autoclaves with 75 to 250 ml capacity are designed, manufactured, and tested with extreme care.  Pressure vessel, complete with PTFE liner, fittings and thermocouple.  Made from a special stainless steel material.  The lid, liner, lid inlets and stirring unit are all made of high quality PTFE, or else covered therewith.  This PTFE is made by a special iostatic compression process.  Its properties of chemical inertness, mechanical strength, temperature resistance and uniform thermal expansion make it an ideal material for autoclaves.  The PTFE lining extends to the inside of the autoclave lid.  The rupture disc fitting, exhaust valve, and manometer mounted on the manifold are not lined with PTFE.

Title: Brooks Instrument Mass Flow Controller Model 5850E
Desc: The Brooks Model 5850E Flow Controller is a mass flow measurement device designed for accurately measuring and rapidly controlling flows of gases.  The Brooks Model 5850E Mass Flow Controller is used widely in the Semiconductor industry as well as many others, where manual, electronic or computer controlled gas handling occurs.  The Model 5850E consists of three basic units: a flow sensor, a control valve and an integral electronic control system.  This combination produces a stable gas flow, which eliminates the need to continuously monitor and re-adjust gas pressures.  Standard features include: fast valve control, remote programming, output limiting and a replaceable cleanable sensor.

Title: Gow-Mac Series 750 Flame Ionization Detector for (69-750, 740p, 750P, 750 IuP)
Desc: The Gow-Mac Series 69-750 Flame Ionization Detector is a rugged, transportable, compact flame ionization detector (FID) gas chromatograph designed for high capacity performance. Title: GSD AutoPycnometer Model 1320
Desc: The GSD AutoPycnometer Model 1320 compresses identically two quantities of a dry gas at the same temperature and pressure, but initially of unequal volume because of the space occupied by a sample.  Since the compression of unequal volumes results in unequal pressures even at the same temperature, an adjustment is made in the volume of the lower pressure gas while under compression to bring it to that of the higher.  The compression of both gases is then removed and gas pressures are equalized.

Title: HP HPLC ChemStation Automating Analyses Handbook

Title: HP HPLC ChemStation Customizing With Macros Handbook

Title: HP HPLC ChemStation The Commands Handbook

Title: HP 1090M Liquid Chromatograph Operating Training Course
Desc: The HP 1090M Liquid Chromatograph Operating Training Course is a 4-day course instructed by Gwen Dee Goretsas and Sue Hulett on operating the HP 1090M Liquid Chromatograph.  This course contains overviews, data acquisition methods such as LC methods, qualitative data evaluation such as DAD, lab sessions such as isocratic operation, gradient operation, optimization of detection parameters, integration of data, calibration of I-single level, multilevel calibration, sequence operation, SDS lab, and injector lab, reports, work sessions including RPN, filer-text editor, macro programming, and sequence macros, breaks, and lunches.  Also includes a course evaluation questionnaire.

Title: Herzog Electronic M 315 Automatic Tag Closed Cup Flash Point Apparatus for ASTM D56
Desc: The Herzog Automatic Tag Closed Cup Flash Point Apparatus is an automated system for running the ASTM D56 Tag Closed Cup flash point method.  The instrument uses a flame ionization type detector to detect the endpoint.  The sample is first cooled to at least 11 degrees below its expected flash point.  Its temperature is then raised 1.0 degrees a minute.  The instrument begins testing the flash point at 5 degrees below the expected flash point and tests every 0.5 degrees.  The test is automatically interrupted when the flash point is detected or at 8 degrees above the expected flash point.

Title: Heraeus BB 5060 Incubator for Tissue Cultures

Title: Isco uLC-500 Micro Flow Pump Instruction Manual
Desc: The Isco uLC-500 is a micro flow syringe pump with a 50 ml capacity, a flow rate range of 0.02 - 600 ul/min, and a 10,000 psi pressure rating.  The pump can be operated in either constant flow or constant pressure modes and has a digital display of flow rate and pressure.  The syringe barrel, piston, and cap are made of Nitronic 50 alloy which is highly resistant to almost all solvents and most corrosive acids up to 20% and halogen acids up to 5% concentration can be handled.  The pump seals are graphite-filled Teflon.  The pump is designed for liquid chromatography including HPLC, micro HPLC, Supercritical Fluid Chromatography, and any other application requiring pulse-free delivery of liquids at low flow rates.

Title: IEC  Centra-8R Centrifuge Instruction Manual

Title: Beckman J2-MI Centrifuge Instruction Manual
Desc: The model J2-MI is a floor-model, refrigerated centrifuge for general purpose laboratory use. The Model J2-MI is microprocessor-controlled and introduces a brushless, induction motor. The instrument features: digital displays, touch switches, keyboard, 10 acceleration rates, 10 program memories, automatic temperature control, and automatic maximum speed limits.

Title: InfraRed Spectratech 7070 Technical Data Manual
Desc: The InfraRed Spectratech 7070 is operated in the photoconductive mode. The detector is a resistive element, whose conductance increases when infrared radiation of the proper wavelength is incident on the active area.

Title: Imass Dynastat
Desc: The Imass Dynastat offers a new concept in instrumentation which permits measurements of viscoelastic behavior in either the static (transient) mode of testing (creep or stress relaxation) or in the dynamic mode (oscillatory deformation).  High reliability, state-of-the-art electronics make possible extremely rapid applications of load or deformation (in the ten millisecond range) with control stability of 1 part in 10,000 of the controlled variable for hours and days.  This is accomplished with the input variable, either load or deformation, under closed-loop servo control.

Title: Imass Dynalyzer
Desc: The Imass Dynalyzer outputs a sine wave of a precise frequency selectable from 0.1 Hz to 199.9 Hz (optionally 0.01 to 99.99) of an adjustable amplitude from 0 to 10 volts.  This output signal can be used to drive a variety of dynamic mechanical test instruments.  The Dynalyzer accepts inputs from transducers which measure dynamic mechanical response of materials to the sinusoidal deformation imposed by the test instrument.  The unit performs a correlation analysis of the two transducer signals with the reference output sine wave from which it measures the phase shift between the two signals and provides voltages proportional to the complex modulus and to the storage and loss moduli.  When properly scaled with specimen geometry and instrument calibrations, these voltages are converted to the corresponding moduli in engineering units.

Title: Coherent Innova 90 Ion Laser
Desc: The Innova 90 Series of Ion Lasers are designed for a broad range of applications requiring reliable continuous wave light across the broad spectrum from ultraviolet through visible to infrared.

Title: Imass Dynatherm
Desc: The Imass Dynatherm is a temperature programmer and real time digital controller with output provisions for operation of up to 5 relay functions and 1 analog voltage source.  A wide variety of control algorithms may be selected for the relay functions; for example, the direct control of heaters, gas valves, water valves and/or liquid nitrogen valves, and/or the indirect control of large heating loads or compressors through the use of auxiliary power relays.  The analog voltage source may be used for the control of large power loads through the use of standard solid state power packs.

Main requirements of large-scale-productions such as stirring, dispersing, heating, cooling and vacuum can thus be simulated in the laboratory.  The reactor vessel can be heated and cooled with warm or cold tap water and also with a laboratory thermostat.

The vessel does not therefore have to be insulated and there will be no oil vapor, oxidation, or moisture absorption at the thermoregulation unit as in conventional thermostats.

Title: Kratos Spectroflow 400 Dual Piston HPLC Solvent Delivery System Operator's Manual
Desc: The Kratos Spectroflow 400 HPLC Solvent Delivery System is a virtually pulse free dual-piston pump with selectable flow rates from 10 uL/min to 4.99 mL/min.  Pressures can be used up to 400 BAR (6,000 PSI) continuously or up to 490 BAR (7,000 PSI) intermittently.  The two pump heads operate in series, and the eluent always flows through both pump heads in one direction.  A different displacement of both pistons is generated by the constant rotation speed of the cams.  The pump head with check valves acts as the working piston, and the pump head without check valves acts as the buffer piston.  A continuous flow and filling of serially connected buffer pump head is achieved by the action of the working piston during its delivery cycle; the buffer piston then delivers while the working piston refills.

Title: Lab-Line Orbital Water Bath Shakers Models 3540, 3540-1, and 3540-1CE
Desc: Lab-Line Orbital Water Bath Shakers Models 3540, 3540-1, and 3540-1CE provide dependable heating from slightly above ambient to 65 degrees Celsius and variable-speed shaking from 40 to 400 rpm.  They are ideal for general laboratory preparation of uniform solutions.  The baths are designed with separate heating and shaking controls, so that they can be used as constant temperature baths (only) or as orbiting shakers (only).  A built-in timer controls the duration of the shaking operation from 0 to 60 minutes, or it can be set for constant operation.  An analog tachometer shows the rotation speed.  An LED readout shows temperature in degrees Celsius.  Bath temperature is controlled by hydraulic thermostats--one for control, the other for overtemperature protection.  The heating element itself has a built-in thermostat that acts as a low-water level safety.  When the water level falls below 1.5 inches in the tank this thermostat shuts off power to the heater.  (The shaker is not affected.)  The rugged, molded polyethylene outer body resists chemical spills and will not rust.

Title: Microsoft Discovering Microsoft Office 2000 Premium and Professional
Desc: The Microsoft Office 2000 Premium and Professional opens an exciting new door to business computing for the millennium.  Now users can work faster and more efficiently than ever before by using the wealth of new features that Office 2000 provides.  Office 2000 also offers new ways to collaborate with other people who are using the Web, or with your company's intranet.

Title: Apple Power Macintosh 7600 Series Computer User's Manual
Desc: The Apple Power Macintosh 7600 Series Computer is designed to give the highest performance combined with real ease of use.  This computer is powered by the new PowerPC microprocessor.  This microprocessor was designed by Apple Computer, Inc., Motorola, Inc., and IBM Corporation.  The PowerPC microprocessor uses Reduced Instruction Set Computing (RISC) technology to deliver very high performance at the lowest possible cost.  The PowerPC RISC microprocessor represents the state of the art in microprocessor design.

Title: Micromass Q-Tof 2
Desc: The Micromass Q-Tof 2 Platform Analyzer performs parallel detection of all masses within the spectrum at very high sensitivity and acquisition rates.  This characteristic is of particular advantage when the instrument is coupled to fast chromatography, since each spectrum is representative of the sample composition at that point in time, irrespective of how rapidly the sample composition is changing.

Title: Mettler Delta 320 pH Meter Operation Manual
Desc: The Mettler Delta 320 pH meter uses a sensing electrode and a reference electrode in combination.  The sensing (pH) electrode or element has an internal buffer solution with a constant pH value and develops a potential (difference between inner and outer ionic charge) when placed in a solution.  This is caused by the activity (concentration) of H+ in the solution.  The reference electrode or element has a defined, stable potential irrespective of the H+ activity in the sample.  The Delta 320 measures and converts the resulting minute electrode voltages into a pH reading.  The response of the pH electrode is defined by the Nernst equation.

Title: Mettler  DL40RC MemoTitrator Operating Instructions
Desc: The Mettler  DL40RC MemoTitrator is a microprocessor-controlled compact instrument used for individual titrimetric analysis.

Title: Macbeth Reflection Densitometer RD-514, RD-517, RD-519 Operator's Manual
Desc: The Macbeth Reflection Densitometers RD-514, RD-517, RD-519 are digital readout reflection densitometers equipped with four, selectable filters for color or visual density measurements within the 0 to 2.50 density range.  Push-button controls and digital density display offer the utmost in operating ease while making it possible to obtain immediate, accurate, and reproducible density measurements with a minimum of operating errors.  A lock-in (hold) capability causes each reading to remain displayed until the next density measurement is made.  The instrument can be used for absolute readings (i.e., conventional densitometer mode) or for density--difference readings (i.e., null-comparator mode).  In null-comparator mode, the density display of measured samples is in terms of plus (+) or minus (-) deviations from a known sample; operator computations are not necessary.  Additionally, instrument zeroing or nulling (in each filter position) is instantaneous and is accomplished without control adjustment.  Individual slope controls for each filter position enable identical readings with two or more instruments when used to measure a specific color sample.

Title: Macbeth Transmission Densitometer TD-904 Operator's Manual

Title: Molecular Dynamics ImageQuant Utilities User's Guide for Microsoft Windows NT, Apple Power Macintosh
Desc: The Molecular Dynamics ImageQuant Utilities User's Guide describes how to use the FluorSep and ImageQuant Tools utilities.  The FluorSep utility uses a fluorochrome separation process to separate the multichannel images created using the FluorImager or Storm 860 instruments.  The fluorochrome separation process removes the cross-contamination by performing a mathematical transformation on the images produced during scanning.  The end result includes two or more images that, under ideal conditions, represent the light emitted from the fluorochromes used in the sample.  The FluorSep utility also provides a method to create multichannel images from single images created using any Molecular Dynamics instrument.  The ImageQuant Tools utility provides several image processing tools.  These tools modify a copy of the original image while the original image remains unaltered.  Both images can be used for quantitation.  Comes with a Molecular Dynamics IQ Solutions Resource CD ROM Version 1.0 Image Database for Personal Densitometer, FluorImager, PhosphorImager, Storm.  Also included are reference manuals, guides, utilities, and tutorial, as well as the MDYN Website.

Title: National Institute of Health NIH Image 1.54
Desc: The National Institute of Health NIH Image 1.54 is an image processing and analysis program for Macintosh.  It can acquire, display, edit, enhance, analyze, print and animate images.  It reads and writes TIFF, PICT, PICS, and MacPaint files, providing compatibility with many other applications, including programs for scanning, processing functions, including contrast enhancement, density profiling, smoothing, sharpening, edge detection, median filtering, and spatial convolution with user defined kernals up to 63x63.  NIH Image also incorporates a Pascal-like macro programming language, providing the ability to automate complex, and frequently repetitive, processing tasks.  NIH Image can be used to measure area, average gray value, center and angle of orientation of a user defined regions of interest. Super-Q Systems can produce up to 12 L/min of high purity water; free of ionic contamination up to 18 megohm-cm resistivity level, and free from particulate and microbiological contamination to an abolute size level determined by the pore size of the Millipore filter element used.  With the appropriate cartridges installed in the proper configuration, a level of down to 20 ppb TOC may be achieved for organics removal.

The purified water produced by the Milli-RO Systems can be stored and used as a laboratory grade (or equivalent) water supply. Title: Perkin Elmer Temperature Programmer C570-0710
Desc: The Perkin Elmer Temperature Programmer C570-0710 is an attachment for the C 570-0701 Digital Controller which may be installed in the field by the user.  The Temperature Programmer provides means for changing the set-temperature of the Controller at a selected rate either upward or downward.  Initial and final set-temperatures are preselected.  Temperature change may be held at any point in the operation and then resumed.  Reset to the starting point at a fast rate is provided.

Title: Perkin Elmer Digital Controller C570-0701
Desc: The Perkin Elmer Digital Controller C570-0701 is designed to read and control the temperature of a variety of thermoelectric cells and cell holders (Temperature Regulated Devices) for use with the Model 570 and 550 series of spectrophotometers.  The Controller monitors the difference between a temperature related voltage from a platinum resistance sensor in the Temperature Regulated Device and a reference voltage set by a manual control related to the desired temperature.  When the difference becomes zero the Controller shuts off power to the Temperature Regulated Device's heating-cooling device and holds the Temperature Regulated Device's temperature equilibrated at the set temperature.  A measuring circuit monitors the sensor or reference voltage and displays the temperature corresponding to the selected voltage on a digital display.

Title: Perkin Elmer Thermoelectric Single Cell Holder Model C 550-0555
Desc: The Perkin Elmer Thermoelectric Single Cell Holder Model C 550-0555 is intended for use with Model 550 Series UV-Visible Spectrophotometers in conjunction with either Temperature Controller, C 570-0702 or Digital Controller, C 570-0701.  For the reference side either Single Cell Holder C 055-0306 or a second C 550-0555 Holder may be utilized.  A 12.5 x 12.5 mm cell is supported in the oven of the Cell Holder so that the spectrophotometer beam traverses the cell and its contents longitudinally and is attenuated by the sample according to the spectral absorptivity of the sample in the cell.  Heating or cooling of the cell is effected by solid-state, Peltier, thermoelectric modules.  A platinum resistance sensor monitors the cell temperature for control purposes.

Title: Perkin Elmer Lambda 3 Double-Beam UV-Visible Spectrophotometer
Desc: The Perkin Elmer Lambda 3 Double-Beam UV-Visible Spectrophotometer is a versatile general purpose instrument usable in a wide range of applications.  It is available in 190 to 750 nm, or 190 to 900 nm wavelength ranges and accepts a full complement of accessories.  This spectrophotometer combines an optomechanical system with microcomputer electronics to achieve precision with fast through-put.  Recorder operation outputs further extend the versatility of this spectrophotometer.  Automatic initial conditioning and self-monitoring features reduce errors.  The Lambda 3 is an electro-optical mechanical instrument utilizing a reflecting Littrow monochromator.  Control functions such as wavelength drive, filter and source changes, recorder control, and enhanced manual wavelength setting are performed by the microcomputer.  Self-baseline/background correction, automatic response time, transmittance-to-absorbance conversion, scale expansion, zero suppression, and self-diagnostics are typical of the microcomputer data handling functions.

Title: Perkin Elmer Infrared Quantitative Analysis Course
Desc: The Perkin Elmer Infrared Quantitative Analysis Course is a 2 part course on infrared quantitative analysis.  The first part introduces the principles first by discussing Beer's Law basis for quantitative absorption spectroscopy.  A systematic approach to performing quant by the solution method considers choice of band, solvent, concentration, pathlength, baseline and calibration curve.  Part 2 discusses some analytical techniques used by more experienced workers.  Alternate methods of band measurement include peak area and first or second derivatives.  Noise reduction methods such as digital smoothing and averaging are reviewed and compared.  Various techniques of baseline construction are considered next.  For those situations where sample thickness is not easily controlled, band ratio methods are applied.  This tutorial comes complete with booklets, 35 mm projector slides, and standard cassette tapes.

Title: Perkin Elmer Model LS-2 Filter Fluorimeter
Desc: The Perkin Elmer Model LS-2 Filter Fluorimeter works through the source, a xenon flash tube, which produces flashes of short duration and high intensity.  The luminescence emission from the sample produces a signal in a photomultiplier.  The signal is gated to produce a pulse, which is ratioed with a similar pulse derived directly from the source to produce a value; this value is compensated for the effects of dark current and residual phosphorescence by subtracting a similarly calculated value for the period preceding each pulse.  The emission values obtained are accumulated and averaged.  The current emission value is shown on the Fluorescence display and is updated every 0.4 seconds.  The luminescence measurement modes that can be selected are Fluorescence, Phosphorescence and integrated Phosphorescence.

Title: Perkin Elmer Integral 4000 Liquid Chromatograph User's Manual (Revision B Software)

Title: Perkin Elmer 950A/970A Intelligent Interface Operator's Manual
Desc: The Perkin Elmer 950A and 970A Intelligent Interfaces (collectively, the 900 Series) are analog-to-digital interfaces that acquire data and store it in a local buffer memory.  The readings are transmitted to the host computer thorugh either an IEEE-488 General Purpose Instrumentation Bus or an RS-232C serial link.  Each Intelligent Interface is capable of multiplexing data from two detectors during a single run.  Four programmable voltage ranges are available: 10 V, 2 V, 1 V, and 0.1 V.  Each voltage range provides a dynamic range of 1:1,000,000 at a sampling rate of 10 Hz.

This Windows '95 based graphical interface offers a second and complimentary level to total instrument control.  An intuitive single control panel provides simplistic control as well as a comprehensive monitoring system.  The operational parameters can be easily manipulated, saved or loaded by using the flexible Methods Editor enabling rapid set-up and custom method archiving.  Other features include audit trail facilities which can be used for diagnostic or simply GLP. Title: Parr 1261 Isoperibol Calorimeter Operating Instructions

The important design and operating concepts incorporated into the 1261 Calorimeter include: isoperibol operation, dynamic operation, microprocessor based process control, full microprocessor based data acquisition and handling, full microprocessor based communications capabilities, and flexible programming.

It also contains a deionizing filter to maintain water quality and a circulating pump with sufficient capacity to supply water for controlling the jacket temperature in one or two Parr 1261 Oxygen Bomb Calorimeters.  The 1563 unit operates as a closed circuit system, eliminating the need for an external water supply and drain at the calorimeter bench.

Title: Rainin Dynamax PDA-1 Photodiode Array Detector Product Brochure
Desc: The Rainin Dynamax PDA-1 Photodiode Array Detector uses 512 diodes to provide real-time spectra.  With a range from 195 to 600 nm, that's about one diode per nanometer.  The PDA-1 monitors UV and visible spectra over the entire chromatogram.  Advanced optics and temperature control mean there's never a need to compromise, and finding an optimum detection zone is easy.  Temperature control of the photodiode array and spectrometer provides a highly stable environment, resisting temperature fluctuations and controlling dark current noise for better signal-to-noise ratio.  Results will always be accurate and reproducible.

Title: Rainin Dynamax PC HPLC Data System And Pump Control for Windows Product Brochure
Model: Dynamax PC HPLC Data System and Pump Control
Desc: The Rainin Dynamax PC HPLC Data System And Pump Control for Windows is a sophisticated data acquisition/analysis and HPLC pump control package designed to run under the popular Microsoft Windows operating environment on IBM-PC compatible computers.  High-speed data acquisition, up to 60 Hz, is achieved with the powerful SS-420 HPLC data acquisition board.  The four independent A-D converters on each SS-420 board provide 20-bit resolution at all sampling rates.  Signals from one to four detectors can be simultaneously acquired by each SS-420 board.  Up to four boards can be installed in the computer, providing as many as 16 independent channels of data acquisition from four HPLC systems.  Each board is calibrated and tested against an NIST-traceable voltage standard to ensure that it meets the highest standards of quality and accuracy.  A standard feature allows automatic calibration by the user.

Title: Micromeritics ASAP 2010 Chemi Accelerated Surface Area and Porosimetry System Operator's Manual
Desc: The Micromeritics ASAP 2010 Chemi Accelerated Surface Area and Porosimetry System Operator's Manual describes how to install and operate the Accelerated Surface Area and Porosimetry 2010 Chemisorption System for Windows.  The ASAP 2010 Chemi System consists of an analyzer, a control module, which enables you to enter analysis and report options, and a chemisorption controller, which controls analyses and gas flow.  The analyzer contains two sample preparation ports and one analysis port.  In-line cold traps are located between the vacuum pump and the manifold in both the analysis and the degas systems.  The analysis furnace resides on an elevator.  Controls and indicators located on a swing-open control panel operate the vacuum systems, degas valves, and heating mantles.  A sliding shield can be lowered to provide safety or raised to provide access to the sample analysis port and preparation ports.  Includes set of 3.5-inch diskettes.

Title: Cetac U-5000AT+ Ultrasonic Nebulizer Operator's Manual
Desc: The Cetac U-5000AT+ Ultrasonic Nebulizer is the central component of CETAC Technologies' modular enhanced sample introduction system for ICP spectroscopy.  The U-5000AT+ improves detection limits by enhancing analyte transport efficiency and reducing solvent loading to the plasma.  Compared to pneumatic nebulization, detection of sample analytes is typically improved by an order of magnitude with the ultrasonic nebulizer.  The sensitivity increase is typically found when used with either an ICP-AES or ICP-MS instrument.  In operation, liquid sample is pumped onto the face of the piezoelectric transducer of the ultrasonic nebulizer where it is converted to a fine, dense aerosol.  The nebulizer gas flow transports the wet aerosol through the heated U-tube where the solvent is vaporized.  Solvent vapors are then condensed by the thermo-electric cooler and removed by the drain pump.  The sample output is a dry, analyte-laden aerosol which is introduced to the plasma.

Desc: The Parr Reactors and Pressure Vessels Catalog Sixth Edition 1989: Since its founding more than eighty years ago by University of Illinois Professor S. W. Parr, the Parr Instrument Company has been engaged exclusively in the manufacture and sale of combustion bombs, calorimeters, chemical reactors, pressure vessels and related equipment developed specifically for laboratory use.  Through its long history in this specialized field the primary emphasis in all Parr manufacturing has been to produce convenient pressure equipment, carefully designed for operation within specific temperature and pressure limits and thoroughly tested for maximum safety and reliability.  Its various offerings in this field are described in separate sections of this catalog.  These are growing lists to which new items are being added frequently.  Parr is proud to offer this pressure equipment as part of its continuing efforts to be of the greatest possible service to chemists and laboratory technicians everywhere who well understand the need for top quality apparatus when working with chemical procedures which require the application of heat and pressure. The analyzer contains two sample preparation ports and one analysis port.  In-line cold traps are located between the vacuum pump and the manifold in both the analysis and the degas systems.  The sample saturation pressure tube is located next to the sample analysis port.  The analysis bath fluid Dewar resides on an automatically-operated elevator. Title: Perkin Elmer LS 55 Molecular Spectroscopy User's Guide
Desc: The Perkin Elmer LS 55 Molecular Spectroscopy User's Guide describes specifications and the installation of the LS 55 Luminescence spectrometer and its accessories.  This device is a computer controlled ratioing luminescence spectrometer with the capability of measuring fluorescence, phosphorescence, chemiluminescence and bioluminescence by use of a xenon discharge lamp.  The sample detector is a gated photomultiplier with modified S5 response for operation up to around 650 nm.

Title: American DN 42 and DN 62 Ovens Operator's Manual
Desc: The American DN 42 and DN 62 Ovens Operator's Manual contains instructions for operating Constant Temperature Mechanical Ovens, Models DN-42 and DN-62.  It also explains those service/maintenance procedures the operator can perform.  These ovens are general purpose, constant temperature mechanical drying ovens used by a broad spectrum of industry for drying and curing of numerous substances and materials.

Title: American DK 42 and DK 62 Operator's Manual
Desc: The American DK-42 and DK-62 are Constant Temperature lab ovens with an operating range of 40°C to 200°C.  Maximum temperature is reached in approximately 70 minutes and the temperature control accuracy is +/- 2°C.  The thermoregulator is an electronic time division proportional control system, with built-in solid state relay, and has thermocouple temperature sensing.

Title: AO Spencer Rotary Microtome Model 820 Reference Manual
Desc: The AO Spencer Rotary Microtome Model 820 Reference Manual contains the installation, use, and maintenance of the American Optical rotary microtome.  Contains 3 identical copies in stock.

Title: ASTM Standards for Bomb Calorimetry and Combustion Methods Compilation, December 1988
Make: American Society for Testing and Materials
Desc: The ASTM Standards for Bomb Calorimetry and Combustion Methods Compilation was compiled by the American Society for Testing and Materials.  The compilation lists 8 standards that have been adopted by the ASTM and published December 1988.

Title: Amersham Pharmacia Biotech FRAC-100 and FRAC-200 Fraction Collector
Desc: The Amersham Pharmacia Biotech FRAC-100 and FRAC-200 Fraction Collectors are versatile instruments for automated fraction collections and evaluation of chromatograms.  In their standard forms they can collect up to 175 fractions in 12 mm diameter tubes, up to 95 fractions in 10-18 mm diameter tubes and up to 40 fractions in 30 mm diameter vials, with the help of the racks provided or with simple accessories.  When connected to a suitable monitor, they can measure peak heights, areas and retention time.  Fraction collectors will also indicate into which tubes the peaks have been collected.  These collectors can collect fractions in a variety of different ways, based either on time, volume or drop counting, controlled via simple programs specified by the operator.

Title: Amersham Pharmacia Biotech DNA-Directed Translation Kit
Desc: The Amersham Pharmacia Biotech DNA-Directed Translation Kit is a cell-free coupled transcription-translation system derived from E. coli.  A complete set of reagents is supplied enabling the reproducible expression of protein-coding information contained on a wide variety of exogenous DNA templates.  The kit is most suitable for use with circular plasmid DNA but under appropriate conditions can be used for the expression of genetic information from linear DNA templates.

Title: Amicon M2000 Motor Housing Ass"Y Assembly Procedures for Model 2000 Stirred Cell
Desc: The Amicon M2000 Motor Housing Ass"Y Assembly Procedures for Model 2000 Stirred Cell contains the assembly procedures as well as wire and parts diagrams, and a parts list.

Title: Aminco "Quickset" Bimetal Thermoregulator Instructions Number 545
Desc: The Aminco "Quickset" Bimetal Thermoregulator Instructions Number 545 is designed for use as a very accurate temperature regulating device.  It is operated on the principle of thermal deflection of a spiral bimetalic element.  Its design is the result of a great deal of planning by Aminco engineers to provide the utmost in sensitivity and reliability of control.  This regulator will maintain the temperature of a bath liquid constant within limits as close as plus-minus 0.005°C, under optimum conditions.  Under average conditions, where due consideration is given to insulation, stirring, etc., a control to within plus-minus 0.02°C may be expected when the thermoregulator is mounted in a vertical position.

Title: Aminco Supersensitive Relay Catalog Number 4-5300 Instructions
Desc: The Aminco Supersensitive Relay Catalog Number 4-5300 with power amplification of 50,000, is designed particularly for actuation by thermoregulators and other delicate contact-making devices.  It has an optimum control circuit current of 10 milliamperes a-c.  (not d-c), which prevents false operation oftimes experienced with ultra-low-current sensitive relays operating on microamperes.

Title: Aminco High-Pressured Shaking Assembly Micro Series 2-9/16 inch o.d. Instruction Number 760-B
Model: Micro Series 2-9 / 16 inch o.d. Shaking Assembly
Desc: The Aminco High-Pressured Shaking Assembly Micro Series 2-9/16 inch o.d. Instruction Number 760-B is designed for research involving high pressures and small quantities of material.  The Shaking Assembly consists of a reaction vessel, heating jacket, and shaking mechanism.  Valves and fittings on the shaking mechanism are of the 30,000 psi class.  Included in the shaking mechanisms are a combined inlet and bleeder valve, a pressure gauge, three-way connector, gauge connector, 1/4-inch o.d. stainless-steel tubing spiral, and a shut-off valve.  The motor is rated at 1/8 hp.  A length of 1/4-inch o.d. stainless-steel tubing is provided for connecting the Shaking Assembly to a gas supply.

Title: Aminco "Meter Mo" Pneumatic Proportioning Valve 44-19620, 44-19665, 44-19650, 44-19695
Desc: The Aminco "Meter Mo" Pneumatic Proportioning Valve 44-19620, 44-19665, 44-19650, and 44-19695 Instruction Number 902.  The "Meter Mo" Valve is a pneumatic-proportioning valve which is designed to alter the flow of either gases or liquids under pressure when it is activated by a control instrument.  The mechanism which performs this control on the valve is the positioner.  The positioner receives a 3 to 15 psi air signal from a control instrument (not supplied) which monitors the flow of the media down stream of the valve.  The controller, based on a preset flow requirement, sends a signal to the positioner.  The signal is interpreted by the positioner which then moves the valve-stem linkage.  The amount and direction of movement is determined by the strength of the signal.  The controller constantly measures the flow and sends a continuous signal to the positioner.  The valves are supplied in either the normally-open or normally-closed position.  The operation is the same in either position.

Title: Aminco High-Pressure Shaking Assembly 4-3/8 Inch o.d. Series Instruction Number 785-D
Desc: The Aminco High-Pressure Shaking Assembly 4-3/8 Inch o.d. Series Instruction Number 785-D is designed for research at pressures to 60,000 psi.  The Shaking Assembly consists of a reaction vessel, heating jacket, shaking mechanism, pressure gauge, inlet and outlet spirals, necessary valves and fittings, and six feet of high-pressure tubing.  Valves and fittings on the shaking mechanism are of the 15,000, 30,000, or 60,000 psi class.  Included in the shaking mechanisms are a combined inlet and bleeder valve, a pressure gauge, three-way connector, gauge connector, 1/4-inch o.d. tubing spirals, an angle valve, and two shut-off valves.  The motor is rated at 1/3 Horsepower, and is available in either 115 or 230 Volts.  Either voltage rating is available in open-type or explosion-proof motors.  A length of 1/4-inch o.d. tubing six feet long is provided, with the ends prepared for connecting the Shaking Assembly to the gas supply.

Title: Applied Test Systems Furnace Instruction Manual Number 169F with Series 2000 Temperature Controller
Desc: The Applied Test Systems Furnace Instruction Manual Number 169F with Series 2000 Temperature Controller also includes a manual for the LFE Instruments Model 2010 and 2011 Controllers "The PµP".  The furnace manual describes the installation, operation, tips on performance, and maintenance.  The ATS Series 2000 manual details the Temperature Control System which controls the amount of power to the resistive heating elements, as required to achieve and maintain the desired temperature as measured through the control thermocouple. Title: Bioanalytical Systems Acetylcholine Choline Assay Kit User Manual
Desc: The Bioanalytical Systems Acetylcholine Choline Assay Kit utilizes a covalently-attached enzyme reactor.  This manual provides the techniques for the preparation and use of this reactor, as well as the analytical column which precedes it.  Two cartridge columns are coupled in series in the liquid chromatography system.  First in line, the polymeric analytical column separates choline and acetylcholine as a pair well resolved from unretained peaks.  Retention is mostly regulated by ionic strength.  The second column, a ready-to-use immobilized enzyme reactor, is coupled to the outlet of the analytical column.  60 units each of choline oxidase and acetylcholinesterase are reacted with this support by BAS personnel.  It is to be stored at 4°C prior to, or between, use.  Amperometric detection is used because the hydrogen peroxide is easily oxidized at a Pt electrode held at +0.5 V vs Ag/AgCl.  While H2O2 can also be detected on carbon electrodes, the kinetics of electron transfer are slow, and the overall selectivity of the method suffers.

Title: Bio 101 Circlegrow
Desc: The Bio 101 Circlegrow is a nutrient medium for growing E. coli host cells to a high density.  The number of cells in a stationary culture grown in Circlegrow is usually greater than 3 times the number of cells in a stationary culture grown in a conventional growth medium.

Title: Cole-Parmer Models 8376-20 and 8376-30 Strip-Chart Recorders Instruction Manual
Desc: The Series 8376 Recorder is a multi-range potentiometric, null balance servo recorder which will provide an accurate, permanent, graphic record of the input signal.

Title: Cole-Parmer Digital pH Wand with ATC Operating Instructions
Desc: Cole-Parmer's 5895-75 pH wand features pH measurement with automatic temperature compensation and temperature measurement. Mode selection keys are located on the splash-proof keyboard. Display indicates mode - pH or C - in the lower left-hand corner.

Title: Cole-Parmer 4644 Series Digital Hot Plate/Stirrer Operating Manual
Desc: The Cole-Parmer 4644 Series Digital Hot Plate/Stirrer is a programmable, general purpose, digital laboratory hot plate with stirrer. All functions are from a digital front panel keyboard and display. Both the plate temperature and the stirrer are controllable to an accuracy never before offered in similar devices. Two manuals in stock.

Title: Cole-Parmer Masterflex Computerized Drive Operator's Manual
Desc: The direct-reading 7550 Pump Drive enables you to obtain consistent flow rates with superb speed regulation, even under variable pressure conditions. It's a great time saver where repetitive tasks and frequent changeovers are required. Just press a key to set up for new tubing sizes, materials, and flow rates. The digital display verifies all your settings.

Title: Bio 101 Circleprep Kit
Desc: The Bio 101 Circleprep Kit consists of the protocol and necessary reagents for 20 rapid isolations of about 50 ug of plasmid DNA.  The isolation procedure takes approximately 90 minutes from bacterial pellet to purified plasmid DNA.  There is a need for a rapid process of obtaining preparative quantities of substrate-quality plasmid DNA to perform intermediate steps in a longer experimental process.  The isolation of usable quantities of relatively pure plasmid DNA often requires one or more days.  The Circleprep Kit allows the investigator to obtain usable quantities of substrate-quality plasmid DNA in less than two hours; leaving enough time, for example, to cut it, ligate it to a fragment and transform it into competent host cells during one normal work day.  The plasmid DNA isolated by the Circleprep Kit often contains less RNA and cellular DNA than CsCl purified plasmid DNA and is typically greater than 80% covalently closed circular.

Title: Bio 101 Geneclean Kit
Desc: The Bio 101 Geneclean Kit contains a specially formulated silica matrix that binds single and double stranded DNA without binding DNA contaminants.  The "cleaning" process is rapid, efficient, and thorough.  Geneclean is a perfect substitute for alcohol precipitation.

Title: Cole-Parmer Masterflex L/S Cartridge Pump Head System Operating Manual
Desc: These pumps are designed to provide up to 12 simultaneously driven pump channels and the ability to provide nearly pulse free flow.

Title: Cole-Parmer Digi-Stalitic Digital Flow Controllers Operating and Maintenance Instruction Manual
Desc: Reliable, variable speed tubing pumps for continuous flow or calibrated flow control applications. In the calibration mode, only a single measurement is required to keep the system calibrated for a wide range of applications.

Title: Cole-Parmer Digi-Sense Temperature Controllers Operating and Maintenance Instruction Manual
Desc: This research grade proportional controller has alarm capabilities for reliable operation in critical heating and cooling applications. Teamed up with a Type J or K thermocouple, the controller detects the slightest deviation from a setpoint temperature and "proportions" the corrective action to the size of the temperature change.

Title: Cole-Parmer Masterflex Digital Unified Drives Operating Instruction Manual
Desc: Digital unified drives increase the utility of the "unified" concept of motor and speed controller in one compact package by adding a digital display of precalibrated flow rates for all standard Masterflex and Quick Load pump heads and providing for external control from a 4-20 ma source.

Title: Bio-Rad Laboratories MJ Mini Gradient Thermal Cycler PTC-1148 Operations Manual
Model: MJ Mini Gradient Thermal Cycler PTC-1148
Desc: The Bio-Rad Laboratories MJ Mini Gradient Thermal Cycler features premium cycling in a medium capacity cycler, ability to program and maintain a 16ºC temperature gradient, front-to-back, along the block for protocol optimization in a single run, upgradability to a real-time PCR system with the addition of the Mini Opticon real-time detector, integrated Hot Bonnet heated lid for oil-free thermal cycling, intuitive software with an easy-to-read interface for rapid input of programs, which may contain advanced protocol steps such as auto-time extension, auto-temperature increment, and variable ramp rates, choice of calculated sample temperature control for highest speed and accuracy or block control for compatibility with protocols designed for a variety of instrument types, space-saving design for easy setup and transportation, instant incubate feature for continuous-temperature incubations, and customizable factory-installed protocols.

Title: Cole-Parmer Masterflex Unified Drives Operating and Maintenance Instruction Manual
Desc: The most versatile electric drive incorporates a new permanent magnet D.C. motor, with increased torque at high speeds, is totally closed and permanently lubricated.

Title: Corning Model 355 Ion Analyzer Instruction Manual
Desc: This manual contains complete information for setting up and using the 355 ion analyzer.

Title: Bio-Rad Laboratories Digilab Qualimatic Infrared Spectrometer Operator's Manual
Desc: The Bio-Rad Laboratories Digilab Qualimatic is a Fourier Transform Infrared Spectrometer that is designed for routine in-plant quality control analyses.  This low-cost bench-top spectrophometer provides research grade, sensitivity and high reliability and yet it can be easily and quickly used by QC technicians.  The Qualimatic quickly analyzes a wide variety of solids, liquids, and gases and then generates an easy-to-read quantitative report of its infrared analysis.  The Qualimatic eliminates the burden of spectral interpretation.  Its microprocessor performs all the required calculations and provides a simple printed report for permanent records.

Title: Bio-Rad Laboratories Model 160 / 1.6 Power Supply Instruction Manual
Desc: The Bio-Rad Laboratories Model 160/1.6 variable voltage, high current power supply is a versatile yet economical power source.  This unique supply may be used for electrophoretic transfers as well as for running horizontal and preparative DNA cells.

Title: Bio-Rad Laboratories Affi-Gel Heparin for Protein Purification Bulletin 1096
Desc: The Bio-Rad Laboratories Affi-Gel Heparin for Protein Purification is a ready-to-use affinity support for the purification of a wide range of proteins.  It consists of Heparin coupled via amide bonds to crosslinked agarose beads.  As a result of this coupling, the gel is stable in all commonly used buffers and denaturants.  No loss of activity is apparent after multiple cycles of use and regeneration.  Affi-Gel Heparin contains 1 (+/- 0.2) mg Heparin/ml gel, and will bind at least 1.2 mg human antithrombin III/ml gel.  It is supplied hydrated in PBS, with 0.02% sodium azide as a preservative.

Title: Bio-Rad Laboratories Radioiodinating Proteins with Enzymobeads Technical Bulletin 1071
Desc: The Bio-Rad Laboratories Radioiodinating Proteins with Enzymobeads Technical Bulletin 1071; May 1981.  Bio-Rad's new solid phase radioiodination reagent provides the gentlest possible conditions for radiolabeling.  Radiolabeling with the Enzymobead reagent is based on enzymatic iodination rather than oxidative substitution.  The Enzymobead reagent consists of immobilized preparations of lactoperoxidase and glucose oxidase which are carefully blended to provide optimal enzymatic activity as a system.  The solid phase support for the lactoperoxidase and glucose oxidase consists of hydrophilic spheres several microns in diameter.  On addition of glucose to a suspension of Enzymobeads, Na125I and protein, the immobilized glucose oxidase continuously generates a small, steady amount of hydrogen peroxide.  The lactoperoxidase, in turn, catalyzes the peroxide oxidation of labeled iodide to iodine.  Then the labeled iodine reacts with protein to produce radioiodinated protein.

Title: Corning Guide to pH Measurement Guide
Desc: The Corning Guide to pH Measurement Guide.

Title: Corning pH Meter 7 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Corning pH Meter Model 7 is a highly reliable general purpose instrument capable of pH and multivolt measurements. The seven-inch taut-band meter provides excellent readability and repeatability.

Title: Bio-Rad Laboratories Sub-Cell Electrophoresis System Instruction Manual
Desc: The Bio-Rad Laboratories Sub-Cell Electrophoresis System comprises a flexible cell which efficiently separates DNA restriction fragments and other nucleic acids, a power supply, and precut blotting media.  Although the system is principally for simple electrophoresis of submersible gels, it may also be used with agarose gel bridges.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Corning Water Purifier LD-5a Installation and Operating Instructions
Desc: The Corning Water Purifier LD-5a is designed to utilize Corning's organic and inorganic removal cartidges in a single unit. Water purity is continuously monitored by a glass-platinum electrode. The dual unit is provided with five purity monitoring levels that will satisfy various needs, and with a "purge" position that allows water to pass through unmonitored. Purity is measured as resistivity in ohm-cm.

Title: Corning Mega-Pure Eleven Liter Automatic Water Still Operating and Installation Instructions
Desc: The Corning Mega-Pure Eleven Liter Automatic Water Still is a compact, all glass and Teflon unit designed to provide 13 liters per hour of ultra high purity distilled water. The product water is non-pyrogenic per U.S.P. XIX and will have a resistivity of 1.0 megohm-cm or higher at the product outlet using most tap water as feed.

Title: Bio-Rad Laboratories Protein Assay
Desc: The Bio-Rad Laboratories Protein Assay is a dye-binding assay based on the differential color change of a dye in response to various concentrations of protein.  In research applications, this assay is recommended as a replacement for other protein assays, especially the widely used Lowry method, for several reasons: First, the Bio-Rad Protein Assay is much easier to use.  It requires one reagent and five minutes to perform as compared to three reagents and 30-40 minutes typical for the Lowry assay.  Second, because the absorbance of the dye-protein complex is relatively stable, the Bio-Rad assay does not require the critical timing necessary for the Lowry.  Third, the Bio-Rad assay is free from most of the interferences which limit the application of the Lowry assay (see Table 1).  A summary of five major protein assay methods is shown in Table 2.

Desc: The CWB Rapid Moisture/Volatiles Tester automates the accurate but time consuming laboratory technique for moisture determinations. The laboratory method involves oven drying, cooling in a desicator and weighing until a constant sample weight is achieved. The percent of moisture and/or volatiles is calculated from the weight loss.

Title: Bio-Rad Laboratories Zeta-Probe Blotting Membranes Instruction Manual
Desc: The Bio-Rad Laboratories Zeta-Probe Blotting Membranes are quaternary amine derivatized nylon membranes which have unique binding and handling properties that make them ideally suited for nucleic acid, and some protein, blotting applications.  Zeta-Probe membranes possess a high tensile strength.  They won't shrink, tear, or become brittle during transfer, baking, hybridization, or reprobing.  Zeta-Probe membranes are heat resistant, non-flammable, and autoclavable.  Zeta-Probe membranes are naturally hydrophilic with no added wetting agents.  These membranes are resistant to a wide variety of chemicals, including 100% formamide, 2M NaOH, 4M HCI, acetone, most alcohols, DMSO, DMF, and chlorinated aliphatic hydrocarbons.  The nominal porosity of Zeta-Probe membranes is 0.45 µm.  When stored at 23-25ºC, Zeta-Probe membranes are stable for at least one year.

Desc: The Blue M Stabil-Therm Mechanical Convection Horizontal Air-Flow Electric Utility Ovens with Patented Power-O-Matic 70 Temperature Control Solid-State Proportioning Control System Models OV-472A-2, OV-475-2, OV-490A-2, OV-500C2, OV510A-2, and OV-520C-2 are manufactured to the highest standards of the industry and are designed to give reliable and satisfactory service, if properly installed and maintained. Title: B/R Instrument Solvent Recycling System & Distillation Systems Model 9400 & 9600 Operating Manual
Desc: The B/R Instrument Solvent Recycling System & Distillation Systems Model 9400 & 9600 represent state-of-the-art development in high purity solvent recycling.  Purification is accomplished by separation of impurities based upon differences in boiling point compared to that of the desired solvent.  The core of the system is a spinning band distillation column which utilizes a helical shaped Teflon band through the length of the column.  This band is rotated while the solvent is being distilled, and results in much higher separating efficiencies than would otherwise be possible.  The system is designed to efficiently purify contaminated solvents back to a grade suitable for reuse.  It is also used as an efficient distillation system in laboratory settings.  The Packed Column models use a packing material to create surface that increases separating efficiencies.  This system is also effective for solvent recycling and efficient laboratory distillations.  The system is microprocessor controlled, which provides simple and highly automated operation.  Nineteen memory areas are available in the microprocessor controller for storage of various programs for repetitive distillations.

Title: Dionex Gradient Mixer Installation Instructions and Troubleshooting Guide

These provide increased cleaning power along with built in sweep frequency to ensure uniform cleaning activity throughout the bath.  The 1/2 and 3/4 gallon models have a molded dip in their rims to facilitate emptying of solution from the tank.  The three larger sizes have built in drains and are supplied with tank drain kits.  Each model can be purchased in three different configurations -- with a Mechanical Timer, with a Mechanical Timer plus Heat, and with Digital Control, plus Heat and Timer.

Title: Brinkmann Instruments Buchi/Brinkmann Rotary Evaporators with Cold Trap Condensers Product Bulletin
Desc: The Brinkmann Instruments Buchi/Brinkmann Rotary Evaporators with Cold Trap Condensers Product Bulletin describes the Models M, R, RE, 115EX and EL that are now available with cold trap condensers offering a more compact design and more efficient distillation than evaporators with tap water cooled condensers.  The cold trap condenser uses dry ice (or mechanical refrigeration) and acetone as a coolant to give a colder surface to condense solvent vapors than a tap water cooled condenser.  This assures maximum condensation of vapors and minimizes the amount of uncondensed vapors that may be lost through the vacuum line.  The cold trap condenser is particularly useful when tap water temperature is too high to efficiently condense the solvent vapors (especially during the summer months) and when evaporating low boiling solvents.

Title: Dynisco PT300 Series Low Level Output Transducers Instruction Manual
Desc: The Dynisco 300 Series transducers are bonded metal foil strain gage instrument. The principle of operation is that the pressure to be measured is applied to a metal diaphragm which becomes stressed due to the pressure on one side. This stress is measured by the strain sensing elements and is converted through the strain gages, which are wired into a wheatstone bridge circuit, to an electrical output proportional to the sensing pressure. Desc: The Brooks Mass Flow Measurement System For Indicating, Controlling, Blending, Recording, and Totalizing Bulletin displays the reasons why Brooks Instrument is the best choice in mass flow measurement systems. Title: Brooks Instrument Mass Flow Controller Model 5850C Installation Instructions

Title: Brooks Instrument Mass Flow Controller Thru-Flow Series Design Specifications
Desc: The Brooks Instrument Mass Flow Controller Thru-Flow Series is designed for automatic control of difficult to handle gases, including silane and other gases which tend to plug or coat, by utilizing a straight through flow measuring tube having no bends or bypass.  The entire flow stream is measured without an internal flow divider.  This unrestricted flow path eliminates blockage and/or deterioration of accuracy.  The flow sensor, using thermodynamic principles, produces a 0 to 5 v dc output signal proportional to mass flow rate.  this output signal is continuously compared to a command signal which represents the desired flow rate.  Deviation between command signal and output flow signal is automatically corrected through the control valve.

Title: Brown Boveri SE 790 Potentiometer Recorder
Desc: The Brown Boveri SE 790 Potentiometer Recorder is a portable recorder in DIN A4 format.  It uses perpendicular coordinates to record the function dependency of two DC electrical quantities Y - f(x), or an integrated time shift unit to record a DC electrical quantity in relation to time Y - f(t).  It can be used the same way to represent electrical (physical, chemical, biological, etc.) quantities provided they can be converted into DC voltages and currents with the appropriate sensors.  The recorder is designed as a compact device for mains voltages of 110 V and 220/240 V.  Two measuring units, "1" and "5", with calibrated measuring ranges graded in decades and steplessly adjustable intermediate ranges, enable the recording of values from 1 mV/cm to 10V/cm on measuring unit 1, and of 0.1 mV/cm to 50 V/cm on measuring unit 5.  Measuring unit 5 is also equipped with a calibrated zero suppression of 2 x 100 %, which means that even relatively small signals with a large base level can be enlarged up to three times and then represented.  The possibility of switching from XY to Yt operation, with external time unit control such as Start, Hold, Reset and Pen Down, opens up a further range of applications.  Because of its many additional features, such as measurement input via plug-in device and limit contacts, event marking, monitor output and input inversion, the device is able to adapt ideally to each different measurement task.

Title: Brookfield More Solutions to Sticky Problems: Guide to Getting More From Your Brookfield Viscometer

This guide will help point out the way to getting more from this apparatus.  Contains graphs and diagrams for explanatory purposes.

Title: Brookfield More Solutions to Sticky Problems: Guide to Getting More From Your Brookfield Viscometer
Desc: The Brookfield More Solutions to Sticky Problems: A Guide to Getting More From Your Brookfield Viscometer is a booklet that supplements the user's manual by guiding the way for the person wishing to explore in greater depth the field of viscosity measurement, with an emphasis on Brookfield equipment. Title: Brookfield Dial Viscometer Operating Instructions
Desc: The Brookfield Dial Viscometer measures fluid viscosity at given shear rates.  Viscosity is a measure of a fluid's resistance to flow.  The Dial Viscometer rotates a sensing element in a fluid and measures the torque necessary to overcome the viscous resistance to the induced movement.  This is accomplished by driving the immersed element, which is called a spindle, through a beryllium copper spring.  The degree to which the spring is wound, indicated by the red pointer, is proportional to the viscosity of the fluid.  The Viscometer is able to measure over a number of ranges since, for a given spring deflection, the actual viscosity is proportional to the spindle speed and is related to the spindle's size and shape.  For a material of given viscosity, the resistance will be greater as the spindle size and/or rotational speed increase.  The minimum viscosity range is obtained by using the largest spindle at the highest speed; the maximum range by using the smallest spindle at the slowest speed.

Title: Buchi Evaporators Models R, RE and EL
Desc: The Buchi Evaporators Models R, RE and EL are rotating evaporators used for extracting many different kinds of substances by evaporation.  By applying vacuum, not only can high boiling solvents be evaporated, but also heat sensitive compounds can be concentrated at low temperatures.  Other possible applications include the drying of powders, freeze-drying and multiple extractions.  By rotating the evaporator flask in a heating bath, the evaporating surface of the solution is increased considerably and the heat transfer from the water bath to the liquid is improved.  There are no hot spots formed due to overheating at the surface of the flask.  By use of the speed control, it is possible to prevent foaming and "bumping" of the liquid and to effectively concentrate viscous materials.  Working under vacuum permits the efficient and careful distillation of high boiling materials and the low temperature distillation of heat-sensitive materials.  The inlet feed tube permits the continuous feed of the liquid into the evaporating flask without interrupting the distillation so that volumes greater than the capacity of the evaporating flask can be evaporated.

Title: Buchi GKR-50 Distillation Oven Instructions
Desc: The Buchi GKR-50 Distillation Oven Instructions manual is a trilingual set of instructions for the GKR-50.  This glass tube oven consists essentially of two concentric tubes of borosilicate glass mounted in the holder.  The heating is accomplished by a totally transparent electrically conducting semiconductor layer vaporized on to the exterior of the glass tube.  This heating layer is supplied with network voltage from the control unit via the supply wires and the two contact rings.  The outer tube prevents damage to the heating tube and acts simultaneously as a guard for the current-carrying parts.  Its inner surface carries a thin, transparent vapor-coated layer that has excellent reflection properties for IR radiation; this keeps outward heat losses to a minimum.  This good thermal insulation prevents the external temperature of the oven from rising much above 100ºC, even at the maximum internal temperature of 250ºC, so that the oven can be handled without any danger whatever.  The holder contains an iris diaphragm, the opening of which can be adjusted infinitely from 6 to 50 mm by moving the lever.  The diaphragm can be fixed at any desired position by turning the knob to the right.  This manual contains additional diagrams and information.

Title: Buchi Micro-Distillation Oven Model GKR-50 Product Bulletin
Desc: The Buchi Micro-Distillation Oven Model GKR-50 uses the Kugelrohr (ball tube) technique to provide rapid, efficient distillaiion of small valume samples with virtually no loss of material.  Model GKR-50 can purify chemcial reaction products and perform ffractional distillation of up to four compuonds (the boiling point of each substance must differ by approximately 20ºC).  Sublimation and vacuum drying of solids can be accomplished with an optional attachement.  The oven heats up to 250ºC and operates under a vacuum as high as 1 x 10^-5 torr.  Model GKR-50 features air heating and a drive assembly to rotate the ball tube for uniform heat distribution.  The double-glass chamber permits visual observation of the distillatin.  The outer chamber acts as an insulator to the inner oven chamber, which has an electrically conductive coating on its surface to produce the required temperature.

Desc: The BYK-Gardner Haze-Gloss Reflectometer 4600 & 4601 are stationary instruments designed to measure specular gloss and reflection haze on paint coatings, plastics, binders, pigments, and metal surfaces.  The sample surface is illuminated at a defined angle and the reflected light is measured photoelectrically.  Selection of the appropriate angle of illumination is dependent on the specific gloss level of the sample surface: matt, medium, or high gloss.  Advanced electronic engineering in the development and production of haze-gloss provides a performance level, ease of operation and high accuracy at a level not previously achieved.

Title: BYK-Gardner Spectrogard Color System Quality Control Software Operator's Manual
Desc: The BYK-Gardner Spectrogard Color System Quality Control Software is designed to determine the color and spectral characteristics of a wide variety of materials under laboratory and industrial conditions.  The System consists of three major components: the Spectrogard scanning spectrophotometer; an IBM compatible host computer with at least 640K RAM and a fixed disk drive (10MB minimum), color monitor and interface boards and cables; and system software to measure, integrate, evaluate, report, and store color and spectral data.  A printer, although optional, is recommended.  Any IBM compatible dotmatrix printer equipped with a parallel port will operate on the system.  The Spectrogard Color System can measure samples in reflectance or transmission modes.  When the reflectance mode is used, the specular component can be included or excluded consistent with operator preference.  The software supplied with the Spectrogard Color System permits choice of two or ten degree observers, multiple color scales and illuminants, asymmetrical tolerancing and delta functions.  The system also computes values for the chromaticity difference, the total color difference, as well as yellowness and whiteness indexes based on established ASTM standard methods.

Title: Jasco Model 880-81 Back-Pressure Regulator Instruction Manual
Desc: The Jasco Model 880-81 Back-Pressure Regulator is specially designed for the use in supercritical fluid extraction and supercritical fluid chromatography.  Its operating principle is totally different from conventional regulators, and is based on high-speed flow switching.  The model 880-81 has many advantages over conventional regulators as low dead-volume prevents fractions from being re-mixed each other, enabling sharp cut-off between fractions, the valve needle is vibrating and continuously forcing precipitate solutes to pass through the value path, allowing stable operation without blocking of the valve path, control pressure can be set simply by the digital switch in three-digit number, operating pressure is displayed on LED digital meter in three-digit number, and the valve body is thermostatted by a PID temperature controller.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Jay Control Model 305 Process Monitor Digital Meter Relays Owners Manual
Desc: The Jay Control Model 305 Process Monitor Digital Meter Relays provides low cost, easy to use indication and control outputs.  Applications may include use in central control stations for monitoring distant measuring or testing devices.  The Model 305 provides for a variety of ranges for voltage and current inputs.  There are five standard voltage and four standard current ranges which monitor most conventional transmitting devices.  Coarse gain and offset ranging are easily accomplished by means of a plug-in socketed resistor set.  A front panel gain and zero control allow for easy calibration once the unit is mounted in a panel to display in any appropriate engineering units.  With the set point controller option, a number of alarm and control modes can be utilized; single set point control with two zone operation, dual set point control with three zone operation, or dual set points with programmable hysteresis operating in two zones.  The set point controller employs one relay with a Form C contact and 2000 VAC 50/60Hz isolation to meter ground per set point.  The entire unit utilizes VLSI circuitry to perform the digital conversion.  The signal conditioning and set point modules are plug-in for easy serviceability.  All modules are housed in a compact 1/8 DIN standard case.

Title: J-Kem Trinity-2M Instructions
Desc: The J-Kem Trinity-2M Power Controller is a solid state version of a variac.  This unit controls power by varying the voltage at the receptacle depending on the position of the Power Control Knob set by the User.  As the Power Control Knob is turned in a clockwise direction, the voltage present at the power outlet increases.  The voltage at the power outlet is shown on the Voltage Readout meter.

Title: J-Kem Model 150/Timer User's Manual
Desc: The J-Kem Model 150/Timer User's Manual contains the operating instructions for this temperature controller.  It describes the tuning and operating procedures of this unit.  Contains 3 identical copies in stock.

Title: Jofra Model EVJ 200 S Temperature Field Calibrator
Desc: The Jofra Model EVJ 200 S Temperature Field Calibrator has been designed with the philosophy of EVJ-temperature calibrators, namely, physically to bring each sensor to a series of pre-determined temperatures and calibrate display/recorder or thermostats accordingly.  The EVJ 200 S may be used for all temperature sensors, including RTD's and thermocouplers.  The EVJ 200 S gives the user the availability to calibrate the complete temperature system from sensor to indicator.  The use of EVJ 200 S offers a number of great advantages above alternative methods of temperature calibration.

Title: Johnke Model AG/5 Glossy Print Dryer
