The A-G/5 consists of a welded steel frame containing a seamless polished stainless steel drum with an electric heating element, a control box with motor, power switch, speed and heat control, a special lint-free preshrunk canvas conveyor apron, a squeegee roller and the rods and rollers to convey the prints around the drum and into the print tray.

Title: Johnson Controls Single Input & Two Input Pneumatic Receiver-Controllers
Desc: The Johnson Controls Single Input T-9001 & T-9005 & Two Input T-9002 & T-9006 Pneumatic Receiver-Controllers:  The T-9001 series receiver-controllers are designed for use with remote temperature, humidity, or pressure transmitters to provide proportional control of pneumatic devices.  The T-9001 and T-9002 are designed for high volume applications while the T-9005 and T-9006 are ideally suited for low volume applications.  All units have built-in restrictor manifolds which provide restricted supply air to low volume remote transmitters thus requiring only one air line connection between the two instruments.  In addition, they can be used with any pneumatic output device which has a calibrated output of 3 to 15 PSIG (21 to 105 kPa), such as a process controller.

Title: Keithley Model 2400 SourceMeter User's Manual

Title: Kepco Model JQE 150-3.5 (M) Compact Power Supply
Desc: The Kepco Model JQE 150-3.5 (M) Compact Power Supply is a general purpose, precision regulated voltage source in the "half rack" configuration.  JQE power supplies feature full range voltage control and current limit adjustment by means of multi-turn front panel controls.  JQE power supplies have linear, full-dissipation series-regulators driven by an integrated circuit operational amplifier.  A sharp current-limit circuit renders the power supply completely short-circuit proof.  JQE power supplies may be readily converted to provide constant current by the addition of an external sensing resistor and a "current control."  The output of the JQE power supply is completely programmable.  All necessary connections are available on terminals at the rear barrier strip.

A sharp current-limit circuit renders the power supply completely short-circuit proof.  JQE Power Supplies may be readily converted to provide constant current by the addition of an external sensing resistor and a "current control".  The output of the JQE Power Supply is completely programmable.  All necessary connections are available on terminals at the rear barrier-strip.

The BOP incorporates two separate control channels, for local or remote control of the output current and the output voltage.  In addition, bonding currents for bipolar voltage and current limiting are provided which may be adjusted manually or can be remotely programmed. Title: Kern Full-Circle Polarimeter
Desc: The Kern Full-Circle Polarimeter is constructed according to the well-known principle of penumbral balance and is fitted with a Laurent quartz lamella.  The field of vision of standard types of commercial polarimeters has until now been divided into two semi-circular portions, which must be adjusted so as to show equal light intensity.  The Kern Full-Circle Polarimeter, however, has its field divided into three areas, of which the two external segments are equally bright, while the center one forms the area of contrast.  This tripartite division greatly facilitates balancing, which is also much more precise than with the usual types.

Title: Micromeritics Model 725 Automatic Injector Instruction Manual

Title: Micromeritics Model 2200 High Speed Surface Area Analyzer Instruction Manual
Desc: The Micromeritics Model 2200 High Speed Surface Area Analyzer measures the surface area of powdered or solid porous materials by determining the quantity of gas necessary to form a single layer of gas molecules, a so-called monomolecular layer, on a representative sample.  Testing is accomplished using nitrogen gas at the temperature of liquid nitrogen, because, under these conditions, the gas molecules are strongly attracted and held--technically called adsorbed--on the solid surface.  Moreover, the space occupied by each adsorbed molecule is known within relatively narrow limits under this condition.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Micromeritics Model 220/00000/0X Surface Area Analyzer
Desc: The Micromeritics Model 220/00000/0X Surface Area Analyzer measures the surface area of powdered or solid porous materials by determining the quantity of gas necessary to form a single layer of gas molecules, a so-called monomolecular layer, on a representative sample.  Testing is accomplished using nitrogen gas at the temperature of liquid nitrogen, because, under these conditions, the gas molecules are strongly attracted and held--technically called adsorbed--on the solid surface.  Moreover, the space occupied by each adsorbed molecule is known within relatively narrow limits under this condition.

Title: Micromeritics Model 728 Autosampler
Desc: The Micromeritics Model 728 Autosampler is a microcomputer-operated, sampling/controller designed for use with most commercially available automatic HPLC injection valves.  It performs repetitive injections at user-selectable time intervals.  The Autosampler accommodates remote control of injection time by contact closure and complete remote control of injection time, number of injections per vial, rinses, an auxiliary timer, and, with certain valves, loop size by means of a standard RS-232 interface.

Title: Microtrac Special Closed Dry Cell Assembly Sampler for Cat 7997
Desc: The Microtrac Special Closed Dry Cell Assembly Sampler for Cat 7997 has been designed to  operate with the Standard Range Analyzer under three different conditions.  The first is under a total vacuum condition; this means operation of the dry sampler with no aspirating air source.  This would be considered a low handling when analyzing fragile materials.  The second method of operating the sampler is supplying an exhaust air source to the exhaust block aspirator.  When supplying an air source to this exhaust block aspirator, the velocity flow of the material is increased.  Varying the air pressure at this point will cause a higher degree of turbulence at the throttle plate in the sample cup, which will increase the separation force of the material as it flows through the closed dry sampler.  The third method of operation would be supplying an air source at the top aspirator, this particular method of sample dispersing would be used if the material was for example metallic.  Each material has different handling characteristics.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Microtrac 7981 Dry Particle-Size Monitor
Desc: The Microtrac 7981 Dry Particle-Size Monitor continuously measures at operator selected time intervals and particle size data is output at the end of each successive measurement cycle as sample is continuously drawn from the process and passed through the measurement zone of the particle size analyzer.  Additionally, the analyzer can be operated in a manual batch mode using an internal dry powder sample conditioner.  The sample is simply loaded into the batch sampler in a sufficient quantity and is delivered to the analyzer measurement zone in the same way the process material is delivered.

Title: Microtrac II Models 7997-10 & 7997-20 Partical Size Analyzer
Desc: The Lees & Northrup Microtrac II Models 7997-10 & 7997-20 Particle Size Analyzers are ruggedly constructed industrial instruments which are equally useful for laboratory research or for on-line process control.  These Analyzers provide simple, fast and reliable analysis of particle size of wet slurry mixtures.  It is particularly useful for batch analysis in production or quality control laboratories of industries where control of particle size is important for quality and/or economy.  The Analyzers utilize the phenomenon of low-angle forward-scattered light from a laser beam projected through a stream of particles.  The amount and direction of light scattered by the particles is measured by an optical detector array and then analyzed by a microcomputer, which calculates the size distribution of particles in the mixture.  Modular construction provides convenience and portability.  These Analyzers consist of a Control Module, an Optics Module, and a Sample Recirculator.

Title: Micromet Microdielectrometer System II
Desc: The Micromet Microdielectrometer System II uses a technique for measuring the low-frequency dielectric and conducting properties of relatively weakly conducting materials, such as resins, plastics, adhesives, and rubber.  The technique uses a novel miniature sensor, the Microdielectrometer "chip," in conjunction with specially configured instrumentation to measure both the permittivity and loss factor of materials placed in direct contact with the sensor electrodes.  The measurements can be used to monitor changes in dielectric and conducting properties that accompany chemical reactions, such as curing of resins, and to examine the effects of temperature and/or aging on these properties after cure.  This equipment is a computer controlled Microdielectrometry instrumentation package.  The system is designed for use with a minimum of adjustments, and standard software permits users to run experiments without additional programming.  For those users who wish to sequence their own measurements, Micromet's firmware enhancements to the BASIC language allow one to write simple BASIC programs that control all of the instrumentation functions.

Title: Nanochem Gas Purifier Operation Manual
Desc: The L Series Gas Purifiers contain Nanochem Resin, a beaded, pourous, chemically stable organolithium polymer that immediately and irreversibly binds to a variety of dilute vapor-phase impurity molecules that may be contained in a non-reactive gas stream.

Title: Micropump Washington Gear Pump Model 210/211-56C Service Instructions
Desc: The Micropump Washington Gear Pump Model 210/211-56C Service Instructions describes the general and specific maintenance that can be conducted on this equipment.  Includes exploded view diagram of parts and a spare parts listing.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Narco Scientific Pneumatic Pulse Transducer Operator's Manual
Desc: The Narco Scientific Pneumatic Pulse Transducer a sensitive piezoelectric transducer for detection of pulsatile volume changes. This transducer is especially suitable for detecting pulsations in a rat's tail for indirect systolic blood pressure determinations.

Title: Narco Scientific Programmed Electro-Sphygmomanometer Operator's Manual

Title: Narco Scientific Small Animal Study Unit Operator's Manual

Title: Narco Scientific Korotkoff Sound Microphone Operator's Manual

It may be taped directly onto an extremity and used in conjunction with a separate occluding cuff for obtaining indirect systolic and diastolic blood pressure measurements on animals such as dogs, chickens, cats, monkeys, etc. It is recommended where the structure of the limb does not permit the use of the conventional cuff with built-in microphone.

Title: Millipore Steritest II System for the Sterility Testing of Pharmaceutical and Veterinary Products
Desc: The Millipore Steritest II System for the Sterility Testing of Pharmaceutical and Veterinary Products was designed to "optimize" the membrane method of sterility testing.  Steritest is a sterile "closed system" that eliminates any possibility of exogenous contamination to the maximum possible extent.  The time consuming and expensive washing and sterilizing procedures, as required for conventional methods, are eliminated with the use of sterile, single-use Steritest inspection units.  There is an additional advantage in the saving of bench area necessary for the equipment.  This can be important when the means of sterilization and sterile working areas are limited.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Millipore OM109 Vacuum Pressure Pump Operation and Maintenance Instructions
Desc: The Millipore OM109 Vacuum Pressure Pump is a portable AC-powered source of vacuum or pressure for filtration and other continuous or intermittent laboratory use.  The motor and pump are permanently lubricated.  Operating noise is low and is further minimized by rubber-cup mounts, and inlet and outlet filter/muffler silencers.  All internal surfaces of the pump (except the stainless steel leaf-valves) are Teflon-coated to prevent possible corrosion of the aluminum surfaces.  The neoprene diaphragm is also protected with an Armalon cover to prevent attack by chemicals or solvent vapors, thus prolonging its use.

Title: Millipore Milli-Q Type I Reagent Grade Water System Operator's Manual
Desc: The Millipore Milli-Q Type I Reagent Grade Water System polishes water that has been pretreated (by deionization, distillation or for best results, Continental Milli-RO reverse osmosis) to give the purest water commercially available.  Long life disposable cartridges remove dissolved organics by activated carbon adsorption and ionized inorganics by mixed bed deionization.  Final Millipore membrane filtration removes all microorganisms larger than 0.22 micrometers.  The four bowl configuration contains a prefilter cartridge to provide the additional filtration required when feeding a Milli-Q system from a central system.  The four bowl configuration may also contain an Organex-Q cartridge for low organic level applications.

Title: Neslab Exacal Bath Circulators, En-Flow Through Coolers and Aerocooler-100 Ambient Bath Cooler Manua

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Infradry Multiple Sample Infrared Drying Oven Operating Manual

Title: Millipore OM 163 MilliBlot SDE Electroblotting Apparatus Operating and Maintenance Instructions
Desc: The Millipore OM 163 MilliBlot SDE Electroblotting Apparatus was designed to perform the transfer of proteins from polyacrylamide gels to membranes in a fast and efficient manner.  Complete transfers can be accomplished in 15 to 45 minutes (average of 30 minutes); a distinct improvement over hitherto existing standard buffer-tank, and graphite "semi-dry" transfer systems.  This system can accommodate six or more gels for transfer at one time with appropriate dialysis membranes separating each trans-unit.  The unit's uniquely designed, removable electrodes provide high conductivity with low heat generation.  The cathode's aluminum plate serves as a heat-sink which evenly disperses heat during the transfer process, and requires no external cooling system.  This design allows the unit to be operated at higher current levels, without compromising resolution, yet taking less transfer time.

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Rollacell Tissue Culture Apparatus Operating Manual
Desc: The Rollacell is a precision roller apparatus used for production of cells in cylindrical bottles. Modular in design, the apparatus comprises a power console which accomodates roller tiers that can be installed as the need arises.

Title: Millipore Point-Of-Use Gun for use with Millipore's Compact Laboratory Water Systems
Model: ZD5 POU STR / ZD5 POU COI
Desc: The Millipore Point-Of-Use Gun for use with Millipore's Compact Laboratory Water Systems is easy to use.  The gun's tubing is connected directly to the Compact System's recirculation loop, providing fully-recirculated water at the point of delivery.  Automatic recirculation keeps the water in the tubing and system pure between uses.  All wetted surfaces are constructed of PTFE, FEP or PFA, the lowest extractable polymers known.  The flow of water can be controlled drop-by-drop for filling graduated cylinders, or in a steady stream with the trigger lock engaged.  Water can be simultaneously dispensed from the three-way valve on the system and from the Point-Of-Use Gun up to 7 feet away.  The Point-Of-Use Gun comes with a wall-mounted clip for easy storage when the gun is not in use.

Title: Buchi R0229
Desc: The solvent in the evaporating flask is heated by the heating bath. The rotation of the evaporating flask ensures an intensive exchange of heat and mass within the contents of the flask, forming a thin film of solvent on the inner surface of the flask. This combination of turbulence and film prevents local overheating and ensures high distillation speed

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Dissolved Oxygen Controller Operating Manual

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Dissolved Oxygen Electrode/Probe Operating Manual

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Automatic Mini pH Control System Operating Manual

Title: Milton Roy Milroyal D Controlled Volume Pump Instruction Manual
Desc: The Milton Roy Milroyal D Controlled Volume Pump is a reciprocating plunger, positive displacement pump designed to deliver accurately measured liquid volumes against a positive differential pressure (or head) between pump suction and discharge.  Precision built, the pump performs this function with a repetitive accuracy of plus or minus one percent of mean delivered volume.  Basically, the pump consists of a drive unit, plunger and displacement chamber or liquid end in which the plunger reciprocates.  The pump delivers a controlled volume of liquid with each discharge stroke.  Pump capacity is adjustable by changing plunger stroking speed and/or length.  Capacity adjustment can be made manually or automatically by signal from remote process control instruments.  Selection of capacity control methods is determined by the nature of the application.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Mini pH Recorder Module Operating Manual

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Bioflo III Microprocessor Controlled Lab-Scale Fermentor Operating Manual

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Portable Gyrotory Shaker Operating Manual

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Gyrotory Tier Shaker Operating Manual

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Aquatherm Water Bath Shaker Operating Manual

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Gyrotory Water Bath Shaker Operating Manual

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Microgen Bench-Top Fermenter Guide to Operations

Title: New Brunswick Scientific Modular Microferm Bench Top Fermenter Operating Manual

Title: Milton Roy Laboratory Data Control Minipump Instrument Pump Models 396 and 2396 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Milton Roy Laboratory Data Control Minipump Instrument Pump Models 396 and 2396 are reciprocating plunger, positive displacement type pumps.  They are designed to produce liquid flow in precise quantities against positive pressure up to 6,000 psig.  A drive-gear motor rotates an eccentric at low speed, causing a plunger to reciprocate within a liquid end.  Model 2396 consists of two pump bodies (hence two liquid ends) mounted on either side of the drive motor.  The liquid end contains a high-pressure plunger seal and back-up ring to prevent leakage, and double ball suction and discharge check valves to precisely control flow direction.  The manual micrometer dial(s) controls the stroke length of the pump, which in turn controls the flow rate.  Adjustment of the flow rate may be made while the pump is either operating or shut down.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Newport Digital Panel Voltometer Owners Manual
Desc: Newport Digital Panel Voltometers are low cost, reliable instruments for digital display of analog bipolar voltages. The display is 1999 counts on any of four ranges from 199.9mV to 199.9V.

Title: Milton Roy Laboratory Data Control Minipump Models 396 and 2396 Instruction Manual

A drive-gear motor rotates an eccentric at low speed causing a plunger to reciprocate within the liquid end.  The liquid end contains a high-pressure plunger seal and back-up ring to prevent leakage, and double-ball suction and discharge check valves to precisely control flow direction.  The manual micrometer dial controls the stroke length of the pump which controls the flow rate.  Adjustments of the flow rate may be made while the pump is operating or shut off.  The pump is precision-built of durable materials, assuring long life and accuracy.  Contains 3 identical copies in stock.

Title: Newport Model 850 Series Linear Actuators Operator's Instruction Manual

Title: Minolta Chroma Meter CR-241
Desc: The Minolta Chroma Meter CR-241 is a tristimulus color analyzer for measuring reflective colors of surfaces.  The CR-241 has interchangeable measurement areas of 1.8 or 0.3mm diameter.  These small measurement areas allow measurements of the color of extremely small specimens, such as printed letters.  The CR-241 utilizes a microscope-like single-lens-reflex viewing system, and is equipped with a specimen stage that can be moved back and forth or from side to side for precise positioning of the specimen.  The CR-241 uses a 45/0 illumination and viewing geometry with 360-degree ring illumination for accurate measurements of textured or glossy surfaces.

Title: Newport Model 835 Laser Pico-Watt Digital Power Meter Instruction Manual

Title: Newport Acousto Optic Modulator Operating Manual
Desc: The modulator system is a tellurium dioxide crystal with a lithium niobate transducer. The RF input should not exceed 1 watt CW. The input laser beam can be varied to produce the desired rise time.

Title: Minolta Chroma Meter CR-241 Data Sheet
Desc: The Minolta Chroma Meter CR-241 enables accurate color measurement of extremely small objects.  Similar to a microscope in design, the CR-241 features an SLR (single-lens-reflex) viewing system and a specimen stage which can be moved up and down for focusing or side to side and front to back for accurate positioning of the specimen.  Measurements are performed without touching the specimen, so wet, soft, or fragile specimens pose no problems.  The measuring area can be easily switched between 0.3mm in diameter and 1.8mm in diameter as desired. The CR-241 features a 45/0 illuminating and viewing geometry with 360-degree ring illumination, permitting measurement of a wide variety of specimens, including textured surfaces and the full range of gloss conditions.  The CR-241's data processor provides a wide range of functions, including choice of five different color notations, measurement of absolute color or color difference, automatic statistical calculations, and data printout. Its popularity is due to its high data transfer rates, versatility and an unambiguous structure of codes, formats, protocols and common commands. Two manuals in stock.

Desc: The Model SZ-III is an advanced version of the Model SZ, a revolutionary product which adopted the zoom magnification mechanism for the first time in the world in a stereoscopic microscope, thus rapidly expanding its range of utilization such as in the classification of plants, anatomy of animals, or in assembly and inspection of modern electronic products and precision instruments.

Title: Omega Recorders/Dataloggers Operating Instructions

Title: Omega Microprocessor Controlled Temperature Indicator Operator's Manual
Desc: The Model 650/660 Series are high performance single channel thermocouple meters that can measure temperature accurately between -245 and +1999 in degrees Celsius or Farenheit. Two manuals in stock.

Title: Omega Digital Temperature Indicators Owners Manual
Desc: This manual contains installation, operation, and service in information for Series 400 digital indicators. These solid state instruments digitally display a number of thermocouple, RTD, linear voltage sources, and current transmitter outputs in linearization, dual slope integration, and a large easy-to-read LED display.

Title: Omega Digital Temperature Indicators Owners Manual
Desc: The Model 199 is a versatile, high-performance, industrial grade readout for thermocouple sensors displaying temperature values from -245 to +1999 degrees Celsius or Farenheit. Three manuals in stock.

Title: Omega Microprocessor Controlled Temperature Indicator Operator's Manual
Desc: The Omega CN9000 Series Miniature Microprocessor Controllers are designed for accurate, precise, temperature control. They feature high accuracy and reliability, and the sophisticated PID with approach control for optimal control during start-up and steady-rate operation.

Title: Omega Handheld Thermometers Operator's Manual
Desc: The Omega HH71 and HH73 are single channel, and the HH72 is a dual channel handheld thermometer with microprocessor-based performance at an economical price.

Title: Omega OM302 Series Thermocouple Digital Data Logger Operator's Manual
Desc: The OM302 Series Thermocouple Digital Data Logger is designed to read and record digitally, as temperatures, the microvolt inputs generated by either Types J, K, T or E thermocouples.

Title: Omega Set Point Controllers Instruction Manual
Desc: The Omega Set Point Controllers Instruction Manual.

Title: Omega Digital Thermometers Operator's Manual
Desc: The Model 115 Digital Panel Meter is a versatile, high-performance, industrial grade readout for type J, K, T, or E thermocouple sensors. Thermocouple linearization, cold junction compensation, gain, and offset error correction are automatic features of the internal electronics.

Title: Omega Precision RTD Readout Instruction Manual
Desc: Models 199P1 and P2 are true industrial-grade Platinum Resistance Thermometers (RTD). They are calibrated for the 100-ohm Platinum RTD sensor per DIN Specification 43760 and measure temperatures from -200 degree C to +800 degree C with 1 degree C or 1 degree F resolution and with a conformity of +/- count.

Title: Omega Series 500 Deluxe Laboratory Chart Recorder Operator's Manual
Desc: The Omega Model 555, 585 and 595 Deluxe Laboratory Chart Recorders are dc analog recorders, a product of advanced electronic techniques. The solid state modular circuitry yields high performance and reliability. The Model 555, 585 and 595 are one, two, and three channel recorders, respectively. Three manuals in stock.

Title: Omega Digital Transducer Indicators Operator's Manual
Desc: The Omega Digital Transducer Indicators Operator's Manual.

Title: Omega Omegaline 600/610 Temperature Recorders Operator's Manual
Desc: The Omegaline 600/610 Temperature Recorder series features high-quality, state-of-the-art construction which makes the instruments simple to operate, easy to service, and facilitates expansion to accomodate a wide variety of recording tasks.

Title: Omega Solid State Relay Owner's Manual
Desc: An Omega Solid State Relay is a single-pole, normally open, solid state switching device with no moving parts, capable of tens of millions of cycles of operation. Eight manuals in stock.

Title: Omega Series CN-2000 Programmable Temperature Controller Operator's Manual
Desc: The Omega Series CN-2000 Programmable Temperature Controllers utilize the latest microprocessor technology to improve reliability, accuracy and control. Inputs can be either thermocouple or three wire RTD temperature sensors, or voltage or current signals from virtually any process variable.

Title: Omega Series 920 Controllers Operator's Manual
Desc: The Omega Series 920 Controllers are extremely versatile controllers offering a wide selection of output options and special features.

Title: Mitsubishi Kasei Automatic Titrator Model GT-06 Instruction Manual Version 2.2
Desc: The Mitsubishi Kasei Automatic Titrator Model GT-06 is a microprocessor-controlled compact automatic true equilibrium titrator that performs any type of titration (neutralization, redox, non-aqueous, precipitation, chelatemetric, or photo-meteric).  The titration modes of the GT-06 are: Test titration; Sample titration; Reagent Factor titration; pH/mV titration; Karl Fischer Volumeteric titration.  System includes: Main meter unit with built-in printer/plotter for parameters, results, and graphic printouts; Automatic buret with 20 ml rapid change buret cassette; Magnetic stirrer; Electrode set with glass and reference electrode.

Title: MKS Baratron Type 122A Absolute Pressure Gauge Instruction Manual
Desc: The MKS Baratron Type 122A Absolute Pressure Transducer marks the beginning of a new era in low cost pressure measurement.  Using a latest-generation single-sided dual-electrode Inconel sensor coupled with a new fixed-frequency bridge signal conditioner, the 122A provides operation which is inherently temperature stable at zero pressure, capable of withstanding high overpressure conditions with minimal or no shifts in output over its range, and high resistance to corrosive environments.  The variable-capacitance sensor is the result of over 25 years of research, development and customer experience in total pressure measurement.  The design incorporates a tensioned metal diaphragm (Inconel), one side of which is exposed to the gas whose pressure is to be measured.  The other (reference) side of the diaphragm contains a dual-electrode assembly (previously found in premium transducers only) sealed in a high vacuum reference cavity which is maintained by a chemical getter system.  The signal conditioning electronics board contains a fixed-frequency oscillator, balance-sensing circuit, linearization circuitry and amplifiers which provide a 0-10 Volt DC full scale output.  The signal conditioner is inherently temperature stable at balance (pressure=0 Torr) and is self-compensating with temperature changes at other pressures.  A drawn aluminum can forms the protective cover for the transducer and a PC board mounted removable terminal block allows connections to be easily made for +/- 15 VDC power inputs and the 0-10 VDC pressure signal output.  In addition the aluminum cover works in conjunction with an inner PC shield board with RF bypass capacitors to virtually eliminate RFI and EMI.  Contains 5 identical copies in stock.

Title: MKS Baratron Type 221A Pressure Gauge Instruction Manual
Desc: The MKS Baratron Type 221A Pressure Gauge consists of three elements, indicator, cable and transducer.  The system is shipped fully interconnected and requires only the addition of an external power supply and the appropriate readout device.  The transducer consists of a tightly tensioned diaphragm on one side of which is placed a dual electrode: i.e., a single-sided system, usable when process contamination is possible.  The cavity on the electrode side is evacuated, sealed and gettered to provide a (zero) reference pressure.  The electronics (signal conditioning measuring circuits, etc.) is contained in a flange mounted aluminum box on the opposite end of the transducer cable.  An electrical connector with a mate is provided to make all input power and output signal connections.

Title: MKS Baratron Type 222B Absolute Pressure Gauge Instruction Manual
Desc: The MKS Baratron Type 222B Absolute Pressure Transducer is composed of two basic parts: A corrosion resistant, taut diaphragm Inconel sensor, and a Printed Circuit Board mounted Electronics (signal conditioner).  One side of the sensor is exposed to the gaseous media whose pressure is to be measured, while the reference side of the sensor is vacuum evacuated, sealed via a soft copper pinch-off tube, and gettered to maintain vacuum integrity.  The electronic circuitry is mounted on the reference side of the sensor where it is connected to the sensor feedthrough terminal.  A drawn aluminum can forms the protective cover for the transducer and a PC mounted terminal block allows for ±15 VDC power input and 0-10 VDC pressure signal output.  Contains 3 identical copies in stock.

Title: MKS Baratron Type 222A Pressure Gauge Instruction Manual
Desc: The MKS Baratron Type 222A Pressure Transducer is composed of a sensor and PC mounted electronics.  The sensor is made up of 3 parts: a taut metal diaphragm welded to support rings, a single ceramic-based electrode, and a reference side cover through which feedthrough terminals make connections to the electrode within the reference cavity.  The PC mounted electronic circuitry contains those components necessary to convert a change in capacitance (caused by diaphragm deflection) to a linear ±10 VDC signal.  Both absolute and differential sensors are available.  In the case of the absolute transducer, the reference side is vacuumed, sealed and gettered.  In the case of the differential sensor, the reference cavity is fitted with a pressure port similar to the Px port.  The electronic circuitry is mounted on the reference side of the sensor and two connections are made to the sensor terminals.  A drawn aluminum can forms the protective cover for the transducer and a PC mounted terminal block allows for ±15 VDC power input and ±10 VDC output.

Title: MKS Type 244A/245 Pressure/Flow Control System Instruction Manual
Desc: The MKS Type 244A/245 Pressure/Flow Control System controls a stepper motor powered Granville-Phillips Type 216 Valve (MKS type 245) to maintain a constant pressure (flow) in a vacuum system by varying the input flow.  The Type 244 can provide ±15VDC supply to the pressure (flow) transducer and will accept inputs from a variety of transducers.  The front panel controls allow selection of the input range, control loop tuning, automatic and manual valve control.  An error meter is provided to assist the operator in tuning the control loop.  External signals can be used to command the external setpoint and open or close the valve.  Typically, the control system will consist of three basic parts: the pressure sensor, the controller and control valve, and the system whose pressure is to be controlled.  The pressure sensor will usually be an MKS Baratron Capacitance Manometer whose output is 0-10VDC.  Provision for other inputs (0-1VDC or 0-100mmV) have been built into the controller so that other transducers may be used.  The pressure (vacuum) system will consist of a chamber and a pumping system.  The 244 controller will take the DC pressure (flow) transducer signal, compare it to the setpoint, and position the valve in such a fashion as to drive the actual pressure (flow) to the set pressure value.  The controller contains the three modes of control action found in most controllers today: proportional, derivative, and integral.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: MKS Throttling Valve Types 253A: -20-40-1&2, -20-2CF-1&2, -1-40-1&2, -1-2CF-1&2, -2-50-2, and others
Desc: The MKS Throttling Valve Types 253A-20-40-1, 253A-20-40-2, 253A-20-2CF-1, 253A-20-2CF-2, 253A-1-40-1, 253A-1-40-2, 253A-1-2CF-1, 253A-1-2CF-2, 253A-2-50-2, 253A-2-3CF-2, and 253A-2-4CF-2 are a type of butterfly valve designed to regulate the removal of gas from a vacuum chamber when used with an MKS 252 Controller.  The valve would normally be flange mounted to a Roots blower, diffusion, turbo, cryo, or other high vacuum pump (running at full speed).  The valve's butterfly is positioned to modulate the gas flow (pumping speed as seen by the chamber), thereby controlling pressure within the vacuum chamber.  A special feature of the valve is a nonlinear actuator placed between the butterfly shaft and the motor drive shaft whose function is to generate a linear valve transfer characteristic.  Practically speaking, the 252 Controller will need little, if any, gain and phase lead adjustment as it operates the valve from the full/closed to full/open position.  This is of extreme importance when systems are automatically programmed to change flows and pressures as a process is carried out within the chamber.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Newport Digital Panel Voltometer Owners Manual
Desc: Newport Digital Panel Voltometers are low cost, reliable instruments for digital display of analog bipolar voltages. The display is 1999 counts on any of four ranges from 199.9mV to 199.9V.

Title: Omega CN7000 Series Auto-Tuning Controllers Manual
Desc: The Omega CN7000 Series Auto-Tuning Controllers are microprocessor based and include auto-tuning of the P.I.D. functions. Gain, reset and rate are all tuned automatically without complex adjustments by the user.

Title: Omega Series 4000 Temperature Controllers Operator's Manual
Desc: The Omega Series 4000 Temperature Controllers are quality built digital instruments with 1 degree resolution, available in thermocouple types J and K in either 0 degree F or C ranges.

Title: Omega PID Autotune Temperature Controller Operator's Manual
Desc: The Omega Models CN6071A and CN6072A are microprocessor-based controllers that provide the most advanced features features in heating and cooling control. The can be addressed and monitored from any make computer-based central or remote station to control temperature.

Title: Omega Model 2176A Multipoint Digital Thermometer Instruction Manual
Desc: The Omega Model 2176A Multipoint Digital Thermometer is a portable four-digit, manual-scan, thermocouple thermometer capable of measuring and 1 of 10 possible like-type thermocouple inputs and resolving 0.2 degree C or 0.2 F over a temperature range of -99.9 to +999.8 degree C or F.

Title: Optical Technology Spectroflourometers Manual
Desc: OTD Spectroflourometers are precision instruments of exceptional quality and flexibility. The high performance characteristics of these instruments make them ideal for use in research studies, while their proven reliability and durability is documented by their use in many clinical laboratories for performing repetitve tests with a large number of samples. Two manuals.

Title: MKS High Accuracy 170 Series Sensor Heads
Desc: The MKS High Accuracy 170 Series Sensor Heads consist of a diaphragm type variable capacitance pressure transducer and electronic preamplifier either as an integral temperature controlled package or as a pressure transducer connected to a separate preamplifier with high temperature cables.  Each Sensor Head package is individually calibrated against NBS Traceable Factory Standards, and Certificates of Traceability are available upon request.

Title: Oriel Research Laser Instruction Manual
Desc: The Oriel Model 79200 Research Laser System consists of a cylindrical laser head and a separate power supply. The precise nature of the laser housing makes it ideal for all types of optical bench and alignment uses.

Title: MKS Mass Flow Control Systems for Low Vapor Pressure, High Temperature Vapor Sources Type 550
Desc: The MKS Mass Flow Control Systems for Low Vapor Pressure, High Temperature Vapor Sources Type 550 is used for semiconductor wafer processing when it is required to accurately and repeatably deliver some quantity of process vapor into the wafer fabrication system.

Title: Oriel Variable Frequency Open Chopper Instruction Manual
Desc: Optical systems often require the use of a chopper to modulate the light beam either because a detector, such as the pyroelectric detector, does not respond to continuous radiation or because the signal to noise ratio can be improved by modulation and filtering techniques. The Oriel Model 75100 Variable Frequency Open Chopper with chopping rates of 10 Hz (with 6 aperture wheel) to 4000 Hz (with 40 aperture wheel) allows optimal modulation of the signal for both low and high speed detectors and permits the user to avoid high noise frequency regions. The chopper system offers great versatility with a variety of chopper wheels and convenient chopper mounting capabilities.

Title: Oriel Photodiode Power Supply
Desc: The 70704 photodiode power supply has been specifically designed by Oriel to supply a regulated +/-15 volts for the operation of transimpedance amplifiers, or other solid-state circuitry, and a regulated DC bias voltage, for the optimal use of photodiodes and similar detectors.

Title: Oriel The Readout Instruction Manual
Desc: The 70701 Readout is a digital signal meter for voltage readings, with the ability to scale the output in meaningful units, e.g., absorbance, watts, or milligrams. A 15 volt power supply is present to run custom circuitry or certain solid state detectors. An optional RS-232 interface enables the signal to be read by a computer.

Title: Oriel Ozone Eater Operating Instructions
Desc: All lamps which emit ultraviolet radiation of wave lengths less than about 300 nm will produce ozone from the oxygen in the air. This mainly occurs in the lamp cooling air and is mostly found in the air exiting the lamp house through its fan.  The ozone is a health hazard and, particularly with the higher voltage arc lamps, may be present in higher than acceptable concentrations. The Model 66087 Ozone Removal Module (Ozone Eater) is designed to eliminate this problem. It is a housing containing catalytic filter elements and a fan. The fan collects air through a flanged-end hose and forces it through the filter elements where any ozone present is converted back into oxygen.

Title: Oriel Photodiode Detection System Instruction Manual
Desc: The Oriel Model 7072 Detection System is an instrument designed for a wide variety of applications in the measurement of light radiation. This highly sensitive, extremely stable unit can, with the appropriate external sensor, allow measurements to be made over the range of 200 nm to 1.1 microns thereby encompassing the ultraviolet, visible and near infrared portions of the spectrum. The 7072 has a fixed internal 45 volt power supply suitable for biasing photodiode sensors, such as Oriel 7050 - 7056 series.

Title: Orion Microprocessor Ionalyzer Instruction Manual
Desc: The Orion Microprocessor Ionalyzer Instruction Manual. 3 manuals in stock.

Title: Orion Microprocessor pH/millivolt meter Instruction Manual
Desc: Orion Microprocessor pH/millvolt meter Instruction Manual.  2 in stock.

Title: Orion pH/millivolt meter Instruction Manual
Desc: Obtaining accurate pH values depends on both correct measurement of standard and sample temperatures and on compensation for any variations in these temperatures. This thermal compensation has generally been accomplished either manually or automatically. Both actions will modify amplifier gain or change the potential at the input of an A/D converter, to scale the measurement into temperature-compensated values. The Model 611 pH Meter requires no temperature dial or separate temperature probe. The meter measures temperature change through resistance changes that occur in the pH electrode, and uses this information to automatically compensate for pH/temperature readings.

Title: MKS Type 170M-6C Electronics Unit Operating and Maintenance
Desc: The MKS Type 170M-6C Electronics Unit High Accuracy Capacitance Manometer Pressure Measurement and Control Systems are designed with a modular concept.  For high accuracy pressure monitoring the only required modules are the Sensor Head and Electronic Unit, while for high accuracy closed Loop Pressure Control the only required modules are the Sensor Head, Electronics Unit, Automatic Pressure Controller and Control Valve.  To these basic systems, optional modules can conveniently be added to provide display and Data Acquisition.  The electronics unit is a self-contained signal conditioner with a built-in regulated power supply, 10 kHz oscillator, a high accuracy AC to DC converter to provide a very stable ± 10V DC output which is linear with pressure.  An MKS Sensor Head and the 170M-6C Electronics Unit provide the minimum necessary configuration required for a conversion of pressure into a usable stable DC output.  Three ranges are provided and are manually selectable or remotely selectable via rear connections.

Title: Orion Digital Ionalyzer Service Information
Desc: The Orion Model 601A Digital Ionalyzer is a 3.5 digit pH meter with a conveniently displayed isopotential point. The instrument is capable of displaying relative and absolute millivolt readings, as well as pH readings. By means of the dual slope analog-to-digital conversion technique, an input voltage is converted to a binary-coded decimal format which is decoded and displayed. The 3.5 digit BCD conversion result is available in parallel form at the rear panel connector. A recorder output is also on the rear panel.

Title: Orion Digital Ionalyzer Service Information
Desc: The Orion Model 601A Digital Ionalyzer is a 3.5 digit pH meter with a conveniently displayed isopotential point. The instrument is capable of displaying relative and absolute millivolt readings, as well as pH readings. By means of the dual slope analog-to-digital conversion technique, an input voltage is converted to a binary-coded decimal format which is decoded and displayed. The 3.5 digit BCD conversion result is available in parallel form at the rear panel connector. A recorder output is also on the rear panel.

Title: Orion Digital pH/millivolt Meter Instruction Manual
Desc: The Model 801A is a digital pH/mv meter recommended for all research and precision measurements with pH and chemical sensing electrodes. It covers a range from pH 0.000 to pH 13.999 in 0.001 pH unit increments and with +/-0.001 pH unit repeatability. When measuring specific ion electrode potentials, it covers a range from +1999.9 to -1999.9 millivolts in 0.1 mv increments and with +/- mv repeatability. 2 in stock.

Title: MKS PDR-D-1 Power Supply & Digital Readout 200 / 400 Series
Desc: The MKS PDR-D-1 Power Supply & Digital Readout 200 / 400 Series is a digital readout and power supply that is packaged in a 96MM X 48MM X 150MM plastic DIN enclosure.  This enclosure can be mounted in any panel through a standard DIN 96MM X 48MM cutout or can be used as a stand alone instrument.  The power supply provides ±15VDC @ 35mA and is capable of supplying the input power for one MKS Baratron Type 221, 221A, 222, 222A-B, 223A-B, 422A or any electronic manometer with similar input requirements.  Connection to a pressure transducer is accomplished via a cable which connects to a rear mounted terminal block.  This terminal block is similar to those found on the other PDRs in the 200 series so cables used on those indicators can be used on the PDR-D-1.

Title: Orion Digital Ionalyzer Service Information
Desc: The Orion Model 701A Digital Ionalyzer is a 4.5 digit pH meter capable of displaying relative and absolute millivolt readings, as well as pH readings. By means of the dual slope analog-to-digital conversion technique, an input voltage is converted to a binary-coded decimal format which is decoded and displayed. The 4.5 digit BCD conversion result is available in parallel form at the rear panel connector. An adjustable recorder output is also on the rear panel. 2 in stock.

Title: Orion Digital Ionalyzer Service Information
Desc: The Orion Model 701A Digital Ionalyzer is a 4.5 digit pH meter capable of displaying relative and absolute millivolt readings, as well as pH readings. By means of the dual slope analog-to-digital conversion technique, an input voltage is converted to a binary-coded decimal format which is decoded and displayed. The 4.5 digit BCD conversion result is available in parallel form at the rear panel connector. An adjustable recorder output is also on the rear panel. 2 in stock.

Title: Orion Analog pH Meter Instruction Manual
Desc: The Model 399A is a line- or battery-operated analog pH meter designed to combine reliability and accuracy with ease of operation. Used with the optional ATC probe, readings are automatically compensated for variations in sample temperature. The sturdy, compact meter is supplied with a research-grade pH electrode, electrode holder, shorting, support rod, and buffer powders.

Title: Orion Syringe Pump Instruction Manual
Desc: Model 341A is a U.L./CSA medically approved, single-channel pump which answers most requirements for continuous infusion of fluids. It accepts all types of syringes, in any size from microliter to 50 cc. Rates are precalibrated and highly reproducible and are offered in two ranges - ml/min and ml/hr. Within each range eleven speeds may be chosen, resulting in twenty-two flow rates possible for each syringe size. Rates from 0.00011 ml/hr (with a 10 microliter syringe) to 20ml/min (with a 50 cc syringe) can be obtained.

Title: Orion Ag/AgCl Glass pH Electrodes Instruction Manual
Desc: Orion Ag/AgCl Glass pH Electrodes Instruction Manual

Title: MKS 200/400 Series PDR-C-2 Instruction Manual
Desc: The MKS 200/400 Series PDR-C-2 is a power supply and digital readout which is packaged in the standard MKS ½ rack mount unit.  This unit contains two active channels, each of which contain a circuit for fine zero adjustment, a rear panel switch to program the proper decimal point, and a terminal block for connection to a remote gauge.  The 4½ place digital panel meter is used to read the pressure outputs of each channel.  This meter is connected to the channel output via a relay.  This relay may be switched manually from the front panel, remotely from a rear control connector or automatically by pressure.  The power supply delivers ± 15 volts to the channel output connectors to provide power to the attached gauges.  This supply contains regulators which are self protected and will shut down under excessive power dissipation or load.  This supply is capable of delivering ± 15 @ ½ A.  This unit contains two set points which may be connected to either channel via toggle switches on the rear panel.  Each set point has a separate level adjustment and "status" lamp.  The set point outputs and controls are available via a rear connector J101.

Title: Orion Electronic Analytical Balances Operating Instructions
Desc: Orion Electronic Analytical Balances Operating Instructions

Title: Orion AF7 Couolmetric Karl Fischer Titrator
Desc: The AF7 Coulometric Titrator employs the well-known technique of passing current through an electrolytic cell and using the iodine liberated as a component in the classical Karl Fischer reaction involving sulfur dioxide, alcohol, and a base. The generated iodine is proportional to the quantity of electricity (Faraday's Law) and current (measured in coulumbs) which replaces volumetric reagent measurement as an indicator of water content.

Title: Orion AF7 Couolmetric Karl Fischer Titrator Instruction Manual
Desc: The AF7 Coulometric Titrator employs the well-known technique of passing current through an electrolytic cell and using the iodine liberated as a component in the classical Karl Fischer reaction involving sulfur dioxide, alcohol, and a base. The generated iodine is proportional to the quantity of electricity (Faraday's Law) and current (measured in coulumbs) which replaces volumetric reagent measurement as an indicator of water content. 3 in stock.

Title: Orion Ross pH Electrode Instruction Manual
Desc: This manual contains insutrctions for the ROSS series of pH electrodes. Operation and maintenance instructions for the following electrodes are included: Model No.  80-05 81-01 81-02 81-03 81-04 81-15 81-35 81-55 81-56 81-63 81-66 2 in stock.

Title: Orion Fluoride Electrodes Instruction Manual
Desc: The Model 94-09 fluoride electrode allows fluoride in aqueous solutions to be measured quickly, simply, accurately, and economically. All apparatus and solutions required for measurement, general analytical procedures, electrode characteristics, and electrode theory are discussed in this manual. The Model 96-09 combination fluoride electrode, useful for fluoride measurements of very small samples, is discussed in this manual.

Title: MTI 1000 Fotonic Sensor Instruction Manual
Desc: The MTI 1000 Fotonic Sensor is a fiber optic system that performs non-contact displacement/vibration and surface condition measurements.  By using fiber optics to measure target motion, the MTI 1000 imposes no load on the target under measurement and remains unaffected by magnetic and electrical fields.  Factory calibrated probe/plug-in modules offer a wide range of probe diameter, sensitivity and frequency response, allowing the user to measure displacement motions ranging from .000001 in. to .25 in. at frequencies ranging from dc to 100 kHz.  All measurements are performed without altering the target's natural position or motion.  Since the probe/plug-in modules are interchangeable, the MTI 1000 adapts easily to changing application needs.  Designed for versatility and accuracy, the MTI 1000 Fotonic Sensor meets the needs of research and industrial measurement applications.

Title: Orion Double Junction Reference Electrode Instruction Manual
Desc: The Model 90-02 Double Junction Reference Electrode is a sleeve-type Ag/AgCl reference electrode with an outer chamber which isolates the inner reference element and filling solution from the sample.

Title: ORSAT Burrell Manual for Gas Analysts
Desc: ORSAT Burrell Manual for Gas Analysts

Title: Molecular Devices Vmax Kinetic Microplate Reader User's Manual
Desc: The Molecular Devices Vmax Kinetic Microplate Reader is designed to analyze the contents of standard 96-well microplates.  It can measure either optical density, or the rate of change of OD, thus permitting kinetic analysis.  This instrument reads in the visible range.  In addition to standard microplates, Vmax can accommodate vessels of similar design with multiple sample sites at 9 mm centers such as strip wells, filter bottom microplates, etc.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: ORSAT Burrell Gas Analysis Apparatus Catalog
Desc: ORSAT Burrell Gas Analysis Apparatus Catalog 81

Title: Molecular Devices SOFTmax PRO Protocol Guide Application Protocals for SOFTmax PRO
Desc: The Molecular Devices SOFTmax PRO Protocol Guide Application Protocols for SOFTmax PRO Microplate Analysis Software Version P1.12 is a guide to the files which contain preset parameters for microplate data collection and analysis.  These protocols are designed to provide the user with a starting point from which one can precisely customize for a particular assay.  The protocols save time by providing preset parameters which include: an overview of the experiment, the instrument control parameters, the raw data reduction parameters, the data display option, and the data analysis groups complete with formulas.  Frequently performed assays can be easily repeated by simply opening up the protocol file and initiating the reading of the plate. (two copies)

Title: Oxford Automatic Dispensor Instructions with Variable Speed
Desc: The Oxford Variable Speed Automatic Dispensor is a general purpose table-top instrument used for dispensing and diluting adjustable volumes of various liquids common to clinical and chemical laboratories. It has dual-range scales and adjustments permitting the use of (1) a 20 mL syringe assembly (usable range 2 to 20 mL), or (2) a 5 mL syringe assembly (usable range 0.5 to 5 mL), and can be set to perform a single manual dispensing cycle or to automatically perform continuous dispensing cycles. The dispensing cycle is adjustable over the entire speed range.

Title: Oxford Sampler Single and Multi-range Micropipetting Systems
Desc: The Oxford Sampler Micropipetting Instrument is a general purpose, hand-held instrument used to dispense specific volumes of various liquids used in clinical and chemical laboratories.

Title: Molytek Model 2700 Microprocessor Based Multipoint Recorder Operating Instructions
Desc: The Molytek Model 2700 Microprocessor Based Multipoint Recorder is designed to meet most process and laboratory applications by combining a wide variety of signal conditioning with the versatility and interface ability that only a microprocessor can provide.  The 2700 overcomes many of the drawbacks of traditional servo type multipoint recorders by effectively combining reliable digital components with user-oriented software.  Most standard thermocouples can be directly connected to the Molytek 2700 using the internal linearization and dynamic cold junction compensation and there are no range cards in the 2700.  Left and right margins and high and low alarm set points are fully programmable at the user's discretion on an individual channel basis.  This capability, combined with five linear voltage ranges from 1 millivolt to 10 volts, makes the 2700 compatible with virtually an transducer.

Title: Oxford Dispensor Instructions
Desc: The Oxford Dispensor Instrument is a general purpose, bottle-mounted instrument used to dispense liquids used in clinical and chemical laboratories. The System consists of a dispensing instrument, detailed operating instructions and, in models requiring a small bottle, a stabilizer base. The adjustable range dispensors also have an adjustment tool for setting the desired dispensing range.

Title: Molytek Recorders / Dataloggers and RTU Instruments Maintenance and Troubleshooting Manual
Desc: The Molytek Recorders / Dataloggers and RTU Instruments Maintenance and Troubleshooting Manual is a service guide for multipoint recorder/dataloggers, RTU data acquisition instruments and programmer/recorder/controllers.  This manual is intended to be used with the Recorders/Dataloggers and RTU Instruments Operating Instructions manual as the second volume of a two volume set.  These instruments utilize the same digital components contained on the same printed circuit board assemblies: the digital processing circuit board, the input board, the display board, the relay board (if equipped) and the current source board (if equipped).  These circuit boards are mounted in different orientations in different units, but functionally they are identical in all instruments.   The mechanical print head drive and chart drive assemblies used in both the sliding chassis and portable chart printing instruments are also virtually identical.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Molytek Model 2702 32 Channel Recorder / Datalogger Software Version 3-A1 and Later
Desc: The Molytek Model 2702 32 Channel Recorder/Datalogger Software Version 3-A1 and Later Maintenance and Troubleshooting Guide contains details on maintenance/service, troubleshooting guidelines, and schematics and drawings for this model.

Title: Molytek Recorders / Dataloggers and RTU Instruments Software Versions 5E, 5E-RTU and Later
Desc: The Molytek Recorders / Dataloggers and RTU Instruments Software Versions 5E, 5E-RTU and Later are designed to meet most industrial process and laboratory applications for data collection and recording.  These instruments combine reliable digital components with multiple purpose, user-oriented software.  The result is are instruments with the capacity for a wide variety of signal conditioning tasks coupled with the versatility and interface ability provided by its microprocessor architecture.  Standard thermocouples, RTDs with a current source, and other transducers with a voltage or current output can be connected directly to the instrument.  Either standard, pre-programmed linearization tables or user-entered tables are used for input scaling.  These tables, combined with five linear voltage ranges from 1 millivolt to 10 volts allow the instrument to read and record the output of practically any transducer.  Dynamic cold junction compensation is provided for temperature channels, and the capacity to standardize readings of up to 32 thermocouples of the same type to within ±0.15°C.  There are no range cards.  Alarm set points and channel ranges are fully programmable on a group or per-channel basis.

Title: Molytek Recorders / Dataloggers and RTU Instruments Software Versions 5E, 5E-RTU and Later
Desc: The Molytek Recorders / Dataloggers and RTU Instruments Software Versions 5E, 5E-RTU and Later are designed to meet most industrial process and laboratory applications for data collection and recording.  These instruments combine reliable digital components with multiple purpose, user-oriented software.  The result is are instruments with the capacity for a wide variety of signal conditioning tasks coupled with the versatility and interface ability provided by its microprocessor architecture.  Standard thermocouples, RTDs with a current source, and other transducers with a voltage or current output can be connected directly to the instrument.  Either standard, pre-programmed linearization tables or user-entered tables are used for input scaling.  These tables, combined with five linear voltage ranges from 1 millivolt to 10 volts allow the instrument to read and record the output of practically any transducer.  Dynamic cold junction compensation is provided for temperature channels, and the capacity to standardize readings of up to 32 thermocouples of the same type to within ±0.15°C.  There are no range cards.  Alarm set points and channel ranges are fully programmable on a group or per-channel basis.

Title: Moore Syncro III Control Station "S" Single Loop Circuit Model Series 528SM; 528SX Service Instruct
Desc: The Moore Syncro III Control Station "S" Single Loop Circuit Model Series 528SM; 528SX Service Instructions.  The Model Series 528S Control Station monitors and controls one process variable.  It provides two modes of control: Manual and Automatic.  A selector switch at the front of the station is used to select the control mode.  The control modes are isolated from each other so that only the selected mode provides control.  During Automatic control, the process is controlled at a setpoint that is adjustable from the panel front.  In manual control, the process is controlled by an operator adjustable valve loading pressure.  All switching is procedureless and bumpless.  The station's readouts are setpoint, process, and station output.  The station is modular in design.  All components are chassis mounted and are accessible from the panel front.  The VertiGage, Setpoint Syncro, Valve Loading Syncro and Nullmatic Controller are plug-in assemblies; they can be replaced without removing the station from service.

Title: Moore Two-Mode Nullmatic Controller Model 502 Service Instructions
Desc: The Moore Two-Mode Nullmatic Controller Model 502 is a two-mode controller with a built-in cut-off relay.  The controller operates on the pneumatic "Null" balance principle.  It controls the process variable in response to an air pressure signal from the process transmitter.  The Model 502 controller incorporates adjustable proportional band (gain) and reset action (two-mode).  There are two basic reasons for applying 502 controllers: on applications where the reset bypass feature is desired to facilitate bumpless transfer between control modes; and on processes where it is desirable to locate the controller in the field to minimize the effect of transmission lag.

Title: Moore Syncro Transmitter Part Number 14490 Service Instructions
Desc: Moore Syncro Transmitter Part Number 14490 is a special purpose device that provides a 3-15 psig output.  They are used in Syncro III Stations.  The Syncro Transmitter has two modes of operation.  It operates as a manually adjusted regulator; or as a servo which reproduces an input signal.  The transmitter can be operated in either mode, but only one mode at a time.  The Syncro is a plug-in unit secured to its mounting block by a quick action retaining ring.  The plug-in barbs are oriented so that the Syncro can be installed in only one position.

Title: Moore Vertigage for Syncro III and 3X6 M/P Service Instructions
Desc: The Moore Vertigage for Syncro III and 3X6 M/P is a 3-15 psig receiver gauge that is used in all Syncro III and 3x6 M/P Stations.  The gauge is available in both single and duplex pointers.  It has a 4 inch vertical scale and incorporates a flat-faced pointer movement to minimize parallex error.  The top edge of the pointer is used to read the scale.  Control stations use a duplex gauge with a red and a black pointer.  Loading stations with a simplex gauge have a blue pointer; receiver gauges have a black pointer.  Loading stations with a duplex gauge have a blue and a black pointer; receiver gauges have a black and a green pointer.  The standard scale provided, unless otherwise specified, is 0-100 linear.  The scales are clear plastic with an opaque white backup strip.  They are channel mounted and simply slide in and out of the gauge.

Title: Moore Model Series 63DL Differential Type Flow Controller Service Instructions
Desc: The Moore Model Series 63DL Differential Type Flow Controller is used in conjunction with an external needle valve to provide constant volume flow rates for either liquids or gases over a continuously adjustable flow range.  In gas service, the 63D is used when the downstream pressure is constant to provide a constant mass flow rate (i.e., standard volume units per time unit; e.g., SCFM).  In gas systems where the upstream pressure is constant a 63U is used.  Constant downstream presure is not needed for constant volume flow rates (i.e., volume units per time unit; e.g., CFM).  Since liquids are incompressible, if the volume is held constant, then the mass is constant.

Title: Moore Constant-Differential Flow Controllers GC-63 Series 63 Product Information Sheet
Desc: The Moore Constant-Differential Flow Controllers GC-63 Series 63 are used in conjunction with an external needle valve to provide constant volume flow rates for either liquids or gases over a continuously adjustable flow range.  With liquids--which are, of course, not compressible--the constant volume flow will also be a constant mass flow.  The ability to control at very low rates (in the order of one scc/min) and their wide rangeability (as high as 500:1 for the low-flow units) make these controllers useful in a wide variety of applications.  One widespread use is in gas chromatography, in which the controller regulates the small (20-200 sccm) helium stream that carries the process sample.  Other applications include: liquid purge and blending operations in process plants, a wide variety of precision flow controls in pilot plants, and many uses in laboratories.

Title: Moore Constant Differential Low Flow Controller Instructions for Installation, Operation & Maintenan
Desc: The Moore Constant Differential Low Flow Controller with built-in needle valve maintains, in standard units, a constant upstream mass and volumetric flow of gas or liquid.  The controller should be used in systems where the upstream pressure is constant - downstream pressure can be constant or variable.  Constant flow is achieved by maintaining a constant pressure drop across the internal needle valve.  The differential across the needle valve is determined by the spring loaded diaphragm.  This diaphragm operates the valve plunger to automatically control the flow of fluid through the needle valve at the required rate.  Since upstream pressure is applied to the top of the diaphragm and downstream pressure to the bottom, any tendency for a change in flow--which is directly related to a very small change in differential pressure--is felt by the diaphragm and the valve plunger is repositioned to maintain the constant flow.

Title: Moore Model Series 750P Valve Positioners Installation and Service Instruction
Desc: The Moore Model Series 750P Valve Positioners are double-acting, cam characterized pneumatic valve positioners used to position valves with rectilinear or rotary actuators.  It can operate within any of three input ranges: 3 to 9 psig, 3 to 15 psig, and 9 to 15 psig.  Several types of cms are available for use with the positioner including standard rectilinear or rotary, modified equal percentage, and quick-opening.  Each cam can accommodate all three input ranges.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: MSA Combustible Gas Detection Systems, Series 510 Set Point AC/DC Instruction Manual
Desc: The MSA Combustible Gas Detection Systems, Series 510, models 510, 511 and 512 dual set point AC/DC are instrument packages designed to continuously analyze an atmosphere to detect the presence of flammable gases and vapors up to their Lower Explosive Limit (LEL) in air, and to give first a warning then an alarm indication when predetermined concentration levels are reached.  The systems are compact in design utilizing all solid state electronics for maximum reliability; a meter readout gives continuous indication of any concentration level below the LEL of combustible gas or vapor in the area being monitored; the systems are capable of operation from either AC or DC power sources.  The systems can also be simultaneously wired to both AC and DC power supplies which results in normal operation from the AC source with DC available as "standby" power ready to take over in the event of an AC power failure without any noticeable interruption of instrument function.  In addition to their advanced features and accurate, dependable performance, the instruments are easy to install, operate and maintain.  Normal care in use will enable them to provide years of service.

Title: MTEC Model 100 Photoacoustic Cell FTIR Sampling Accessory Instrument Manual
Desc: The MTEC Model 100 Photoacoustic Cell FTIR Sampling Accessory is designed to enable measurement of high signal-to-noise absorption spectra of solids primarily as an accessory with FTIR spectrometers.  Important design features include fast sample cycling, helium gas purging to enhance signal-to-noise without disturbing samples or causing nonrepeatable variations in cell sensitivity, and kinematic cell mounting for easy installation and removal from FTIR spectrometers.

Title: Panametrics Model 2000 Hygrometer Operating and Service Manual
Desc: The Panametrics Model 2000 Hygrometer is a versatile, compact instrument used to measure water vapor pressure in both gases and liquids over a very wide dynamic range.  Dew points from +20°C to -110°C can be measured quickly, accurately and repeatably.  This range represents a change in water concentration from 20,000 ppm to about .001 ppm in gases or from approximately 1% by weight to less than .001 ppm in liquids.  A single readout can monitor up to 6 sensor probes located remotely at distances of up to several thousand feet.  The sensor is operable under static or flow conditions, pressures from 10^-3 mm of Hg to 5000 psig, and temperature to +70°C.  The use of solid state components throughout gives the Model 2000 both ruggedness and reliability.  The unit features intrinsic safety, remote control output/input and simplified multi-point recorder operation.  In addition to these standard features a wide range of options and accessories are available.

Title: Panasonic KX-P1180i Impact Dot Matrix Printer Operating Instructions
Desc: The Panasonic KX-P1180i Impact Dot Matrix Printer is a durable, highly reliable dot matrix printer.  In addition, it has a small footprint, making it ideal for a compact workstation.  This printer uses a nine pin print head to form a 9x9 dot matrix character in Draft mode.  In Near Letter Quality mode, the matrix for Courier, Prestige and Bold PS is 18x18; Sans Serif 18x9.  Available are the complete Epson and IBM character sets as well as 13 international character sets.  In addition to Pica (10 characters per inch) and Elite (12 characters per inch) printing, this printer can print in Micron mode of 15 characters per inch, Compressed mode of 17 characters per inch and Elite Compressed mode of 20 characters per inch.  Elite Compressed mode yields a total of 160 characters per line.  In addition, this printer has proportional spacing thus, six basic printing pitches are available.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Panasonic KX-P1180i Impact Dot Matrix Printer Operating and Setup Reference Page
Desc: The Panasonic KX-P1180i Impact Dot Matrix Printer Operating and Setup Reference Page contains a quick view of the common operations and functions of this apparatus.  It also contains a quick guide to the set up of this machine, the DIP switches, and the corresponding DIP switch functions.  Includes illustrations for demonstrative purposes.  Printed in Japan.

Title: Panasonic PK-959 8:1 Auto Focus Power Zoom Lens Electronic Viewfinder Color Video Camera
Desc: The Panasonic PK-959 8:1 Auto Focus Power Zoom Lens Electronic Viewfinder Color Video Camera Operating Instructions contain the necessary procedures to operate the Panasonic video camera including camera features and controls, mounting procedures, interfacing with VCRs and televisions, and camera special features.  Contains illustrations.

Title: Panasonic Color Video Data Monitor Model CT-1400MG Operating Instructions
Desc: The Panasonic Color Video Data Monitor Model CT-1400MG Operating Instructions contain the installation and normal operating procedures of this cathode ray tube-styled optical projecting device.  Using specialized phosphor, this apparatus delivers RGB-standard color images with a resolution of 370 TV Lines (Comb Filter ON) at Video Signal, 580 dots at RGB Signal.

Title: Panasonic AC Adaptor WV-PS03 Operating Instructions
Desc: The Panasonic AC Adaptor WV-PS03 is used to supply the DC power to the color camera WV-3260/8AF or WV-D5000, or to the pan/tilt head WV-PH10 as a power source.  It is also used with the gen-lock adaptor WV-AD36 in the EFP application for supplying the DC power and distributing the gen-lock signal sent from the special effects generator.

Title: Anton Paar DMA 45 Calculating Digital Density Meter for Liquids and Gases Instruction Manual
Desc: The Anton Paar Calculating Digital Density Meter for Liquids and Gases DMA 45 simplifies the accurate determination of the density of liquids and gases by reducing the procedure to the electronic measurement of a time period from which the density is automatically calculated by a built-in arithmetic processor.

Title: Anton Paar External Measuring Cells Model DMA Instruction Manual
Desc: The Anton Paar External Measuring Cells Model DMA is a digital precision density measurement system for liquids and gases.  External measuring cells have been developed for solving special measuring problems (e.g., higher measuring temperatures, higher pressures) and to achieve the highest possible accuracy and precision of the measurement  results.  This applies in particular to the combination with a DMA 60, in which case, the measuring cell and the electronics are thermally separated.  The DMA External or Remote Measuring Cells simplify the accurate determination of the density of liquids and gases by reducing the procedure to the electronic measurement of a time period.

Title: Parr Analytical Methods for Oxygen Bombs
Desc: The Parr Analytical Methods for Oxygen Bombs article discusses basic ASTM referee methods for sulfur and chlorine.

Title: Parr 1108 Oxyen Combustion Bomb Operating Instructions
Desc: The Parr 1108 Oxygen Combustion Bomb is used to determine calorific values of solid or liquid combustible materials in a Parr calorimeter, or when using an 1108 bomb in a 1901 Oxygen Bomb Apparatus to prepare solid or liquid samples for chemical analysis.  Contains 3 identical copies in stock.

Title: Parr Introduction to Bomb Calorimetry
Desc: The Parr Introduction to Bomb Calorimetry is intended to give Parr calorimeter users an overview of the basic principals involved in measuring the heat of combustion (calorific value) of solid and liquid fuels, foodstuffs and other combustible materials in a bomb calorimeter.

Title: Parr 1341 Oxygen Bomb Calorimeter Operating Instructions
Desc: The Parr 1341 Oxygen Bomb Calorimeter Operating Instructions cover the steps to be taken in setting up and operating this apparatus.

Title: Parr Plain Oxygen Bomb Calorimeter Bulletin 1300
Desc: The Parr Plain Oxygen Bomb Calorimeter Bulletin 1300 briefly summarizes the merits of using a Parr Oxygen Bomb.  One of the most important tests in the evaluation of materials which are burned as fuels is the determination of their heats of combustion, or calorific value.  These measurements can be made quickly and accurately in Parr oxygen bomb calorimeters, utilizing either the latest in automatic calorimetric equipment or in simple calorimeters in which all elements have been reduced to their fundamental forms.  Uses for these calorimeters extend into any chemical, physical or physiological process in which heat generation or burning is an important factor.  In addition to their wide use for testing fuels and foodstuffs, Parr calorimeters also have important applications in college and university laboratories where instruction in the art of calorimetry is an essential part of the basic training for all fields of science and engineering.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Parr 1341 Plain Jacket Oxygen Bomb Calorimeter Instructions
Desc: The Parr 1341 Plain Jacket Oxygen Bomb Calorimeter Instructions describes the steps to be taken when setting up and operating this apparatus.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Parr Safety Rupture Discs Safety Bulletin S2
Desc: The Parr Safety Rupture Discs are installed in Parr laboratory reactors and pressure vessels to protect the operator and the equipment from destructively high pressures.  These discs will function as an effective safety device when properly installed and used as directed.  Safety discs are, however, of such simple construction that a user will often take them for granted and will overlook the potential hazards which can arise from improper disc selection, improper installation, improper maintenance and usage, and from failure to provide adequate venting.

Title: Parr Safety in the Operation of Laboratory Reactors and Pressure Vessels
Desc: The Parr Safety in the Operation of Laboratory Reactors and Pressure Vessels article discusses the dangerous and deadly consequences that could occur without the proper safety precautions necessary to ensure the user's protection against such occurrences.  Included are articles on the user's responsibility, chemistry considerations, barricades and ventilation, maintenance and training, pressure and temperature limits, and loading limits.  Also included is a reprinted article by H.K. Livingston, "I Didn't Know It Was Loaded!!".  Includes references.

Title: Parr 1421 Semimicro Bomb Calorimeter Instructions
Desc: The Parr 1421 Semimicro Bomb Calorimeter is an easily operated instrument which can be used to measure the heat evolved in a combustion reaction of a solid or liquid sample with high pressure oxygen.  Measurements are made at room temperature for samples producing energy changes ranging from approximately 50 calories to 1.2 kcl.  At the start of the test in this calorimeter the bomb is immersed in a glass Dewar while the combustion sample, either solid or liquid, is held within the bomb.  After the calorimeter has come to thermal equilibrium, the operator starts the reaction by electrically igniting a fuse which in turn kindles the sample.  The reaction then proceeds to completion and the heat produced by the combustion raises the temperature of the calorimeter.  Throughout the test, temperatures in the calorimeter are sensed by a thermistor and read from an electronic bridge which is built into the calorimeter case.  Deviations from the bridge reading are traced by a potentiometric strip chart recorder to produce a thermogram showing the temperature change produced by the reaction.  Data from the thermogram can then be used to compute the heat of combustion.

Title: Parr 3911 & 3921 Hydrogenation Apparatus Operating Instructions
Desc: The Parr 3911 & 3921 Hydrogenation Apparatus Operating Instructions describe the steps to be taken when setting up and operating any Par 3911 or 3921.  All operating and safety instructions given apply equally to both units since both operate in the same manner and use the same hydrogen supply system.  Samples to be treated in a Parr hydrogenator are placed in a reaction bottle with a catalyst and clamped in a shaking mechanism.  A gas connection is made to the bottle from a multiple valve and all air is removed either by evacuation or by flushing with hydrogen.  Hydrogen is then introduced from a 4-liter reservoir while the bottle is shaken vigorously to initiate the reaction.  Heating or cooling can be applied, if necessary.
