After the reaction reaches the desired point the shaker is stopped, the bottle vented and the product and catalyst are recovered.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Parr 1261 Isoperibol Calorimeter Operating Instructions
Desc: The Parr 1261 Isoperibol Calorimeter has been designed to provide rapid and reliable heat of combustion values for solid and liquid fuels.  This instrument combines third generation microprocessor hardware and software with the calorimeter designs, technical knowledge and customer support developed by Parr in the 85 years that calorimetry has been the principal thrust of the company.  The important design and operating concepts incorporated into the 1261 Calorimeter include: isoperibol operation, dynamic operation, microprocessor based process control, full microprocessor based data acquisition and handling, full microprocessor based communications capabilities, and flexible programming.

Title: Parr Mercurial Calorimetric Thermometers Operating Instructions
Desc: The Parr Mercurial Calorimetric Thermometers Operating Instructions detail how to care for this apparatus.  Included are diagrams and procedures in rejoining mercury.

Title: Parr 1661 Recording Calorimetric Thermometer Operating Instructions
Desc: The Parr 1661 Recording Calorimetric Thermometer measuring system has been developed specifically to provide a simplified procedure for measuring and computing the net temperature rise in a Parr 1341 plain oxygen bomb calorimeter with better resolution than can be obtained with the usual 19-35°C mercurial thermometer and with considerable saving of the operator's time.  It consists of a special thermistor probe and the bridge which can be used with a strip chart recorder to produce a permanent graphic record of the temperature rise during a calorimetric test.  The net corrected temperature rise can then be determined directly from the recorded trace by a graphic method without having to compute and apply specific heat leak corrections.

Title: Parr Thermometer Test Certificate for Model 1603 S/N 8L2130
Desc: The Parr Thermometer Test Certificate for Model 1603 S/N 8L2130 certifies that this thermometer has been tested for use in differential temperature measurements, as in calorimetry.  The test was made by comparison with a quartz thermometer traceable to the National Bureau of Standards.  The thermometer was held upright in a large, covered, circulating water bath with the bulb and scale completely immersed.  All readings were taken with the aid of a magnifier and were estimated to one-tenth of the smallest scale division.  In normal use a large portion of the stem will not be immersed and its temperature may differ slightly from the bulb temperature.  This will introduce no significant error if the difference between stem and bulb temperatures is less than 1/6th of the range of the thermometer.  If the temperature difference is larger, an emergent stem correction should be applied.

Title: Parr A472E Thermocouples for Parr Reactors Bulletin
Desc: The Parr A472E Thermocouples for Parr Reactors are Type J (I/C) thermocouples when measuring temperatures in all Parr reactors and autoclaves.  These thermocouples are sealed in 1/8" dia. stainless steel probes of different lengths to match different bomb sizes.  These probes are either inserted into a thermowell attached to the bomb head or, in Parr "Mini" reactors, the probe extends directly into the bomb cavity.  In all cases the probe remains in the bomb head when opening and servicing the reactor, but a separable plug on the end of the stem makes it easy to disconnect the A470E2 extension wire which runs to the controller.

Title: Parr Limited Warranty Notice
Desc: The Parr Limited Warranty Notice details the legal rights, obligations, and limitations that Parr Instrument Company has with the original purchaser-user in regards to Parr combustion bombs, calorimeters, reactors, pressure vessels and associated products.

Title: ASTM Standards for Bomb Calorimetry and Combustion Methods Compilation, June 1979
Desc: The ASTM Standards for Bomb Calorimetry and Combustion Methods Compilation was compiled by the American Society for Testing and Materials for Parr Instrument Company.  The compilation lists 8 standards that have been adopted by the ASTM and published June 1979.

Title: Parr Teflon Lined Acid Digestion Bombs Bulletin 4745
Model: Parr Teflon Lined Acid Digestion Bombs
Desc: The Parr Teflon Lined Acid Digestion Bombs are the rapid and safe way to dissolve inorganic samples in HF, HCI and other strong mineral acids, or to digest organic samples in strong alkalis or oxidizing acids at temperatures well above normal boiling points with complete sample recovery and without losing any trace elements.  Parr acid digestion bombs have added a new alternative to the task of preparing analytical samples for analysis.  By combining the unique chemical inertness of Teflon with the advantages of a sealed, stainless steel pressure vessel, these convenient bombs offer a rapid procedure for sample dissolution or digestion which has several important advantages over more traditional methods of sample preparation.

Title: Anton Paar DMA Continuous Flow and Pressure Adapters for Digital Density Meters Instructions for Use
Desc: The Anton Paar DMA Continuous Flow and Pressure Adapters for Digital Density Meters are suitable for all models of DMA digital density meters and for all DMA external measuring cells.  By means of these adapters, different type tubings can be connected to the Digital Density Meters.  Special care has to be taken when introducing the sample into the oscillator tube of the DMA.  Due to the application of Adapters for Pressure a direct contact between hypodermic syringe (which is used for single measurements) and opening of oscillator cell is avoided, thus eliminating the danger of cell fracture.

Title: Anton Paar DMA 45 Calculating Digital Density Meter for Liquids and Gases Instruction Manual
Desc: The Anton Paar Calculating Digital Density Meter for Liquids and Gases DMA 45 simplifies the accurate determination of the density of liquids and gases by reducing the procedure to the electronic measurement of a time period from which the density is automatically calculated by a built-in arithmetic processor.

Title: Parr 1451 Solution Calorimeter Instructions
Desc: The Parr 1451 Solution Calorimeter is an easily operated instrument which can be used to measure the heat evolved or absorbed by chemical reactions in a liquid media.  Measurements are made at room temperature and atmospheric pressure for systems producing energy changes ranging from 2 to 1000 calories.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Parr Magnetic Drives in Parr "Mini" Reactors Numbers 4561 thru 4565 Installation & Servicing Manual
Desc: The Parr Magnetic Drives in Parr "Mini" Reactors Model Numbers 4561 - 4565 require little attention and maintenance.  When properly installed, the outer rotor should spin freely and the inner (driven) unit should follow without slippage, providing a high torque stirring action without requiring a packing gland on the shaft.  This manual gives instructions for operating and servicing magnetic drives in any Parr "Mini" Reactor, including instructions for installing a magnetic drive in any existing reactor equipped with a gland-type shaft seal.

Title: Parr Safety in the Operation of Laboratory Reactors and Pressure Vessels
Desc: The Parr Safety in the Operation of Laboratory Reactors and Pressure Vessels article discusses the dangerous and deadly consequences that could occur without the proper safety precautions necessary to ensure the user's protection against such occurrences.  Included are articles on the user's responsibility, chemistry considerations, barricades and ventilation, maintenance and training, pressure and temperature limits, and loading limits.  Also included is a reprinted article by H.K. Livingston, "I Didn't Know It Was Loaded!!".  Includes references.

Title: Tips for Safe Parr Hydrogenation Use Technical Reports Volume 4, Number 26
Desc: Tips for Safe Parr Hydrogenation Use Technical Reports Volume 4, Number 26.  Catalytic hydrogenation is a standard synthetic transformation and the use of a Parr hydrogenation apparatus to conduct this transformation is quite common.  Several tips for safely performing a hydrogenation reaction and good practices for using a Parr apparatus are described in this report.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Partlow Non-Indicating Temperature Controls Models NSS, NSSX Instruction Sheet
Desc: The Partlow Non-Indicating Temperature Controls Models NSS & NSSX provides the versatility of two independent temperature controls in a single instrument.  It is used when two fixed temperatures are specified as control points and a change or adjustment of these points is seldom required.

Title: Partlow Indicating Controllers Series L, M, and MF Scale Change-Out Instructions
Desc: The Partlow Indicating Controllers Series L, M, and MF Scale Change-Out Instructions describes the procedures necessary to replace a temperature controller.  Contains illustrations for identification of components.te

Title: Patterson Kelley Liquid-Solids Twin Shell Blender Eight & Sixteen Quart Models Operating Instruction
Desc: The Patterson-Kelley Liquid-Solids Twin Shell Blender Eight & Sixteen Quart Models Operating Instructions details the procedures for preparation, operation, and maintenance of these apparatus.  Contains mechanical schematics with identifications of components.

Title: Fisher Scientific Pensky-Martens Closed Flash Point Tester Electrically Heated Model Instructions
Desc: The Fisher Scientific Pensky-Martens Closed Flash Point Tester Electrically Heated Model Catalog Number 13-497-5 is a closed cup tester used to determine the flash point of fuel oils, lube oils, suspensions of solids, liquids that tend to form a surface film under test conditions, and other liquids.  With minor exceptions, the apparatus is described in ASTM designation D93 -- which is included with these instructions.  The design adheres to the specifications of the American Society for Testing and Materials, the American Standards Association, and the Federation of Societies for Paint Technology.  In addition, an accessory stirring motor is available if one is needed to meet the procedural requirements.

Title: Perkin Elmer Four Position, Motor Driven, Water Thermostatted, Stirred Cell Holder
Desc: The Perkin Elmer Four Position, Motor Driven, Water Thermostatted, Stirred Cell Holder accepts 12.5 mm (10mm path length) square cells.  The cell holder is controlled from the PC using the Cuvette Options dialogue.  From this dialogue the cell position and stirrer can be selected.  The sample can be maintained at a temperature between ambient and 600 °C by circulating thermostatically controlled water through an internal passage in the cell holder.  Cooled water can also be circulated.  The cells are located in a motor driven turret and are labeled "1" to "4".  A reaction taking place in the cell can be stirred using a magnetic stirrer.

Title: Pesco Hydraulic Flow Equalizer Model 397 Series Guide
Desc: The Pesco Hydraulic Flow Equalizer Model 397 Series is a valve consisting of an aluminum alloy housing containing two sets of steel gears through which the hydraulic fluid must pass.  These gears are of the same size and displacement and therefore, have the same output.  Two perfectly balanced regulating valves, one for each set of gears, are also contained within the housing, to provide an equal flow of hydraulic fluid from the outlet ports of the valve to the control cylinders.  A relief valve is provided next to the intake port to relieve excess pressure caused by fluid expansion due to heating.  The Pesco flow equalizer is designed to divide the fluid flow equally from a common pressure line into two discharge lines for the synchronized actuation of any pair of hydraulically operated units such as wing flaps, landing gear, or wing tip floats.  The unit operates accurately under pressure differentials up to 1400 P.S.I. which may exist due to unbalanced load conditions.

Title: Pharmacia Prefilter for Prepacked Columns Code Number 19-5084-01
Desc: Pharmacia Prefilter for Prepacked Columns is used to filter solvents from the pump to the column.  It should be located between the pump and the injector.

Title: Pharmacia Filter Assembly HR 5 Code Number 18-0427-01 (5 mm) Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Filter Assembly HR 5 Code Number 18-0427-01 (5 mm) Instructions detail the procedures for replacing a filter on the HR 5/5 and HR 5/20 which occasionally need filter changes.  Filter assemblies are positioned inside the top and bottom plungers.  Includes schematics with component identification.

Title: Pharmacia Superloop 10ml, 50ml Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Superloop 10ml, 50ml is a unique component for a chromotagraphic set up.  This product from Pharmacia allows the introduction of large volumes of secondary solutions into a pressurized fluid system.  Applications include chromatofocusing, applications of large volume samples, developing buffers and specific eluents in affinity chromatography.  Used together with the Pharmacia Valve V-7 (Code No. 19-7500-01) it replaces an ordinary sample loop.

Title: Pharmacia Single Path Monitor UV-1 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pharmacia Single Path Monitor UV-1 is a dual beam flow-through UV-absorptiometer for monitoring the UV-absorption of a flowing liquid at 254 nm or 280 nm.  The measuring cell has an optical path-length of either 3 mm or 10 mm.  Results are expressed either as absorption or as transmission.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Pharmacia Flow Cell HR 10 Specifications & Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Flow Cell HR 10 is specially designed for high resolution liquid chromatography.  All dead volumes in the cell are minimized.  With a built-in low volume heat exchanger in combination with two optical lenses, disturbances from refractive index changes are efficiently reduced.  It can be used with all aqueous solutions and organic solvents commonly used in liquid chromatography.  The Flow Cell HR 10 fits Pharmacia monitors UV-1 and UV-1/214 for monitoring at 405, 280, 254, and 214 nm.

Title: Pharmacia Flow Cell HR 10 Specifications & Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Flow Cell HR 10 is specially designed for high resolution liquid chromatography.  All dead volumes in the cell are minimized.  With a built-in low volume heat exchanger in combination with two optical lenses, disturbances from refractive index changes are efficiently reduced.  It can be used with all aqueous solutions and organic solvents commonly used in liquid chromatography.  The Flow Cell HR 10 fits Pharmacia monitors UV-1 and UV-1/214 for monitoring at 405, 280, 254, and 214 nm.

Title: Pharmacia 3-Way Valve LV-3 and 4-Way Valve LV-4
Desc: The Pharmacia 3-Way Valve LV-3 and 4-Way Valve LV-4 are valves designed for sample application, flow reversal, recycling chromatography, fraction collection, column packing etc. in gel filtration and other liquid chromatographic techniques.  For use in aqueous solutions and nearly all organic solvents commonly used in chromatography with the following few exceptions: chlorinated hydrocarbons, acetone and other ketones, and aliphatic esters.

Title: Pharmacia Valve V-8 Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Valve V-8 is designed to be used as a selection valve for columns, solvents and samples or as a mini-fraction collector.  The valve lever rotates through a 360° angle and has eight different positions.  Each position connects a central port with one of the eight peripheral ports.

Title: Pharmacia Motor Valve MV-7 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pharmacia Motor Valve MV-7 is a 3 position, 7-port motorized valve designed to be used as an automatic sample injection valve or system valve.  The valve has 3 positions: LOAD, INJ, WASH.  A channel plate inside the valve body is rotated to line up the various ports on the valve.  When used in an automated FPLC System, the Valve MV-7 is controlled from the Liquid Chromatography Controller LCC-500 which can accommodate up to six motorized valve designed as an automated selection valve for columns, solvents and samples or as a minifraction collector.  Together with one Motor Valve MV-8, the MV-7 can inject up to eight samples automatically.

Title: Pharmacia FPLC-Cable kit -- GP-250 & FPLC-Cable kit -- LCC-500
Desc: The Pharmacia FPLC-Cable kit -- GP-250 and FPLC-Cable kit -- LCC-500 contain a set of cables for electrical connections in the FPLC System.  The GP-250 contains cables for a manual FPLC System based on the Gradient Programmer GP-250 and the LCC-500 contains cables for an automated FPLC System based on the Liquid Chromatography Controller LCC-500.

Title: Pharmacia Chromatography Rack-II Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pharmacia Chromatography Rack-II is a laboratory stand on which Pharmacia chromatography equipment can be mounted.  The rack is designed so that all items of equipment are sited in their logical operation positions.  Electrical and tubing connections are greatly simplified.  This functional mounting of system components can increase operational productivity and precision since it groups together equipment logically, reduces the amount of tubing and wiring, makes more bench space available for other uses and helps maintain a clean working environment.  The Pharmacia Chromatography Rack-II can be used in a variety of ways to suit different applications.  It has high capacity thus allowing convenient arrangement of complex chromatography set-ups e.g. for automated purification with multicolumn techniques.  Assembly is straight-forward, requiring only the supplied Allen key and a Phillips screwdriver.  All electrical components are already assembled and connected.

Title: Pharmacia Fraction Collector FRAC-100
Desc: The Pharmacia Fraction Collector FRAC-100 is a versatile instrument for automatic fraction collection and evaluation of chromatograms.  In the standard form it will collect up to 95 fractions in tubes with diameters of 10-18 mm.  It will also collect up to 45 fractions in 28 mm diameter vials with the help of a simple accessory.  When connected to a suitable monitor, it will measure peak heights, areas and elution volumes or times for up to 11 peaks as well as indicating into which tubes the peaks have been collected.  Contains 3 identical copies in stock.

Title: Pharmacia Single-Channel Recorder and Two-Channel Recorder Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pharmacia Single-Channel Recorder and Two-Channel Recorder are high quality, potentiometric strip chart recorders with a compact flatbed design.  These reliable and versatile instruments can accurately record any incoming DC signal from 1 mV to 5 volts.  The Model 482 Two-Channel Recorder can simultaneously record two separate incoming signals.  The Pharmacia Recorders allow convenient "push-button" selection of 14 chart speeds (0.1 mm/min to 10 mm/sec) and 12 sensitivity ranges (1 mV to 5 volts).  In addition, the chart speed can be controlled by an external frequency source, and intermediate values of the sensitivity ranges can be set with the variable attenuator control.  By pushing the range "zero" button, the recorder baseline can be checked without altering any settings.  Chart paper can be conserved by using the chart drive "off" button as a pause control which, when pushed in, stops the chart drive while leaving all other operations and settings unaltered.

Title: Pharmacia High Precision Pump P-500 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pharmacia High Precision Pump P-500 is a high precision laboratory pump for use in liquid chromatography and other applications where constant flow at pressures up to 4 MPa (40 bar) is required.  The P-500 is very accurate and reproducible, especially at low flow rates over the whole pressure range.  The excellent chemical resistance of the pump makes it possible to work with corrosive liquids, e.g. organic solvents, as well as aqueous solutions.

Title: Pharmacia Flanging / Start Up Kit Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Flanging / Start Up Kit is used to flange tubing ends (0.5-0.8 mm i.d.) so that the tubing is retained inside the tubing connector.  With the flanging kit it is possible to prepare tubing of any length to fit a specific system.  Flanges are made by pushing the capillary tubing onto the heated flanging tip.  As the tubing heats up it flares out; the flanging tip is removed and the tubing is pressed against a flat, cool surface in order to fix the flange.

Title: Pharmacia LCC-500 Chromatography Controller Programming Guide
Desc: The Pharmacia LCC-500 Chromatography Controller is designed to form gradients by controlling the relative flow rates of two P-500 pumps.  Pump A pumps start buffer (A) while pump B pumps.  A gradient is formed by the binary mixing of these two buffers in the mixing chamber.  The LCC-500 can be programmed to control the formation of many different types of gradients.  However, simple, linear gradients are often adequate to achieve excellent results with FPLC.

Title: Pharmacia Adaptor A 16 Specifications & Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Adaptor A 16 consists of a plunger and bed support mounted on inner and outer adjusting tubes.  The top piece of the adaptor fits the column end piece and sealing against the column wall is provided by an O-ring on the plunger backed by an expander ring.  Contains 4 identical copies in stock.

Title: Pharmacia Gel Filtration Calibration Kit Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pharmacia Gel Filtration Calibration Kit for Protein Molecular Weight Determinations by Gel Filtration is a chromatography technique based on the well-established ability of gel filtration media, such as Sephadex, Sepharose, and Sephacryl, to separate molecules according to size.  Molecular weight determinations by gel filtration are carried out by comparing some elution volume parameter such as Kav of the substance of interest, with the values obtained for several known calibration standards.  In practice it is found that for a homologous series of compounds a sigmoidal relationship exists between their various elution volume parameters and the logarithm of their molecular weights.  A calibration curve is prepared by measuring the elution volumes of several standard substances, calculating their corresponding Kav values (or similar parameter), and plotting their Kav values versus the logarithm of their molecular weight.  The molecular weight of an unknown substance can then be determined from the calibration curve once its Kav value is calculated from its measured elution volume.  For accurate determination of molecular weight, the calibration standards must have the same relationship between molecular weight and molecular size as the substance of interest.  Pharmacia Calibration Kits provide highly purified, well-characterized, globular protein standards for protein molecular weight determination.

Title: Pharmacia Adaptor A 26 Specifications & Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Adaptor A 26 consists of a plunger and bed support mounted on inner and outer adjusting tubes.  The top piece of the adaptor fits the column end piece and sealing against the column wall is provided by an O-ring on the plunger backed by an expander ring.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Pharmacia Column K 16 Specifications & Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Column K 16 consists of a chromatographic tube with two end pieces and a thermostat jacket for controlled temperature work.  The top piece has a combined inlet nipple and air vent; the bottom piece is fitted with a flow control valve.  Contains 4 identical copies in stock.

Title: Pharmacia Column K 26 Specifications & Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Column K 26 consists of a chromatographic tube with two end pieces and a thermostat jacket for controlled temperature work.  The top piece has a combined inlet nipple and air vent; the bottom piece is fitted with a flow control valve.  Contains 3 identical copies in stock.  Contains 5 identical copies in stock.

Title: Pharmacia Electrophoresis Constant Power Supply ECPS 3000/150 and Volthour Integrator VH-1
Desc: The Pharmacia Electrophoresis Constant Power Supply ECPS 3000/150 and Volthour Integrator VH-1 Instruction Manual.  The ECPS 3000/150 is a constant power supply of advanced design, which can produce a maximum of 3000 volts.  It can deliver 150 mA up to a power limitation of 150 watts.  It is extremely lightweight, and can be easily carried.  The digital display uses bright LED diodes which makes meter reading very easy.  The unit is mounted in a case which is both attractive and functional because the extruded aluminum sides are an aid to cooling.  The Pharmacia Volthour Integrator VH-1 monitors elapsed volthours.  It can do this in one of two modes, either by counting down from a preset value to zero when an alarm will sound (ideal for routine experiments), or by counting up from zero to whatever figure that is obtained when the experiment is terminated (the mode of choice when investigating an unknown protein).  The VH-1 will operate in either of two ranges, 0 to 9,999 or 0 to 99,999 volthours, depending upon the scale selected.  If counting downwards the Volthour Integrator will automatically continue to 9,999 (or 99,999 depending upon the scale selected) once it has passed through zero.  If counting upwards, the Volthour Integrator will continue from zero once 9,999 (or 99,999) has been passed.

Title: Pharmacia Power Supply DPS Specifications & Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Destainer Power Supply DPS is for controlled destaining of gel slabs and gel rods.  The power supply has three individual constant voltage settings, a built-in maximum current value, an automatic timer for operation control, and full personnel and instrument protection.  Additional terminals permit its use in other systems.  The Pharmacia Destainer Power Supply DPS is supplied for use with the Gel Destainer GD-4 and for operation from 115 V ± 10%, 60 Hz or 220 V ± 10%, 50Hz.

Title: Pharmacia Electrophoresis Power Supply EPS 500/400
Desc: The Pharmacia Electrophoresis Power Supply EPS 500/400 is an accurately controlled power source of modern design that has been designed for safe and easy operation.  The EPS 500/400 is designed to be used with the Pharmacia electrophoresis apparatuses (eg. the Gel Electrophoresis Apparatusus GE 2/4 and GE 2/4 LS, and the Flat Bed Electrophoresis apparatuses FBE Immuno and FBE 3000) or with any other suitable electrophoresis or immunoelectrophoresis chambers.  In addition, the EPS 500/400 is designed to be used with the Pharmacia Volthour Integrator, VH-1.  An outlet is provided on the EPS 500/400 for connection to this accessory.  The Volthour Integrator is an advanced concept that brings added precision to electrophoretic experiments.  It is designed to integrate the voltage applied to the electrophoretic system with time, so that experiments are accurately defined in terms of volthours.

Title: Pharmacia Volthour Integrator VH-1 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pharmacia Volthour Integrator VH-1 can only be used when connected to a suitable Pharmacia Power Supply ECPS 3000/150, or the Electrophoresis Power Supply EPS 500/400 (with digital readout) both of which have the relevant Remote Outlet.  The Volthour Integrator will operate only with a low voltage source and must never be connected to the mains supply.

Title: Pharmacia Gel Electrophoresis Apparatus GE-2/4 LS Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pharmacia Gel Electrophoresis Apparatus GE-2/4 LS is a multipurpose apparatus for vertical electrophoresis in polyacrylamide gels.  It is designed for high resolution techniques such as electrophoresis in gradient gel slabs, SDS work, molecular weight determinations and isoelectric focusing.  The apparatus is ideal for two dimensional work using the O'Farrell technique for instance, and is designed to accept gel slabs of various sizes up to 180 mm wide by 200 mm long, as well as various gel rods up to 180 mm long.  The apparatus will handle up to 4 slabs 80 mm wide, 1 or 2 slabs 180 mm wide or up to 20 gel rods at one time.  Full details of the gel cassettes and gel rods available for this apparatus are listed in Table 1.  Polyacrylamide gels in cassettes 80 x 80 and 80 x 140 mm in size are cast in the Pharmacia Gel Slab Casting Apparatus GSC-8.  Gel casting in cassettes 180 x 140 and 180 x 200 mm is undertaken in the Pharmacia Gel Slab Casting Apparatus GSC-2.

Title: Pharmacia Destainer GD-4 II Specifications & Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Destainer GD-4 II is for fast, effective destaining of gel slabs and gel rods by electrophoresis and for destaining by diffusion with solvent circulation.  The destainer has the capacity to destain 8 standard (80 x 80 x 3 mm) or 4 large (140 x 80 x 3 mm) gel slabs or 16 gel rods (max. length 14 cm) simultaneously.  The apparatus consists of a solvent vessel containing a holder for a dye adsorbent bag, a circulating pump which is mounted on the vessel, and a top-plate which carries the electrodes, electrode connecting leads and holders for holding the gels during destaining.  The Pharmacia Gel Destainer GD-4 is supplied for use with the Pharmacia Destainer Power Supply DPS or other low-voltage power supplies of sufficient power output.  It is a part of the complete Pharmacia system for electrophoresis, which is described in a free booklet available on request.  Two gel rod holders and a dye adsorbent bag for anionic dyes are supplied with the apparatus.

Title: Pharmacia Gel Slab Drier with Heater GSD-4 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pharmacia Gel Slab Drier with Heater GSD-4 is designed for drying Pharmacia gradient gels PAA 4/30 and PAA 2/16, and any other kind of homogeneous and gradient polyacrylamide gels.  The GSD-4 produces tough, transparent dried gels for autoradiography, fluorography, densitometry or notebook record.  Gels are rapidly dried between cellophane membranes by heating under reduced pressure.  The heavy duty, high capacity Gel Slab Drier accepts single gels of up to 200 x 180 mm in size.  Slab gels, such as those used in two-dimensional electrophoresis with the Pharmacia Electrophoresis Apparatus GE 2/4 LS can be easily dried in the GSD-4.  Up to eight Pharmacia PAA 4/30 or PAA 2/16 gradient gels can be dried simultaneously.

Title: Pharmacia Reservoir R 15/16 Specifications & Instructions
Desc: The Pharmacia Gel and Eluant Reservoir R 15/16 functions both as a packing device and as a Mariotte flask with columns of the K 15 and K 16 series.  As a packing device it consists of a cylinder with a conical adaptor, which screws onto the column, and a screw cap.  As a Mariotte flask, the same cylinder and screw cap are combined with a similar screw cap carrying an adjustable Mariotte tube.  The reservoir is supplied as a packing device.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Pharmacia Reservoir R 25/26
Desc: The Pharmacia Gel and Eluant Reservoir R 25/26 functions both as a packing device and as a Mariotte flask with columns of the K 25 and K 26 series.  As a packing device it consists of a cylinder with a conical adaptor, which screws onto the column, and a screw cap.  As a Mariotte flask, the same cylinder and screw cap are combined with a similar screw cap carrying an adjustable Mariotte tube.  The reservoir is supplied as a packing device.

Title: Pharmacia VacuGene XL Vacuum Blotting System Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pharmacia VacuGene XL Vacuum Blotting System uses a low pressure vacuum to transfer nucleic acids from a gel to a transfer membrane.  DNA and RNA fragments separated by agarose gel electrophoresis can be transferred, ensuring that optimal results are obtained even from genomic DNA digests.  The procedure is rapid with transfers taking a maximum of one hour.  The VacuGene XL unit is convenient and easy to use, with both pretransfer and transfer steps being carried out in the blotting unit.  The gel to be transferred is placed on the transfer membrane which is held within a "window" in the waterproof mask.  The mask is supported on the porous screen in the base of the VacuGene XL unit.  After locking the upper frame to the base, the base is evacuated and the gel is flooded sequentially with depurination, denaturation, neutralisation and transfer solutions.  By subjecting the gel continuously to a vacuum, transfer of nucleic acids to the transfer membrane occurs in one direction only.  The VacuGene XL Unit accepts gels up to 20 cm x 30 cm.  The transfer procedure is reproducible and, since no stacks of paper are required and most solutions can be recycled, the unit is inexpensive to run.  The transfer procedure is safe and efficient.  No high voltages are used and the transfer efficiency is high, usually better than 95%.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Phillips Steam Heated Vapor Degreasers Installation Operation Maintenance Handbook
Desc: The Phillips Steam Heated Vapor Degreasers Installation Operation Maintenance Handbook: A solvent is used and brought to a vigorous boil by the steam coil.  The boiling solvent creates a vapor which is able to permeate and dissolve oils, waxes, or substances which have a base soluble in the solvent used.  The cold room temperature metal parts condense the hot vapors as they make contact, thereby stripping the parts of any oils.  When the metal parts reach the same temperature as the vapors, the cleaning cycle is over, however globs of contaminant may still be removed by the heat of the vapors and by use of the flushing hose, parts must be up to vapor temperature.  Upon slow removal from vapor zone parts will be dry and clean.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: PHI DT5000 Controller/Programmer Operating Manual
Desc: The PHI DT5000 Controller/Programmer is a Microprocessor Based Multichannel Controller/Programmer.  It monitors and controls up to 4 independent channels utilizing a standard 3 mode (PID) control scheme, including anti-reset windup.  Numerous alarm functions are incorporated to monitor various system parameters.  It also contains a 16 segment setpoint and event programmer, as well as a serial interface so it may be used with the DT5500 Press Controller.  Each channel may operate independently or channels may be programmed to operate together (Master-Slave) in any combination.  In all cases the operator instructs and views the channels via a master control program that simplifies the human interface.

Title: Photo Research UCI-80 Level II MOD VIII Software for IBM PC/XT/AT and Compatibles--1980B Systems
Desc: The Photo Research UCI-80 Level II MOD VIII Software for IBM PC/XT/AT and Compatibles--1980B Systems SpectraMetrics Operating Instructions: The UCI-80 Level II MOD VIII Software is designed to integrate the PR-1980B Spectroradiometer System with IBM Compatible computers, via IEEE-488 or RS-232 interfaces located on the 1980B UCI Console.  The software is based on the Universal Computer Interface Command Language (UCICL), which is designed to afford maximum measurement flexibility: DOS-System based software utilizes this flexibility in a user-friendly package.  The MOD VIII package is menu-driven, allowing the user to use pre-programmed functions that call up UCICL Commands for measurement set-up, initiation, and data and file handling.  Program functions of the MOD VIII software include the performance of spectral or spatial measurements (either singly or in multiples), and multi-interval scans (which allow for different increments to be chosen within a single scan).  The instrument can also be set up to perform a series of Spectral scans at up to eight spatial positions, or a series of spatial scans at up to eight wavelengths.  Includes system 5.25" disks.

Title: Photovac MicroTIP Hand Held Air Monitor/Photoionization Detector User's Manual
Desc: The Photovac MicroTIP Hand Held Air Monitor/Photoionization Detector measures the concentration of airborne ionizable gases and vapors and automatically displays and records these concentrations.  MicroTIP operates automatically.  The user reads concentrations directly from MicroTIP's display.  The display updates itself each half second.  The Minimum, Maximum, and Average concentrations measured in each 15-second period are automatically recorded in MicroTIP' datalogging memory.  MicroTIP's memory holds the last 12.0 hours of concentration data measured.  Concentration data can be played back from memory on MicroTIP's display or sent to a printer or computer in either tabular or graphical form.  Data are recorded by date, time, and by a user-entered event number.  Data are played back by the user specifying a start and a stop event number.

Title: Photovolt Aquatest IV Operating Instructions
Desc: The Photovolt Aquatest IV is an automatic analyzer for the determination of water.  It is the most advanced version of Photovolt's coulometric titrators and incorporates microprocessor control.  It is based on the specific and quantitative reaction of water with Karl Fischer reagent.  This instrument is unique in that the reagent is generated electrolytically rather than added from a burette.  This eliminates the need for standardization or calibration because 1 coulomb is equivalent to 186.53 micrograms of water.

Title: Photovolt Aquatest II Model 702 Test Procedures
Desc: The Photovolt Aquatest II Model 702 Test Procedures contains test procedures and electrical schematics.  The Aquatest II is the newest completely automatic titrator for the determination of traces of water.  Water is titrated by the electrolytic generation of Karl Fischer reagent.  Aquatest obsoletes manual and automatic titrators.  It is no longer necessary to standardize, add or measure reagents.  Because it reads out directly in micrograms of water, no computations are necessary.  Furthermore, the unit is always ready for the next sample.  The Aquatest II accepts solid samples as easily as liquid samples.  The sample capacity is 200 ml.--Aquatest II operates at ambient pressure.  This, with other improvements provides a large sample capacity, long chemical life and low operating cost.  A "CAUTION" light indicates electrode failure, coated electrodes, or clogged pores at the electrode junction.

Title: Packaging Industries Sentinel Impulse Sealer Model SC Series
Desc: The Packaging Industries Sentinel Impulse Sealer Model SC Series provides controls over every phase of a heat seal, with an instrument panel mounted and marked for ready reference.  After determining the proper settings for voltage, pressure, impulse time for sealing and dwell-time for cooling, it is possible to seal a wide variety of thermoplastic films of many thicknesses, including polyethylene, saran, pliofilm, nylon, acetate, mylar, and vinyl.

Title: PI - Packaging Industries Sentinel Impulse Sealer Model 12 SC Series
Desc: The Packaging Industries Sentinel Impulse Sealer Model SC Series provides controls over every phase of a heat seal, with an instrument panel mounted and marked for ready reference.  After determining the proper settings for voltage, pressure, impulse time for sealing and dwell-time for cooling, it is possible to seal a wide variety of thermoplastic films of many thicknesses, including polyethylene, saran, pliofilm, nylon, acetate, mylar, and vinyl.

Title: Pine Instrument AFASR Analytical Rotator Instruction Manual
Desc: The Pine Instrument AFASR Analytical Rotator has been designed to rotate a disc or ring-disc electrode at precise adjustable speeds up to 10,000 RPM.  The Rotator is generally used as part of a system, which may include a potentiostat, X-Y recorder, electrodes and cell.

Title: Pitney Bowes Model 6200 Modular Mailing Machine Operating Guide
Desc: The Pitney Bowes Model 6200 Modular Mailing Machine consists of a basic mailing machine that processes meter mail individually conforming to specific size limitations.

Title: Plasmatic Systems PLASMA-PREEN System User Manual
Desc: The Plasmatic Systems PLASMA-PREEN System is a plasma etching system capable of performing many functions in the plant or laboratory.  This system is manufactured from a microprocessor controlled microwave oven and uses the relevant digital control functions incorporated in the microwave oven.  The PLASMA-PREEN system also has an additional analog power control feature added to provide a wider control range of plasma power.  This system operates by flowing a process gas (usually oxygen or argon) at reduced pressure (from 1 to 5 torr) through the process chamber and exciting the plasma discharge with the microwave energy from the microwave oven.  This process produces ionized gas species and free radicals within the gas.  These active species sputter and/or react with the work within the chamber.  Since this process occurs in the gas phase at reduced pressure, little material is consumed or discharged.  Reactions occur at the work surface (gas solid interface and are subject to the geometrical constraints this arrangement introduces.

Title: PMC Industries Model 440A DATAPLATE Hot Plate/Stirrer Instruction Manual
Desc: The PMC Industries Model 440A DATAPLATE Hot Plate/Stirrer is designed to do a number of jobs within the laboratory.  Contains illustrations.

Title: Polymer Laboratories DMTA Software for Hewlett Packard 200 Series Computers User's Guide
Desc: The Polymer Laboratories DMTA Software for Hewlett Packard 200 Series Computers can be used for aiding calibration of the DMTA, controlling DMTA for various types of measurements, and retrieving DMTA data previously collected.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Polymer Systems 69-912 Lowline Granualtors & 68-912-1116-1120 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Polymer Systems 69-912 Lowline Granulators & 68-912-1116-1120 Beside the Press Granulators Instruction Manual contains procedures on the operation, maintenance, and safety precautions for these granulators.  Includes parts list, illustrations, and mechanical and circuit board schematics.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: PolyScience Model 73 Immersion Circulator Operating Instructions
Desc: The PolyScience Model 73 Immersion Circulator is a finely crafted electro-mechanical instrument which has been fully tested and packaged to rigorous standards.  Contains information on setup, operation, service, and troubleshooting of this apparatus.  Also contains illustrations and instructions for reuniting mercury columns in thermometers.

Title: Pope 2" Wiped-Film Still Owner's Manual
Desc: The Pope 2" Wiped-Film Still operates on the premise that liquid to be separated flows from the Feed and Degasser Flask on the still body inner wall by means of gravity.  Rate of flow is varied by adjusting the metering valve.  The revolving wiper blades contact this liquid and spread it out in a thin film and also create a turbulence to expose more of the material to the vaporizing heat.  The slots in the blades force the liquid downward.  Varying the speed of the motor will result in a change of flow rate downward of the liquid, thus varying its residence time in the heating zone.  Residence time can be somewhat increased over gravity flow by reversing the motor.  Depending upon the temperature at the evaporating surface, the more volatile components of the liquid will be evaporated as the liquid flows down the wall through the heating zone.  The resultant vapor contacts the condenser or condensers, where it is condensed and flows downward into the distillate receiver flask.  Any liquid on the evaporating surface which is not evaporated continues to flow downward and into the residue receiving flask.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Powers Process Controls Powers 535 1/4 DIN Process Controller User's Manual
Desc: The Powers Process Controls Powers 535 1/4 DIN Process Controller is designed to ensure the integrity of a user's process with maximum reliability from its surge-resistant power supply to its rugged construction--hour after hour, day after day.  The isolated inputs and outputs guard against the dangers of electrical interference, the front face meets NEMA 4X standards for watertight operation and exposure to corrosive environments, and the solid metal housing and sturdy rubber keys enhance durability and ESD protection.  The 535 has been engineered to be the industry's most user-friendly process controller.  With three digital display areas--two offering up to 9 characters of true alphanumerics--the 535 effectively eliminates the cryptic messages that could confuse even the most experienced operator.  The bright, crisp display is vacuum fluorescent, and offers much better readability than any other display technology.  Additional operator-friendly features include: custom programmable alarm messages, illuminated keys, and an easy-to-use menu system.  The 535 is the most accurate instrument in its class.  With a sampling rate of ten times per second, it is ideal for demanding pressure and flow applications.  The 535 also offers a universal process input and modular, field interchangeable outputs that allow more flexibility than ever before.  The RS-485 serial communications interface allows the controller to utilize sophisticated software routines and high speed hardware to provide exceptionally fast and accurate transmission of data.  The 535 also offers sophisticated control algorithms, including our exclusive Adaptive Tune which constantly analyzes the process and makes modifications to the tuning parameters to ensure the user is always under control.

Title: Practical Automation Moduprint Model A4-289 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Practical Automation Moduprint Model A4-289 Instruction Manual contains information on a Moduprint-type printer.  This manual has information on mounting, paper loading, re-inking, interchange, electrical characteristics, and power supply requirements.  Also contains schematics and diagrams.

Title: Precision Scientific Wet Test Meters Round 63111, 63115, 63119, 63123 Square 63125, 63126
Desc: The Precision Scientific Wet Test Meters Round 63111, 63115, 63119, 63123 Square 63125, 63126 are designed to provide an accurate measure of the total volume of gas flowing through them.  They are installed between the gas source and the fixture or apparatus using the gas.  The mechanism is simple and fool proof.  The incoming gas flows into a quadrant of the rotor.  This displaces the water in the quadrant, causing  the rotor to turn.  Gas cannot pass through the meter unless it follows this path.  Contains 4 identical copies in stock.

Title: Precision Saybolt 2 & 4 Tube Viscosimeters Operating Instructions
Desc: The Precision Saybolt Viscosimeters are designed to comply with the specifications set forth in ASTM D-88; and may be applied to test procedures such as A.P.I. Test Method 5.8, A.M.A. #Z11, 2, & Federal Test Method Standard 304.7. This operating instruction manual are applicable to Cat. 74962 and 74966, both units which re designed to operatre within the range of 70° to 210°F.

Title: Precision Reid Vapor Pressure Bath Instruction Manual
Desc: These instructions encompmass the Reid Vapor Pressure Baths model number 74893 and 74884. The Reid vapor Pressure Bath is designed to determine the absolute vapor pressure of volatile crude oil and volatile non-viscous petroleum products, except liquified petroleum gases, in accordance to ASTM D-323. It is also designed to determine the gage vapor pressures of liquified petroleum products under test temperautre conditions at 37.8°C (100°F), which is pertinent to problems of selecting properly designed storage vessels, shipping containers, and customer utilization of equipment to ensure the safe handling of such products, all in accordance to ASTM D-1267.

Title: Precision Saybolt Viscometer Instruction Manual
Desc: The Precision Saybolt Viscometer Instruction Manual encompasses the following models: 74939, 74966, 74965. These viscometers are built to conform to ASTM D88 and AASHTO T72, and ASTM E102 for model 74965 only. ASTM D88 covers procedures for determining the Saybolt Universal or Saybolt Furol viscosities of petroleum products at specified temmperatures between 21 and 99°C (70 and 210°F), while ASTM E102 covers procedures for determining the Saybolt Furol viscosities of bituminous materials at specified temperatures between 120 and 240°C (248 and 464°F). The efflux time in seconds of 60mL of sample, flowing through a calibrated orifice, is measured under carefully controlled conditions. The time is corrected by an orifice factor and reported as the viscosity of the sample at that temperature. 2 manual(s) in stock.

Title: Precision Saybolt 2 & 4 Tube Viscosimeters Operating Instructions
Desc: The Precision Saybolt Viscosimeters are designed to comply with the specifications set forth in ASTM D-88; and may be applied to test procedures such as A.P.I. Test Method 5.8, A.M.A. #Z11, 2, & Federal Test Method Standard 304.7. This operating instruction manual are applicable to Cat. 74962 and 74966, both units which re designed to operatre within the range of 70° to 210°F. 2 instruction manual(s) in stock.

Title: Precision General Purpose Ovens Instruction Manual
Model: STG 40, STG 80, STG 145, STM 40, STM 80, STM 135
Desc: Precision Scientific General Purpose Ovens Instruction Manual. STG models 40, 80 and 145 use gravity convection as a method of heat transfer within their respective chambers. STM models 40, 80 and 135 use mechanical convection as a method of heat transfer. All of the model STG and the model STM 40 ovens use two highly accurate hydraulic thermostats -- one control and one safety high limit. This provides a sensitivity to ±0.25°C. 2 manual(s) in stock.

Title: Precision Direct Drive Vacuum Pumps Owner's Manual
Desc: Precision Direct Drive Vacuum Pumps Owner's Manual for models DD-20, DD-50, DD-100, DD-90, DD_195, DDC-195, DD-310, DDC-310, DD-475, and DDC-475. This manual also includes pump assembly for DD-50 and DD-100. Model numbers refer to free air capacity of the pump. For example, model DD-20 will evacuate 30 liters of gas every minute at atmospheric pressure. DD series pumps are constructed with specifications for general application. DDC series has components selected for  more demanding application. 2 manual(s) in stock.

Title: Precision General Purpose Water Baths Instructions
Desc: Precision Scientific General Purpose Water Baths Instructions for model  numbers 180, 181, 182, 183, 184, 185, 186, 188 Dual, 190, and 261. Baths differ mostly in capacity for water, ranging from 2 to 50 L. All information within the manual refers to all models unless otherwise stated. Operation and maintenance of these baths are covered in this manual. 10 instruction manual(s) in stock.

Title: Precision Low Temperature Incumbators Instruction Manual
Desc: Precision Scientific Low Temperature Incubators Instruction Manual for incubator models 816, 815, and 818.The "PRECISION" Low Temperature Incubators have been designed to provide the ultimate in temperature control. The user is assured of dependable and precise performance through the use of solid state components in the temperature control circuitry. The Model 815 is operable in the range of -10° to 50°C. Models 816 and 818 are operable in a range of 10° to 50°C with interior illumination; without illumination the range is the same as model 815.

Title: Precision Automatic CO2 Water Jacketed Incubators Instruction Manual
Desc: Precision Scientific Automatic CO2 Water Jacketed Incubators Instruction Manual for models 1020 (Single Chamber) and 2020 (Double Chamber). Precision's constant temperature CO2 incubators provide a controlled environment for the growth of cultures common in virology, physiology and microbiology. The 1020 and 2020 have working capacities of 6.5 cubic feet (184 liters) and 13 cubic feet (368 liters) respectively. The model 2020 has independent temperature and CO2 controls and LED displays for each chamber.

Title: Precision Shaking Water Baths Operating Manual
Desc: Precision Scientific Shaking Water Baths Operating Manual for models 25, 50, and 75. These shaking baths utilize electronics and will provide the user with the utmost in temperature control, media agitation and versatility with regard to accommodation of glassware. Solid state time proportioning heat control allows precise temperature control within the range of -10° to 100°C. Oscillating speed is easily adjusted and not affected by voltage fluctuations. A meter is provided so that the rate of oscillation, 20 to 200 osc/min, can be readily observe and reproduced. 4 manual(s) in stock.

Title: Precision Shaking Water Baths Instruction Manual
Desc: Precision Scientific Shaking Water Baths Instruction Manual for models 25, 50, and 75. These shaking baths utilize electronics and will provide the user with the utmost in temperature control, media agitation and versatility with regard to accommodation of glassware. Solid state time proportioning heat control allows precise temperature control within the range of -10° to 100°C. Oscillating speed is easily adjusted and not affected by voltage fluctuations. A meter is provided so that the rate of oscillation, 20 to 200 osc/min, can be readily observe and reproduced.

Title: Packard Tri-Carb Sample Oxidizer Performance Verification Procedure
Desc: Packard Instruments Performance Verification Procedure for the Model 306 Tri-Carb Sample Oxidizer. All items required to perform this procedure are included with the instrument in the Spec-Chec kit consisting of nonactive spec-chec (50mL), tritium spec-chec (25mL), and radiocarbon spec-chec (25mL). The model 306 is used for liquid scintillation and burns samples with C14 or H3.

Title: Precision Orbital Platform Shaker Instruction Manual
Desc: The Precision Scientific Orbital Platform Shaker Model 360P Instruction Manual. The 360P provides for a smooth, quiet orbital shaking action required in tissue culture and biotechnology applications. The shaker is suitable for cold room application when sub ambient temperatures are required. The control panel contains an illuminated power switch, analog speed control, and a 12-hour timer with "Hold" function. Speed ranges from 40 to 400 RPM.

Title: Priority Co. Pritic Magnetic Principal Polishing & De-Burring Machine User's Manual
Desc: The Priority Company Pritic Magnetic Principal Polishing & De-Burring Machine User's Manual. The M-1 is used to smooth and polish burrs with magnetic media. The magnetic media (Stainless steel needle magnetized) which are not consumable goods can be used semi-permanently and can be managed very easily. And they are free from rust, wear and tear, and can be recovered simply and easily. The containers are polypropylene containers. Since each piece of the media moves independently, they do not clog. And since each of them is a permanent magnet, they react to magnetism, in other words, stainless steel needles rotates 360 degrees in all directions and penetrate into surface of minute forms, gaps, inside of pipes and even into one-sided holes and get into contact with everything everywhere to work on them evenly and without deforming anything. 2 manual(s) in stock.

Title: Priority Co. Pritic Magnetic Principal Polishing & De-Burring Machine User's Manual
Desc: The Priority Company Pritic Magnetic Principal Polishing & De-Burring Machine User's Manual. The M-1 is used to smooth and polish burrs with magnetic media. The magnetic media (Stainless steel needle magnetized) which are not consumable goods can be used semi-permanently and can be managed very easily. And they are free from rust, wear and tear, and can be recovered simply and easily. The containers are polypropylene containers. Since each piece of the media moves independently, they do not clog. And since each of them is a permanent magnet, they react to magnetism, in other words, stainless steel needles rotates 360 degrees in all directions and penetrate into surface of minute forms, gaps, inside of pipes and even into one-sided holes and get into contact with everything everywhere to work on them evenly and without deforming anything. 2 manual(s) in stock.

Title: Procedyne TPE Furnace Operating and Installation Instructions
Desc: Procedyne Corporation's Operating and Installation Instructions for the TPE 1030 Furnace. TPE furnaces utilize a dry fluidized bed as the heat transfer medium to provide a uniform, safe and inert high temperature environment for cleaning, incineration, heat treating, temperature testing and many other applications where a high heat transfer mechanism is desirable. The heat transfer medium in the calibration reservoir is air fluidized aluminum oxide, an inert solid material with a usable temperature to 1900°C. When properly fluidized, the particle bed becomes highly thermally conducting with fluid like characteristics. 2 manual(s) in stock.

Title: Procon Precision Crafted Positive Displacement Pumps Catalog
Desc: Catalog for Procon Products Precision Crafted Positive Displacement Pumps. Described in the catalog are the 6 series of vane pumps made by Procon, to give information to help decide which pump is needed for use or help order pumps.

Title: RF Shielded Ambient Temperature Photomultiplier Housings Instruction Manual
Desc: Products for Research, Inc. RF Shielded Ambient Temperature Photomultiplier Housings Instruction manual for PR-1400RF. The PR-1400RF and PR-1401RF housings are specifically designed to incorporate all of the important features for optimum PM tube performance. The PR-1400RF accomodates 2 inch and 1 1/2 inch diameter PM tubes while the PR-1401RF specifically houses 1 1/8 inch diameter and smaller PM tubes. 2 instruction manual(s) are in stock.

Title: PPI Agigated Reactor Instruction Manual
Desc: Pressure Products Industries Instruction Manual for 3M10 PMD reactor, 5M10 1 Gallon Reactor, and Impak VS Drive D-3701-4. Contains sections for installation, closures, agitator drives, operation, maintenance, heating & cooling, electrical circuits, safety devices, and miscellaneous parts. Includes bill of material and reactor schematics.

Title: PAR Electrochemistry System Instruction Manual
Desc: Princeton Applied Research Electrochemistry System Model 170 Instruction Manual. Model 170 is an all-electronic multifunctional electrochemical instrument capable of performing almost all known electrochemical techniques. Its capabilities include most forms of polarography, constant current or constant ptoential electrolysis, cyclic voltametry, coulometry, chronopotentiometry, chronocoulometry, etc. It incorporates a built-in X-Y plotter for accurate data recording and a potentiostat with ±100 volts of compliance and current capabilities of 1 amp at 100 V or 5 amps at 20 V.

Title: Q-Panel Accelerated Weathering Tester Operating Manual
Desc: Q-Panel QUV Accelerated Weathering Tester Operating Manual. The QUV Accelerated Weathering Tester is a laboratory simulation of the damaging forces of weather, for the purpose of predicting the relative durability of materials exposed to the outdoor environment. Rain and dew are simulated by a revolutionary condensation system. The damaging effects of sunlight are simulated by fluorescent UV lamps. Exposure temperature is automatically controlled, as is the daily sequence of UV periods and condensation periods. In a few days or weeks, the QUV can produce damage that might occur over months or years of outdoor exposure, Deterioration observed includes fading, chalking, cracking, crazing, hazing, blistering, gloss loss, strength loss, and embrittlement.

Title: Quantachrome Rotary Micro Riffler
Desc: The Quantachrome Rotary Micro Riffler was designed having in mind that the last step prior to any laboratory characterization or analysis of a powder should be the proper preparation of a representative sample.  Any attempt to prepare a representative sample larger than the size actually to be analyzed can and often does result in separation or misrepresentation when the sample is reduced to the quantity required for analysis.  Optimum results will be obtained when the collector head rotation rate is fast compared to the delivery rate.  This procedure will insure that each segment of an even grossly separated sample in the bowl will be delivered so that each collecting tube will acquire its representative portion.

Title: Quantachrome Penta-Pycnometer PP-3
Desc: The Quantachrome Penta-Pycnometer PP-3 is specifically designed to measure the volume and true density of solid objects.  This is accomplished by employing Archimedes principle of fluid displacement to determine the volume.  The displaced fluid is a gas which can penetrate the finest pores, thereby assuring maximum accuracy.  For this reason helium is recommended since its small atomic dimensions assures penetration into crevices and pores approaching one Angstrom in dimension.  Its behavior as an ideal gas is also desirable.  Other gases such as nitrogen can be used, often with no measurable difference.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Quantachrome Quantector Gas Flow System
Desc: The Quantachrome Quantector Gas Flow System uses the differences in thermal conductivity for gases and vapors in its operation.  A carrier gas is allowed to flow across two plated filaments into a glass cell containing the powder sample, then across two more filaments.  The four filaments constitute the arms of a "Wheatstone Bridge" circuit.  Any change in the concentration of the gas as it flows through the sample cell will result in a change in the temperature of the filaments.  The temperature change causes a variation in the filaments' resistance which in turn produces an unbalance of the bridge.  The unbalance is displayed by the meter mounted on the front panel of the Quantector.  A voltage output is also provided for monitoring the signals on a strip-chart recorder.

Title: Quantachrome Quantasorb Sorption System
Desc: The Quantachrome Quantasorb Sorption System determines the surface area of a sample by employing the techniques of adsorbing the adsorbate gas from a flowing mixture of adsorbate and an inert non-adsorbable carrier gas.  The process of adsorption and desorption is monitored by measuring the change in the thermal conductivity of the gas mixture.

Title: Quantel TDL50 Nd:YAG Pumped Dye Laser Operation and Maintenance Manual
Model: TDL50 with Additional Output Port & Shutter
Desc: The Quantel TDL50 Nd:YAG Pumped Dye Laser is designed for being pumped by a YG580 series YAG laser.  The complete YAG pumped dye laser is called Datachrom 5000.  Previous designs of Quantel dye lasers have used the grazing-incidence grating method for tuning.  The new Moya Dye Laser Cavity design improves the grazing-incidence method by using higher resolution gratings for better wavelength selectivity.  The key to the low level of fluorescence of the Moya oscillator lies in the pumping configuration and the way energy is coupled out of the cavity.  A portion of the intracavity beam undergoes total internal reflection off the dye cell window.  This configuration ensures that the main direction of emission of the fluorescence does not coincide with the direction of the beam.  The laser oscillation takes place between two totally reflecting mirrors.  Energy is coupled out by diffraction around one edge of the oscillator dye cell.  This configuration ensures that fluorescence coming back from the amplifiers does not hit any reflecting surface before striking the grating, thus dispersing it and attenuating it to very low levels.

Title: Radio Navigational Instrument Radio Set SCR-503-A Operating Instructions for War Department 9/1/43
Desc: The Radio Navigational Instrument Radio Set SCR-503-A for War Department 9/1/43, Order Number W2281-SC-311, consists of two portable direction finders, each an independent operating unit and differing from the other in frequency range; one covering the range of 1 to 3 mc in 2 bands, and the other covering the range of 100 to 1000 kc in 3 bands.  Each direction finder utilizes two loops, permanently displaced at an angle of 90° with respect to each other, and mounted on a common vertical axis.  This pair of loops called the loop assembly, on which is also mounted the collapsible antenna, is rotatable about its common vertical axis.  The signal picked up by each loop and by the antenna is fed through a pair of shielded conductors to separate collector rings, which rotate with the loop assembly, and thence through stationary brushes into the receiver.  Each receiver is a specially designed twin channel superheterodyne for AM signals and operates from a dynamotor power supply.  Each channel amplifies the signal received by its respective loop, and the separate amplified outputs are connected to individual movements of the bearing meter, the pointers of which move and intersect over a common dial.

Title: Queue Model 2700 Series Water-Jacketed CO2 Incubator Cell Culturing System Operators Manual
Desc: The Queue Model 2700 Series Water-Jacketed CO2 Incubator Cell Culturing System will provide the most maintenance-free, precisely controlled in-situ culture environments available.  This incubator is intended for use in applications such as growing eukaryotic cell culture, including hybridomas and fibroblast, where temperature, carbon dioxide, oxygen, and relative humidity levels must be accurately maintained.  This system automatically provides the fastest time to recovery of gas set points when the inner glass door has been opened and closed.

Title: Radiometer Copenhagen TTT60 Titrator Service Manual
Desc: The Radiometer Copenhagen TTT60 Titrator's primary function is to regulate the addition of titrant for end-point titrations where the amount of titrant necessary to reach a certain fixed end-point must be accurately measured.  In order to carry out a titration, the TTT60 must be connected to a pH meter and an autoburette.  To obtain short titration times and high accuracy, the titrator is built so that starting a certain distance from the end-point, the titration delivery rate is lowered as the sample's pH value nears the final value.

Title: Radiometer Copenhagen PHM82 Standard pH Meter Operating Instructions
Desc: The Radiometer Copenhagen PHM82 Standard pH Meter is a digital precision laboratory instrument which satisfies all normal requirements for pH and other potentiometric measurements.  The high input impedance in combination with the solid-state, drift-free amplifier ensures exceptionally high measuring accuracy, even when high-resistance electrodes are employed.  The wide pH-range in combination with the adjustable displacement voltage of 0 to ± 600 mV makes the instrument well suited for direct activity (pX) measurements with Selectrodes of monovalent as well as divalent ions.  The mV-range greatly facilitates all kinds of mV-measurements, e.g., concentration measurements with Selectrodes, redox measurements with redox electrodes and Dead-Stop End-Point titrations with the above mentioned displacement voltage used as polarizing voltage.  The recorder output makes PHM82 the ideal basic building block for systems, e.g., in the broad variety of Radiometer titration systems.

Title: Radiometer Copenhagen TTA80 Titration Assembly Operating Instructions
Desc: The Radiometer Copenhagen TTA80 Titration Assembly is intended for aerobic or anaerobic titrations in special titration vessels of samples from 0.5 ml to 45 ml, aerobic or anaerobic thermostatted titrations of samples from 0.5 ml to 45 ml, and titrations in open beakers of samples up to approximately 250 ml.  TTA80 is specially designed for optimal titration performance over a wide volume range.  It is a self-contained instrument offering the highest degree of accuracy and convenience.  The entire volume range is covered by only two electrode heads: The Standard Electrode Head covering the range 8-250 ml, and the Micro Electrode Head covering the range of 0.5-9 ml.  Both Titration Heads also facilitate the use of thermostatted jackets in conjunction with the VTS13 Water Thermostat.

Title: Rainin Dynamax RP-1 Peristaltic Pump User Guide
Desc: The Rainin Dynamax RP-1 Peristaltic Pump is specifically designed for fluid transfer.  The rotating head has ten stainless-steel rollers.  As the head rotates, five of the rollers press the tubing up against the compression arm, producing flow by peristaltic action.  Five rollers constantly in contact with the tubing ensures low pulsation, smooth flow, and high pressure.  The Model RP-1 pump is ideal for critical liquid chromatography, gradient generation, and flow analyzer applications.  The RP-1 incorporates a unique cam design: the adjustment screw does not press the compression arm directly.  Instead, turning the adjustment screw in the RP-1 moves a cam which applies gradual force to the compression arm.  This results in more precise flow control and reduced tubing wear.  The RP-1 is powered by a high torque stepper motor, controlled by a microprocessor with unique feedback circuitry for good speed stability, even at extremely low flow rates.  Speed stability is maintained between 0° - 40°C and against back-pressures of up to 5 bars.  Pump speed is shown in revolutions per minute and a liquid crystal display on the pump front panel.  Pump speed and decision of rotation are controlled by a membrane keypad next to the display.

Title: Rainin Instrument Rainin Rabbit Miniature Peristaltic Pump Instruction Manual
Desc: The Rainin Instrument Rainin Rabbit Miniature Peristaltic Pump consists of a Speed Control Base Module and a Pump Head.  The various size pump heads are interchangeable on the Speed Control Base.  Only two Allen-head machine screws fasten the head to the Control Module.  The correct installation of a different pump head is simplified by placing a dab of stopcock grease on the tongue of the white plastic coupling which is located between the motor and the shaft of the head.

Title: Rame-Hart Contact Angle Goniometer Instruction Manual
Desc: The Ramé-Hart Contact Angle Goniometer is part of Ramé-Hart's line of surface science instrumentation offering flexibility in studying surface phenomena.  This manual contains the NRL Contact Angle Goniometer System Guide along with setup and operating instructions for Model 100-00 NRL Contact Angle Goniometer, Model 100-10 Micro-Syringe Attachment, Model 100-07 Environmental Chamber, Model 100-09-10 Chamber Cover with Stage, Model 100-07-60QC Environmental Fixture, Model 100-11 Elevated Temperature Syringe Attachment, Model 100-06 Tilting Base Assembly, Model 102-00 Telegoniometer, and Model 100-08-30 High Pressure System. (see M-011130222)

Title: Raytest USA RAMONA Radioactivity Flow Through Monitor Operation Manual
Desc: The Raytest USA RAMONA Radioactivity Flow Through Monitor operation manual was written for the Ramona RM, A, B, 5, 6, and LS versions.  This apparatus is used for continuous measurement of beta-labeled and gamma-labeled substances in liquid eluates.  The optimum adaptation to the isotope is provided by selecting the scintillator and by setting discriminators to define accurately an energy counting window.  The design of the flow cells, the detector, and the measurement electronics is such that low-energy beta particles such as tritium can be measured with relatively high efficiency.  This also provides very sensitive photon recording in the measurement of bioluminescence and chemiluminescence in liquids.  The measurement cells are designed in such a way that the efficiency is relatively high while the background signal is relatively low.  Cells of various designs and different scintillators allow an optimum choice for all applications.

Title: Reliance Electric Reeves X-V Motodrive for Sizes A050-A100-A200 Instruction Manual G-3040
Desc: The Reliance Electric Reeves X-V Motodrive for Sizes A050-A100-A200 is a mechanical variable speed unit designed to provide infinitely variable speed through as much as 10-1 speed variation.  The variation is accomplished by means of a manually adjusted hand control, an electrical remote control unit or an air operated device called "Airtrol".  By changing the position of the constant speed adjustable disc and with the opposite reaction of the spring loaded disc on the variable shaft, the pitch diameters are shifted from one set of discs to the other thus varying the speed of the Motodrive output shaft.  The power of the unit as well as the speed variation is transmitted through a specially designed belt.

Title: Remcor Liquid Circulators Models CFF-250, 330 & 500 Owner's Manual
Desc: The Remcor Liquid Circulators Models CFF-250, 330 & 500 are self-contained units designed to maintain the temperature of many different liquids, both corrosive and non-corrosive, in such typical applications as photographic processing, chemical laboratories, environmental systems, and equipment cooling water jackets.  They consist of a circulating pump, heater, cooling system, heat exchange tank, and 2-stage thermostat, housed in a rugged cabinet with a baked-on grey "hammer tone" finish.

Title: Numinco Orr Surface Area Pore Volume Analyzers Models MIC 101, 102, 103 Service and Maintenance
Desc: The Numinco Orr Surface Area Pore Volume Analyzers Models MIC 101, 102, 103 Service and Maintenance manual is intended to assist the customer in properly setting up the Orr Surface Area Analyzers, maintaining them, and operating them at peak performance.

Title: Retsch Ultra Centrifugal Mill ZM 100 Operating Instructions
Desc: The Retsch Ultra Centrifugal Mill ZM 100 is suitable for crushing soft to medium-hard materials to a grain size of 10 mm.  This unit is designed as a laboratory unit for 8-hour, single-shift operations with a 30% duty cycle.

Title: Retsch Model DR 100 Vibratory Feeder Operating Instructions
Desc: The Retsch Model DR 100 Vibratory Feeder is a highly modern, high-performance product.  Many laboratory units work particularly efficiently when provisions are made for constant material feed.  Many processes can be simplified and improved in this way.  The operator can use these feeder units for uniform conveyance and feed of free-flowing bulk goods and powders.  Whether in direct conjunction with Retsch size-reduction units such as the ZM 1, ZM 100, ZM 1000 or sample dividers such as the PT 1000 and PK 1000 or for simple loading of scales and for mixing and agitating processes or measurement instruments: the DR 100 units are flexible and effective in use.  The specimen passes through the fill hopper and onto the vibratory feeder channel.  The latter is set in motion by an electromagnetic directional-throw vibrator at 50 or 60 Hz, giving uniform material conveyance.  The oscillation intensity and with it the feed speed are infinitely adjustable.  The feed period can be pre-selected and is shown digitally.  When operating under remote control, the DR 100 is controlled directly, in dependency on the momentary load, by downline units.  All the parts which come into contact with the products are made of stainless steel.

Title: Retsch Laboratory Sample Divider for the Representative Division and Reduction of Solids Brochure
Desc: The Retsch Laboratory Sample Divider for the Representative Division and Reduction of Solids are used for the representative division and reduction of flowable powders and granular substances.  The division of a sample into representative partial quantities is prerequisite to an exact chemical or physical analysis.  In addition, a reduction of the sample material in its entirety will be required in almost all cases since only small quantities and/or several identical portions are usually needed for such an analysis.

Title: Retsch Vibratory Mill, Type MM-2 Operating Instruction
Desc: The Retsch Vibratory Mill, Type MM-2 works in a three-dimensional motion for colloidal micro grinding and homogeneous mixing.  Maximum initial grain size is approximately 4 mm.

Title: Revco Chest & Upright Freezers Ultima 700 Series and Elite 500 Series Installation and Operation
Desc: The Revco Chest & Upright Freezers Ultima 700 Series and Elite 500 Series Installation and Operation Manual gives the user information on these apparatus.

Title: Revco Chest & Upright Freezers Ultima 700 Series and Elite 500 Series Installation and Operation
Desc: The Revco Chest & Upright Freezers Ultima 700 Series and Elite 500 Series Installation and Operation Manual gives the user information on these apparatus.  Includes a 5.25-inch floppy disc with Data Acquisition program for the acquirement of data from the freezer.

Title: Robinair Refrigerant Recycling Unit Model 17150A and 17151A
Desc: The Robinair Refrigerant Recycling Unit Model 17150A and 17151A for recycling refrigerant R-12, R-22, R-500 and R-502 is part of the Refrigerant Management System, which includes portable split-system units that make recovery and recycling practical, convenient, and affordable.  Designed as a companion to our Refrigerant Recovery Units, it's small enough to take to the job site and comes with dual filter-driers to handle even big systems.  It not only has multiple refrigerant capabilities for versatility and convenience, but can also handle any refrigerant tank with separate inlet and outlet.  It must be used with a recovery unit which has oil separation capability.  It features a dual filter-drier that is conveniently located with capacity for large system recycling, an air purge indicator gauge that lets you know when to purge air from the tank, a moisture indicator that clearly shows when refrigerant is ready to be reused, and a compact design--it weighs just 53.5 pounds.  The Refrigerant Recycling Unit contains only the components necessary for recycling refrigerant and must be used with a tank that has a liquid valve and a vapor valve.

Title: Rosemount Temperature Calibration and Interpolation Methods for Platinum Resistance Thermometers
Desc: Rosemount Temperature Calibration and Interpolation Methods for Platinum Resistance Thermometers Report 68023F.  Platinum Resistance Thermometers (PRT's) are made in a seemingly infinite variety of designs.  These designs vary in their ability to measure temperature with precision and accuracy.  It is useful to be able to recognize certain problems which limit the accuracy with which PRT's can be calibrated or used.  This paper addresses some of the problems which can be encountered and shows how they can be evaluated and minimized during calibration.  Additionally, the calibration report which accompanies all PRT's calibrated by Rosemount is discussed.  The data reduction methods are explained and illustrated by examples.  Suggestions are also presented which can enable the user to make better use of these reports.

Title: Ross Model LDM One Quart Ross Double Planetary Laboratory Mixer Installation, Operating, Maintenance
Desc: The Ross Model 130 LDM One Quart Ross Double Planetary Laboratory Mixer Installation, Operation & Maintenance Instructions contain the installation, operation, and maintenance information for the Charles Ross & Son Company's Ross Model LDM One Quart Ross Double Planetary Laboratory Mixer.  Also includes detailed mechanical schematics and handwritten parts list.

Title: Rudolph Research Visual Polarimeter Model 63 Instructions
Desc: The Rudolph Research Visual Polarimeter Model 63 is a moderately priced high quality polarimeter designed for the control or research laboratory where high cost is not justified but where optical rotation measurements of an accuracy approaching that of precision polarimeter are required.
