The polarimeter consists essentially of the following units; the analyzer unit, the polarizer unit, the base with tube trough unit.  The analyzer and polarizer are mounted at opposite ends of the one-piece cast aluminum base, with the tube trough mounted in optical alignment directly between them.  The light source, which is adjustable to facilitate proper optical alignment, is located beyond the polarizer at a fixed distance determined by the support arm and lens provided with the instrument.  The tube trough is detachable.  A 4" x 12" surface is provided at the bottom of the base 12' below the optical center to make the instrument readily adaptable for the insertion of temperature control of electro-magnetic units such as are used in studying the Faraday and Cotton-Mouton effects.  Also contains technical bulletins on various Rudolph Research equipment.

Title: Rudolph Research Visual Polarimeter Model 63 Instructions
Desc: The Rudolph Research Visual Polarimeter Model 63 is a moderately priced high quality polarimeter designed for the control or research laboratory where high cost is not justified but where optical rotation measurements of an accuracy approaching that of precision polarimeter are required.  The polarimeter consists essentially of the following units; the analyzer unit, the polarizer unit, the base with tube trough unit.  The analyzer and polarizer are mounted at opposite ends of the one-piece cast aluminum base, with the tube trough mounted in optical alignment directly between them.  The light source, which is adjustable to facilitate proper optical alignment, is located beyond the polarizer at a fixed distance determined by the support arm and lens provided with the instrument.  The tube trough is detachable.  A 4" x 12" surface is provided at the bottom of the base 12' below the optical center to make the instrument readily adaptable for the insertion of temperature control of electro-magnetic units such as are used in studying the Faraday and Cotton-Mouton effects.

Title: Rudolph Research AutoEL-III Condensed Operating Instructions
Desc: The Rudolph Research AutoEL-III Condensed Operating Instructions: The Rudolph Ellipsometer AutoELIII (single wavelength 6328Å) allows measurement of the thickness and refractive index of one or two thin transparent films on a substrate. The AutoEL III is designed to provide precision film thickness measurements with simplicity of use.  Internal data reduction software offers the convenience of automatically transforming delta and psi into the physical properties of thickness and refractive index.  The system’s non-volatile memory allows users to retrieve previously determined sample parameters during future measurements, to speed repeated analyses of similar materials.  The system's thermal printer can provide a hard copy of the results.

Title: RCA Video Camera Power Supply CPS03 Installation and Operating Instructions
Desc: The RCA Video Camera Power Supply CPS03 Installation and Operating Instructions contains information on setting up the power supply which is intended for use with RCA Color Cameras CKC018, CKC019, CKC020, CKC021, and CKC031.  Includes a connection diagram.

Title: Ruska Proportioning Pump Model 2259 NI M052 Operating Manual
Desc: The Ruska Proportioning Pump Model 2259 NI M052 Operating Manual contains information on this positive displacement pump.  This manual contains the operation and safety directions as well as parts list, diagrams, and schematics.  Also includes a Browning Double Reduction Worm Gear Reducer manual.

Title: Ruska Positive Displacement Pump Model 2234 (M979) Operating Manual for Proportioning Pumps
Desc: The Ruska Positive Displacement Pump Model 2234 (M979) Operating Manual for Proportioning Pumps contains the operation and safety directions as well as parts list, diagrams, and schematics.  Also includes a Browning Double Reduction Worm Gear Reducer manual, and 3 Zero-Max Series "S" and "W" gearheads instruction and parts booklets.

Title: RAC Micro-Bellows Metering Pumps
Desc: The RAC (Research Appliance Company) Micro-Bellows Metering Pumps are designed for laboratory, pilot plant, and chromatography applications.  This line of precision designs will pump corrosive and difficult-to-handle fluids or gases with optimum accuracy.

Title: Saft Standby Power System User Manual
Desc: The Saft Standby Power System protects data and equipment in such important applications as computer functions, security and alarm systems, manufacturing process controls, medical equipment, cash registers and communications equipment in two vital ways.  First, it acts as a transient voltage suppressor.  During normal line power operation, a suppression device keeps transient voltage spikes from entering sensitive equipment.  Secondly, inverter power is provided by the self-contained maintenance-free battery mated to sophisticated electronic circuitry.  The circuitry constantly monitors line voltage and automatically switches to inverter power in less than one-half cycle when line voltage drops to 15% below nominal.  When line voltage returns to within 7% of nominal the system will automatically switch to normal line operation.  An integral regulated charger maintains the battery at full capacity.  The front panel indicator lights together with an internal audible alarm report system status even warning of low battery in the case of an extended black-out.

Title: Sartorius Thermo Control YTC 01 L Installation and Operating Instructions
Desc: The Sartorius Thermo Control YTC 01 L Infrared Dryer is a highly sophisticated electronic instrument that will give the user years of service.  Sartorius will help lighten the daily workload with this Dryer.  This dryer features a phase-drying mode and drying with the automatic stop mode.  This manual conveniently contains English and German versions.

Title: Sartorius MC1 Balance/Scale Operating Manual
Desc: The Sartorius MC1 Balance or Scale can do much more than "just weigh."  It can "think" in various units of measure, adapt to unfavorable conditions and process weight data for a variety of applications.  In the operating menu, a user can define how the balance or scale will adapt to ambient conditions and also how it will work to meet any special requirements.  In addition to the functions implemented strictly for weighing, Sartorius Balances and Scales of the MC1 generation offer a variety of application programs for use in the laboratory or in industrial plants to handle tough daily routine work.

Title: Sartorius Interface WYD6039-a89111 Interface Description for Sartorius Balances and Scales
Desc: The Sartorius Interface WYD6039-a89111 Interface Description is written for users who wish to connect their Sartorius Balance or Scale to a computer or a peripheral device using a V24/V28-RS232C(-S)/423 interface.  By using an online computer, a user can change, activate, and monitor the functions of the balance/scale and dedicated Data Input software.  All Sartorius Balances and Scales equipped with dedicated software come with a V24/V28-RS232C(-S)/423 interface as a standard feature.  Also, the data transmission interface can be used independently of a dedicated application.

Title: Sartorius Research R 200 D Electronic Semi-Microbalance Installation and Operation Instructions
Desc: The Sartorius Research R 200 D Electronic Semi-Microbalance is a high-quality electronic weighing instrument that will ease a daily work load.  Manual contains information on the installation and operation of the Research Semi-Microbalance.  Conveniently written in 4 different languages.

Title: Sartorius Supermicro S 4 Electronic Ultra-Microbalance Installation and Operation Instructions
Desc: The Sartorius Supermicro S 4 Electronic Ultra-Microbalance is a sophisticated, high-quality precision weighing instrument that will hope ease daily work load.  Manual contains information on the installation and operation of the Ultra-Microbalance.  Conveniently written in both English and German.

Title: Sartorius Basic Balance Interface Description
Desc: The Sartorius Basic Balance Interface Description is written for users who wish to connect their Sartorius Balance, which has a built-in V24/V28-RS232C(-S)*) interface as a standard feature, to a computer or a different peripheral device.  By using an on-line computer, one can change, activate and monitor the functions of the balance.  In addition, a universal switch for remote control of various functions can be connected to the data interface port.

Title: Sartorius MP8-1/MP8-2/Data Input Interface Description
Desc: The Sartorius MP8-1/MP8-2/Data Input Interface Description contains information a variety of data input & output formats and other technical specifications regarding the data input interface for the Sartorius MP8-1 and MP8-2.  Conveniently written in both English and German versions.

Title: Sartorius Data Print 7079 in Connection with MP - Balances Installation and Operation Instructions
Desc: The Sartorius Data Print in Connection with MP - Balances 7079 Installation and Operation Instructions describes the installation and operation of the Data Print 7079.  Contains itemized diagrams for clarification purposes.  Also includes dual language instructions in English and German.

Title: Sartorius 2002 MP1 / 2003 MP1 Installation and Operation Instructions
Desc: The Sartorius 2002 MP1 / 2003 MP1 Installation and Operation Instructions contain the installation and operating instructions for these electronic analytical balances.  Contains itemized illustrations for clarification purposes.

Title: Savant AminoPrep Hydrolyzer AP100 Manual
Desc: The Savant AminoPrep Hydrolyzer AP100 is a convenient and safe hydrolysis apparatus.  Microprocessor control ensures consistent and repeatable results.  The AP100 uses a SpeedVac compatible rotor, which can accommodate tubes used in an amino acid analyzer.  The ability to move samples from the SpeedVac concentrator through hydrolysis and to analysis, without handling the samples, eliminates most of the manual labor and minimizes the risk of contamination.  Hydrolysis is achieved by bringing the sample into contact with a hydrolyzing agent such as hydrochloric acid, in the liquid or vapor state, at high temperatures.

Title: Savant AES1000 / AES2000 Automatic Environmental SpeedVac with VaporNet Instruction Manual
Desc: The Savant AES1000 / AES2000 Automatic Environmental SpeedVac with VaporNet is a complete system for solvent evaporation, sample concentration and drying.  AES systems use a patented technique which combines centrifugal force, vacuum and applied heat to eliminate sample bumping and foaming.  Application of thermal energy to the sample during concentration counteracts the natural evaporative cooling effect that slows the drying rate.  These systems integrate a SpeedVac concentrator, an oil-free vacuum pump, a refrigerated vapor trap with CFC free refrigerant and a patented VaporNet controller into a single compact package.  The AES2000 is a high capacity system for processing up to four 500 ml samples.  The AES1000 features a smaller chamber capable of processing up to four 100 ml samples.  Both units have an advanced front panel with dual timer for automatic or manual control of run parameters.

Title: Savant Automatic SpeedVac Concentrator Models AS160 & AS290 Manual
Desc: The Savant Automatic SpeedVac Concentrator Models AS160 & AS290 are complete, computerized systems for the rapid concentration and drying of liquid samples.  These units are based on a patented technique that combines the use of centrifugal force, controlled vacuum, and applied heat.  An advanced microprocessor design makes the units easy-to-use and ensures consistent and repeatable results.  Long and optimum operation is guaranteed through a built-in system of monitors and maintenance schedules.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock and an 1 addendum to manual.

Title: Savant Rotary Vacuum Pumps Models VP100 and VP190 Installation and Operating Instructions
Desc: The Savant Rotary Vacuum Pumps Models VP100 and VP190 Installation and Operating Instructions contain the setup, operation, and maintenance of the VP100 and VP190 pumps.  Contains price list and itemized diagrams for clarification purposes, as well as an exploded view diagram.

Title: Sargent-Welch SarVac Vacuum Pump 8803 & 8804 Owner's Manual
Desc: The Sargent-Welch SarVac Vacuum Pump 8803 & 8804 are direct drive, very lightweight portable units designed to be used in a wide range of vacuum applications.  The single stage SarVac, Model 8803, employs a single stage mechanism: a rotating concentric rotor containing two metal vanes, mounted eccentrically in a stage ring.  The rotor is mounted directly on to the motor shaft.  The pump unit and motor are mounted on opposite sides of a central cast iron mounting plate to which a base, handle and the in take nipple are attached.  The two stage SarVac, Model 8804, utilizes similar construction but the two stages are mounted in series on a common shaft which is driven by the motor through a shaft coupling.  The two stage pump has the vented exhaust feature to aid moisture removal.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Sargent-Welch DuoSeal Two-Stage Models & Single-Stage Models Owner's Manual
Desc: The Sargent-Welch DuoSeal Two-Stage Models 1374, 1375, 1376, 1392, 1395, 1396, 1397, 1398, 1400, 1402, 1405, and Single-Stage Models 1373, 1380, 1399, 1403, 1404, 1410 Owner's Manual was compiled not only for the care and maintenance of the DuoSeal pump but as a helpful reference and guide for many problems which are usually associated with mechanical vacuum pumps.  Contains information on installation, operation, maintenance, specifications, accessories, glossary, and reference data on these models.  Also contains illustrations, diagrams, and charts for reference.

Title: Lindberg/Blue M HTF55000 Series Hinged Tube Furnaces Installation and Operation Manual
Desc: The Lindberg/Blue M HTF55000 Series Hinged Laboratory Tube Furnaces feature Moldatherm.  Lindberg's vacuum formed ceramic fiber insulation and patented LGO (light gauge overbend) heating elements.  Available in standard single-zone and three-zone heated chambers for process tubes from 3/4 to 6 inches, these versatile tube furnaces are adaptable to a wide variety of processes.  In addition, these furnaces are designed to operate in either a horizontal or vertical position.  All 55000 series tube furnaces are designed for use with standard Lindberg 58000 series control consoles.

Title: Heat Systems-Ultrasonics Sonicator Microtips
Desc: The Heat Systems-Ultrasonics Sonicator Microtips attaches directly to the 0.5" disruptor horn and can treat volumes down to 2ml with the appropriate test tube.  It is particularly useful for difficult cells since the intensity is much greater than the regular step horn.  The special stepped microtip attaches to the convertor directly.  It has much lower intensity, but can process down to 0.25ml in the small culture tube.  Sample test tubes are supplied with both microtips.

Title: Sargent-Welch DuoSeal, DirecTorr, TurboTorr, CryoSource, & SarVac Vacuum Pumps and Accessories
Desc: The Sargent-Welch DuoSeal, DirecTorr, TurboTorr, CryoSource, & SarVac Vacuum Pumps and Accessories contains specifications and listings for Sargent-Welch's lines of products.  Sargent-Welch pumps are composed of either one or two stages, the number of stages being determined by the degree of vacuum desired.  The stages of a two-stage pump are connected in series and mounted on a common shaft in such a manner that one stage backs up the other to obtain the best possible vacuum.  Each stage consists of a rotor mounted concentrically on a shaft and located eccentrically in a generally cylindrical stator or ring, together with two movable vanes located diametrically opposite each other in slots of the rotor.  An important feature in the construction of Sargent-Welch pumps is the controlled clearance maintained between the moving elements of the stage.  Each element must have exactly the proper clearance to assure minimum friction as well as provide sufficient flow of oil for lubrication and adequate sealing against loss of vacuum.  The success of a good pump is determined, in part, by the control of these clearances.

Title: Schoeffel SD 3000 Spectrodensitometer Instruction Manual
Desc: The Schoeffel SD 3000 Spectrodensitometer is a double beam ratio type scanning spectrodensitometer, incorporating a high intensity continuous Xenon light source and a low stray light Quartz Prism Monochromator.  Thin layers, as well as gels and paper strips of all types, and preparative forms can be rapidly and very accurately scanned for quantitative determinations.  The instrument will also facilitate liquid samples in static or flow cells for a great number of investigations in the field of column chromatography, spectrodensitometry and kinetic and denaturation research.  This instrument provides the necessary sensitivity, accuracy and repeatability which is so essential for today's analytical work, together with a double beam ratio type system designed to eliminate errors due to changes in thickness of the base material.  The system also compensates for fluctuations in lamp intensity and photomultiplier tube supply voltage, making stable base lines an effortless accomplishment.  A complete line of accessories is available to complement the spectrodensitometer and increase its already superb versatility.

Title: Schott-Geräte Titration Unit TitroLine Alpha Operating Instructions
Desc: The Schott-Geräte Titration Unit TitroLine Alpha is a self-contained titration computer enabling versatile titrations in laboratories owing to its processor and hardware.  It is possible to carry out pH, redox, Karl-Fischer, and pH-stat titrations with up to 8 memorizable methods.  Apparatus applications include food technology, pharmaceuticals, biochemistry, photofinishing, environment, quality control, and process monitoring.  Owing to its connections the Titration Unit TitroLine Alpha is very versatile in combination with other devices.  Conveniently written in English, French, and German.

Title: Schott-Geräte TW 280 Titration Sample Changer Operating Instructions
Desc: The Schott-Geräte TW 280 Titration Sample Changer enables series titrations with automatic sample change.  It can be used for all samples which can be carried out in an open beaker glass.  With a suitable titration head, CSW titrations can be carried out directly in standardized reaction vessels according to DIN 38 409, part 41.  The Titration Sample Changer TW 280 is controlled via RS-232-C of computer or titrators' interfaces.  Conveniently written in English, French, and German.

Title: Schott-Geräte Titration Unit TitroLine Alpha Shortform Operating Instructions
Desc: The Schott-Geräte Titration Unit TitroLine Alpha Shortform Operating Instructions is a compact titrator with integrated dosing unit.  To assist the operator in setting up and installing the system, the manufacturer summarized the most important information and main steps in this short manual.

Title: Scientific Industries Vortex Genie 2 Mixer Models G560 and G560E Operating Instructions
Desc: The Scientific Industries Vortex Genie 2 Mixer Models G560 and G560E, with cup head and a three-inch platform head, is an upgraded version of the industry standard Vortex Genie Mixer with many new capabilities and features.  It has interchangeable Quick-Change snap-on heads which can be pressed on and popped off without the use of tools.  It features "constant" on and "touch" on capability.  The motor has been strengthened to accommodate the weight of the new functions.  The Vortex Genie 2 Mixer has both vortex and shaking actions greatly expanding the applications it can be used for.  So any desired mix homogeneity can be achieved (and repeated) according to viscosity, miscibility, and container.

Title: Scientific Industries Vortex-Genie Mixer Instructions for Use
Desc: The Scientific Industries Vortex-Genie Mixer is very simple to use and does not require any extensive practice or instruction.  It features an InstanTouch Starter Switch for automatic "start and stop" operation and a Variable Speed Control to regulate mixing action.  These instructions are a guide to its use.  This versatile mixer can quickly fit into the user's procedures and can be easily judged as to how much mixing time is required.  In some cases a quick touch for a fraction of a second is enough; or a few seconds may be required to dislodge a stubborn precipitate.  Various sizes and shapes of tubes and small flasks can be mixed on the Vortex-Genie.  Just try them out and it can be quickly determined what the greatest possible use out of the Vortex-Genie.  Contains 5 identical copies in stock.

Title: Sciex Auxilary Mass Flow Controller Kit Elan Set-Up Procedure
Desc: The Sciex Axillary Mass Flow Controller Kit Elan Set-Up Procedure documents the procedures for the Auxiliary Mass Flow Controller Kit #006910 for the Elan.  The procedure described in this document is test procedure #006672.

Title: SCP Process Controller 3150 Manual
Desc: The SCP Process Controller 3150 is a versatile module designed specifically for high and low constant temperature baths used in wafer processing.  It combines quartz precision timing and precise temperature control with a group of standard features including a self contained internal timer.  These specifically address the unique and ultra-critical world of wafer processing clean rooms.  The unit is a micro-computer controlled all-solid-state module featuring high reliability and plug-in modular serviceability.

Title: Sears Craftsman 12-Inch Band Saw/Sander Model 113.243300 & 113.243310 Owners Manual
Desc: The Sears Craftsman 12-Inch Band Saw/Sander Model 113.243300 & 113.243310 are basically "curve cutting" machines.  It is not capable of doing inside cutting.  The Craftsman Band Saw/Sander is not only capable of the usual band saw operations, but it can be converted into a sander as well.  The scientist can finish wood, certain compositions and plastics and non-ferrous metals.  It is also used for straight-line cutting operations such as crosscutting, ripping, mitering, beveling, compound cutting, and resawing.

Title: Separations Technology SepTech TurboPrep HPLC Equipment Software
Desc: The Separations Technology SepTech TurboPrep Innovative software designed for the automation of Preparative and Process HPLC Equipment is an interactive preparative and process HPLC control system.  The operator can automate sample injection, gradient formation, fraction collection and column switching.  Controls for each fraction collection and optionally for column switching can be timed, slope or external signal controlled.  All the automation power of TurboPrep can be used interactively.  This allows the operator to write a separation program while performing the operation for the first time.  The default conditions in the program allow the operator to perform all controls with a few key strokes.  The interactive nature of the program also allows editing on the fly of any controls that have not been completed.  This allows the operator to adjust a separation during operation in real time.  All operations are saved as a separation program.  The run data is also saved in a separate run data file.  This data can be recalled to review and/or print out all system settings and data.  This includes chromatogram plots.

Title: Serfilco Filters and Pumps Mermaid SCL10 1/2P SPPV S-1707 C Parts List and Operating Instructions
Desc: The Serfilco Filters and Pumps Mermaid SCL10 1/2P SPPV S-1707 C Parts List and Operating Instructions.  Documents installation, operating, safety precautions and parts list for the Mermaid Intank Filtration System.

Title: Shimadzu GC-7AG Series Gas Chromatograph Instruction Manual
Desc: The Shimadzu GC-7AG Series Gas Chromatograph is the latest gas chromatograph, which ensures top performance both in isothermal GC and in programmed temperature GC.  It can incorporate up to four detectors, out of thermal conductivity detector (TCD), flame ionization detector (FID), electron capture detector (ECD), flame photometric detector (FPD), and flame thermionic detector (FTD).  The GC-7AG Series is equipped with a ghost-cut type sample injection port, which eliminates ghost peaks that cause trouble in high-sensitivity analyses.  The modular electric control unit is fully digitalized to ensure ease of operation and excellent repeatability.  Data processing devices such as integrators and computers, automatic samplers, and various other accessories are available for automation of analyses.

Title: Shimadzu C-R3A BASIC Applied Programs
Desc: The Shimadzu C-R3A BASIC Applied Programs is a compilation of applied programs that contain programs relatively often used.  Desired programs can be input using the C-R3A keys, or the full keyboard, a special accessory.  Some program modification may be needed, depending on the intended use.  There is a wide range of applications for C-R3A BASIC programs; this collection contains only a portion.

Title: Shimadzu C-R3A BASIC
Desc: The Shimadzu C-R3A BASIC is designed to be used as a general data processor without BASIC programming.  However, programming will make the C-R3A more effective.  BASIC (Beginners All-purpose Symbolic Instruction Code) is a programming language widely used.  The C-R3A BASIC can be roughly divided into general BASIC and analytical BASIC.  General BASIC contains commands relating to fundamental BASIC programming and almost complies with the ANSI (ISO) standard.  Analytical BASIC is unique to the C-R3A, and therefore cannot be handled by ordinary personal computers.  Peak processing parameters, ID files, raw peak data and quantitative results can be handled by this BASIC, and also peak conditions and C-R3A conditions may be judged by the program.  In addition, when a GC-9A or LC-4A is connected through the current loop interface, analytical conditions for the GC-9A and LC-4A can be handled by this BASIC.  BASIC may look difficult for those who are not accustomed to it.  True, *ERROR* may be indicated or no operation may be conducted no matter what is done first.  However, as the operator gets used to it, the scientist will hopefully find it interesting, though individual differences are unavoidable.  This manual will let a user master BASIC, if trying to solve the problems contained in it and given the apparatus and enough time to practice.  The operator will become skilled by means of everyday practice.  Shimadzu would appreciate it very much if the scientist would acquire the knowledge of BASIC so as to make the C-R3A more effective.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Shimadzu UV-1601 Spectrophotometer User's System Guide Instruction Manual
Desc: The Shimadzu UV-1601 Spectrophotometer User's System Guide Instruction Manual documents the installation, construction, maintenance and checking, specifications, and optional accessories of the Shimadzu UV-1601.

Title: Shimadzu Specular Reflective Attachment for 5° Incidence Angle for UV-1200, 2200, and 3100 series
Desc: The Shimadzu Specular Reflective Attachment for 5° Incidence Angle for UV-1200 series/160(A)/240/250/260/265 and UV-2200 series/2100(S)/3100 series, MPS-2200 is used to measure the relative specular reflectance at an incidence angle of 5°.  A sample is to be placed horizontally on the stage facing downward, being illuminated from the bottom.  Therefore, the sample is easily to be set on the stage.  Includes companion manual written in Japanese.

Title: Sierra 900 Series Dual Channel System Unit Instruction Manual
Desc: The Sierra 900 Series Dual Channel System Unit is a highly integrated systems solution to flow measurement, and control.  One or two independent flow meters or controllers can be operated simultaneously.  Linear operation with LCD readout is standard.  The alphanumeric LCD reads out directly in units of measurement.  The back panel flow value outputs of 0-5 VDC and 4-20 Ma. are 0-100% analogs of the flow range.  Both voltage and current outputs are simultaneously available.  Flow setpoint for controllers is from either the front panel pots or a remote source via the back panel I/O interface.  Side=Trak controllers also incorporate valve purge/monitor/off functions accessible from the back panel I/O connector.  Each channel has a high and low alarm (open collector) output.  These alarm points are under System Unit control and can be read out on the front panel display for ease of adjustment.  An optional built-in totalizer on single channel configurations displays the total mass flow.  The electromechanical totalizer is highly immune to power line interruptions.  The power supply is a linear (non-switching) laboratory quality unit capable of easily supplying power to 2 channels simultaneously.  Contains 5 identical copies in stock.

Title: Sierra Series 741 Flo-Trak Air Flow Controller for Spinners Instruction Manual
Desc: The Sierra Series 741 Flo-Trak Air Flow Controller System for Spinners is designed to facilitate even drying of photoresist in semiconductor photolithography machines (spinners) by controlling the flow of drying air at the exhaust.  The system consists of a thermal mass flowmeter with integral motorized valve and a Power Supply box including LCD readout, set point potentiometer, 0-5VDC or 4-20mA outputs and optional alarms.  One to five channel systems are available.  Contains 5 identical copies in stock.

Title: Sierra 830/840 Side-Trak Mass Flow Meters & Controllers Instruction Manual
Desc: The Sierra 830/840 Side-Trak Mass Flow Meters and Controllers are used to measure control gas mass flow.  All Side-Trak flow meters rely on a large diameter thermal mass flow sensor which is virtually clog-proof.  The unique straight sensor tube has access ports at either end permitting easy cleaning.  316 stainless steel wetted surfaces and Viton seals are standard.  Controllers incorporate either an electromagnetic or a motor operated proportional control valve.

Title: Sierra Accu-Mass Flow Meter Systems Instruction Manual
Desc: The Sierra Accu-Mass Flow Meter Systems, within the flow body, senses the flow of gas mass that enters the flow body and goes through a precision flow nozzle within the flow body and exits the system.  The Accu-Mass flow sensor is a self-heated platimun resistance temperature detector (RTD) immersed in the flow.  Another RTD senses the temperature of the air and automatically maintains the velocity sensor at a constant temperature differential above ambient.  The unexcelled stability and reproducibility of RTD's has made them the standard of NBS.  The cooling effect of the air as it passes over the heated sensor is measured by the bridge voltage.  The resulting non-linear voltage/mass flow curve provides excellent rangeability and low-flow sensitivity.  Since the heat is carried away by the molecules in the air, the sensor measures air mass flow, referenced to standard conditions.  Direct measurement of mass flow means no temperature and pressure corrections are required - a disadvantage of other flow meters.

Title: Sierra AVS-600 Air Velocity Systems Probe Instruction Manual
Desc: The Sierra AVS-600 Air Velocity Systems probe has two sensors, a velocity sensor and a temperature sensor.  The velocity sensor is a self-heated platinum resistance temperature detector (RTD).  The bridge circuit continuously maintains the velocity sensor at a constant temperature differential above ambient.  The velocity sensor measures the cooling effect of the air as it passes over it.  The temperature sensor compensates for changes in ambient temperature.  The unique Accu-Flo probe is responsible for the unsurpassed accuracy, stability, ruggedness, and reliability of the system.  The unexcelled stability and reproducibility of RTD's has made them the standard of NBS.  The sensors are large, rugged, insensitive to dirt, and easily cleaned.  The circuit heats the velocity sensor at a constant temperature differential above ambient and measure the cooling effect of the air flow.  The resulting output provides unsurpassed low-speed sensitivity and a rangeability of 2000:1.  Since the heat is carried away by the molecules in the air, the sensor measures air mass velocity, referenced to standard conditions of 70°F and 760 mm mercury.  For most applications, standard velocity is the desired quantity because it is a measure of air mass velocity or air mass flow.  For "actual" velocity the standard velocity is simply multiplied by the air density ratio.  The probe has negligible flow blockage and pressure drop, resulting in energy savings.  The Accu-Flo probe is ideal for operation in buildings, outdoors, shops, and most other applications.  Dirty air flows can foul the sensors over extended operating periods.  If they get dirty, the sensors are easily cleaned manually.  Contains 3 identical copies in stock.

Title: Signature Label Ice Cream Dispensing Equipment Cleaning and Sanitation Program
Desc: The Signature Label Ice Cream Dispensing Equipment Cleaning and Sanitation Program is an overview of the various cleaning and sanitizing equipment designed for this sweetened frozen liquid dessert dispensing apparatus for super-happy-fun-time enjoyment.  A service of Ecolab, this booklet contains information on product line, product profiles and use instructions, start-up kit program, product material safety data sheets, and Occupational Safety and Health Administration regulatory compliance.

Title: Signet Scientific MK 509 Self-Powered Analog Flometer Instruction Manual
Desc: The Signet Scientific MK 509 Self-Powered Analog Flometer indicates flow rate of a liquid in a pipe by measuring the signal generated by a Signet Paddlewheel Flosensor.  The fluid level in pipes must be full for accurate measurements.  This measurement is displayed on a large, graduated analog meter.  The MK 509 utilizes a sensitive meter movement and applications in a high vibration environment should be avoided.  The MK 509 requires no routine maintenance.  The MK 509 is powered by the transducer signal generated within the Flosensor.  The MK 509 is designed for use with the MK 515 Paddlewheel Flosensor and MK 415 High Clearance Flosensor only.  Neither Flometer nor Flosensor requires an external power source.

Title: Signet Scientific MK 510/511 Flolimit Detector Instruction Manual
Desc: The Signet Scientific MK 510 and MK 511 Flolimit Detector are externally-powered analog amplifiers designed to sense when the flow rate received from a Signet Micro, Micet, Paddlewheel, or Magnetic Flosensor varies above and below user pre-set limits.  Exceeding these limits trips an alarm circuit which activates relay contact closure for controlling external equipment.

Title: Simplex Double Dial Clock Installation Instructions
Desc: The Simplex Double Dial Clock Installation Instructions succinctly lists the steps necessary to install this apparatus.  Tools required.

Title: Simco IOCLEAN Ionizing Blow-Off Gun and System Part Number 4001539 or 4001609
Desc: The Simco IOCLEAN Ionizing Blow-Off Gun and System Part Number 4001539 or 4001609 is used to remove micron size particulate contamination from critical surfaces in Class 10 or Class 100 clean room environment.  The IOCLEAN System consists of IOCLEAN blow-off gun, a package of 0.2 micron filters, gun stand, Control Monitor and Indicator Monitor.

Title: Simpson Model 5723 Temperature Controller Operator's Manual
Desc: The Simpson Model 5723 Temperature Controller is a precision electronic temperature controller, featuring the most modern designs in temperature control and proportioning circuitry.  This controller is distinguished by its broad capabilities where temperature applications require an accurate and reliable instrument.  The Model 5723 Controller employs a new type of proportioning control, whereby start-up of a system controlled by a Model 5723 occurs with a minimum of overshot of the controlled value.  Thus, the pre-adjusted set-point is obtained without deviation from the control point.  Furthermore, the sensing reaction to disturbances in the controlled system occurs quicker and more effectively than previously possible.  The Model 5723 Controller has continuously adjustable proportional control and a potential free relay output, or transistor output for Triac triggering.  This Instrument is insensitive to mounting position, resistant to shock and vibration.  It also has an actual value indication, and is a reliable, maintenance-free device.  Actual value indication is accomplished by means of a moving coil movement with internal core magnet and spring-loaded jewels.  The indication is made on a large, rotating 8-inch drum type scale, which permits easy readability of the indicated and set-point temperature.

Title: Skatron Microwash II Operating Manual
Desc: The Skatron Microwash II was manufactured due to the need to thoroughly wash the unbound antigen, antibody, binding protein, enzyme or receptor from the solid-phase binding support, one of the most important steps in the enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay.  This instrument meets this requirement and other requirements of numerous laboratory assays now being performed in 96 well microplates, wherein thorough washing is an essential component of the assay.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: SLM Aminco DW-2C UV-VIS Spectrophotometer Operator's Manual
Desc: The SLM Aminco DW-2C UV-VIS Spectrophotometer enables quantitative absorbance or % transmittance spectral measurements of compounds in solutions, turbid samples, fluorescent samples, or solid samples (when Solid-Sample Accessory is used).  Several modes of operation are provided.  When operated in the double-beam mode, a single monochromatic beams is alternately passed through a sample and a reference cuvette.  When operated in one of the dual-wavelength modes, two monochromatic beams of different wavelengths are alternately passed through a single cuvette.  The four modes of operation are double-beam mode, dual-wavelength (non-scanning) mode, dual-wavelength scanning mode, and rapid kinetics mode.

Title: Soltec 1244 & 1246 Flatbed Strip Chart Recorder Operator/Service Manual
Desc: The Soltec 1244 & 1246 Flatbed Strip Chart Recorders are high performance recorders with 250mm chart width, 4 to 6 channels, and overlapping pens which are suitable for laboratory use and systems application.  these recorders can be provided with a variety of options and input units.

Title: Soltec 6213 & 6223 Chart Recorder Instruction Manual
Desc: The Soltec 6213 & 6223 Chart Recorders are automatic null balance pen recorders that feature the proven engineering and reliability long appreciated by users of the VP-6500 series.  One-, two-, and three-channel models are now available.  Their feltpen and thermal-stylus writing systems put an end to ink problems.  External control functions and chart-speed control are standard on all models, making them useful not only in a wide range of laboratory measurements, but also as components of analytical and test equipment.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Soltec 1241, 1242, 1243 - 250 mm 1-3 Pen Strip Chart Recorders Operator/Service Manual
Desc: The Soltec 1241, 1242, 1243 - 250 mm 1-3 Pen Strip Chart Recorders are high performance recorders with 250mm chart width and 1 - 3 channel and overlapping pens which are suitable for laboratory use and systems application.  These recorders can be provided with a variety of options and input modules.

Title: Sonobond Model S-1260 Sonosolder Ultrasonic Soldering Equipment Instruction Manual
Desc: The Sonobond Model S-1260 Sonosolder Ultrasonic Soldering Equipment consists essentially of a small, hand-held soldering unit, a solid-state frequency converter, and a heating platen.  The soldering unit operates at a nominal frequency of 60 kHz.  The frequency converter operates from ordinary 120-volt, 60-Hz electric current and gives a rated power output of 12 r-f watts.  The platen can be heated to a maximum temperature of 750°F.

Title: Sorvall H-1000B Horizontal Rotor Instruction Manual
Desc: The Sorvall H-1000B Horizontal Rotor is designed for use in Sorvall RT6000 and GLC-4 Centrifuges.  The rotor assembly is composed of a stainless steel rotor body and four aluminum buckets which hang from the rotor body on support pins.  The buckets accept a variety of adapters made of glass-filled nylon.  The adapters accept glass or plastic tubes or bottles up to 70 mm in diameter.  Optional clear plastic bucket covers adapt the rotor for sealed centrifugation.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Sorvall A-500, A-384, M and SP/X Fixed Angle Rotors Instruction Manual
Desc: The Sorvall A-500 and A-384 Fixed Angle Rotors are designed for use in the Sorvall GLC-4 and RT6000 General Laboratory Centrifuges.  The Sorvall M and SP/X Rotors are designed for use in the Sorvall RC-3 General Purpose Centrifuge as well as the Sorvall GLC-2B and GLC-3 General Laboratory Centrifuges.  Each rotor assembly is composed of a stainless steel rotor body and a stainless steel rotor cover.

Title: Sorvall RC-5B Refrigerated Superspeed Centrifuge Instructions
Desc: The Sorvall RC-5B Refrigerated Superspeed Centrifuge Instructions documents the installation and operation of this centrifuge.

Title: Sorvall SS-3 Automatic Superspeed Centrifuge Instruction Manual
Desc: Sorvall SS-3 Automatic Superspeed Centrifuge is designed to perform high-speed separation of samples, prepare samples for virus and particle counting and provide zonal separation by centrifugal force.  The centrifuge is a table-top model which uses a fan cooled brush-type motor with automatic acceleration and dynamic braking.  A Gyro-Action Centering Drive accepts a variety of Sorvall rotors.  The chamber has a leakproof seal around the base of the drive assembly.  The centrifuge is finished in corrosion-resistant gray epoxy enamel.  The steel cover is equipped with a spring catch which locks onto the heavy steel safety guard in the centrifuge chamber in case of impact.  The rear and bottom panels of the centrifuge can be removed to service the unit.  Air intakes at the bottom and rear of the instrument direct cool ambient air at the rotor/drive bearings and motor/electrical components.  Exhaust outlets are in the rear of the centrifuge.  Inlet and outlet ports in the chamber wall permit the use of Sorvall continuous flow systems in the SS-3 Centrifuge.

Title: Sorvall RC-3B General Purpose Automatic Refrigerated Centrifuge Operating Instructions
Desc: The Sorvall RC-3B General Purpose Automatic Refrigerated Centrifuge is a large capacity, versatile, quiet and reliable centrifuge for low speed (to 6000 rpm) work designed to meet the needs of research and clinical laboratories, blood banks and plasmapheresis centers.  The centrifuge system has a fan-cooled motor with automatic programmed acceleration and braking.  The motor is balanced to ensure smooth, quiet operation over its full speed range and to promote long life for the brushes and bearings.  A gyro-action drive with a square spindle drive shaft accepts a variety of Sorvall rotors.  A clear acrylic viewing port located in the center of the chamber door permits calibration of rotor speed with a stroboscope.  The refrigeration system consists of a low-temperature condensing unit with a twin cylinder, hermetically-sealed power assembly (motor and compressor), a finned condenser and a fan.  The cooling system is designed to maintain temperature within 3°C of setpoint.  The centrifuge includes the following safety features: protective, armor plate steel guard within the cabinet; automatic shutoff of the drive motor for overspeed protection and of the refrigeration motor to prevent damage from overheating; electrical circuit breakers on the main power and the control panel circuits; operating controls which may be changed during operation without damage to the centrifuge; and a door interlock which prevents opening the chamber door while the rotor is in motion and/or starting of the rotor drive while the door is open.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Sorvall Super T 21 Refrigerated Tabletop Superspeed Centrifuge Operating Instructions
Desc: The Sorvall Super T 21 Refrigerated Tabletop Superspeed Centrifuge combines the high speed and capacity of a traditional floor-model superspeed centrifuge with the convenience of a tabletop centrifuge.  It reaches a maximum speed of 21,000 rpm and a maximum relative centrifugal force of 49,555 g, and it fits on top of a typical laboratory bench.  In addition, several rotors are available for the centrifuge.  The rotors have nominal tube capacities that range from 1.5 to 250 ml.  The centrifuge has a brushless dc drive, a high-capacity refrigeration system charged with SUVA refrigerant, one of Sorvall's CFC-replacement coolants, and a unique rotor identification system.  All systems are microprocessor-controlled.  The control panel is designed for ease of operation, both for basic runs where only speed, time, and temperature are selected and for specialized runs where one or more of the advanced features are selected.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Sorvall RC-3B Plus General Purpose Automatic Refrigerated Centrifuge Operating Instructions
Desc: The Sorvall RC-3B Plus General Purpose Automatic Refrigerated Centrifuge is a large capacity, versatile, quiet and reliable centrifuge for low speed (to 6000 rpm) work designed to meet the needs of research and clinical laboratories, blood banks and plasmapheresis centers.

Title: Sorvall MC 12V & MC 12C Tabletop Microcentrifuges Operating Instructions
Desc: The Sorvall MC 12V & MC 12C Tabletop Microcentrifuges are compact, non-refrigerated tabletop microcentrifuges that are designed to rapidly sediment cells, cell debris, large particles, and both DNA and macromolecular precipitates from small volume samples.

Title: Sorvall RC-3B Plus General Purpose Automatic Refrigerated Centrifuge Condensed Operating Instruction
Desc: The Sorvall RC-3B Plus General Purpose Automatic Refrigerated Centrifuge Condensed Operating Instructions are intended to be used only as a guide to operate the RC-3B Plus.  Sorvall Centrifuges recommends that the user read the instruction manual thoroughly, particularly all Warnings and Cautions, before operating the centrifuge.

Title: Sorvall RT6000B and T6000B Tabletop Centrifuges Operating Instructions
Desc: The Sorvall RT6000B combines the feature of the tabletop centrifuge and those of the larger refrigerated centrifuge in a compact tabletop instrument.  It is similar to other Sorvall Tabletop Centrifuges, with an added refrigeration system that consists of an evaporator/rotor chamber and a low-temperature condensing unit.  The system is designed to maintain temperature within 1°C, while in the operating range of -5°C to +25°C.  The T6000B is a non-refrigerated tabletop centrifuge.   (two copies, plus Condensed Operating Instructions)

Title: Span LR300 Multi-Channel Display/Controller Installation and Step-By-Step Operating Instructions
Desc: The Span LR300 Multi-Channel Display/Controller is a microprocessor based display/controller.  It combines indication, control and computer interface into one unit.  The LR300 is a single, two, or four channel display designed to monitor analog input signals.

Title: Spectra-Physics Model 102 & 105 Scientific Helium-Neon Lasers
Desc: Spectra-Physics Model 102 & 105 Scientific Helium-Neon Laser is an acronym for Light Amplification by Stimulated Emission of Radiation.  Four unique properties distinguish this apparatus from conventional light sources: directionality, intensity, monochromaticity, and spatial coherence.

Title: Spectra-Physics Labnet Operators Manual Part Number A0099-083
Desc: The Spectra-Physics Labnet is a low-cost, easy-to-use interactive communications network designed specifically for automating chromatography system laboratories.

Title: Spectra-Physics SP4100 Autolab BASIC Manual Part Number A0099-085
Desc: The Spectra-Physics SP4100 Autolab BASIC is the programming "language" used to communicate with the SP4100.  It is a variation of BASIC (Beginner's All-Purpose Symbolic Instruction Code) developed originally at Dartmouth College.  Autolab BASIC is designed for laboratory functions possible with SP4100.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Spectra-Physics SP4200 Operator's Manual
Desc: The Spectra-Physics SP4200 Operator's Manual

Title: Spectra-Physics SP4400 Integrator Technical Reference Manual
Desc: The Spectra-Physics SP4400 Integrator makes logical decisions concerning peak detection, integration and baseline correction for all types of peaks.

Title: Spectra-Tech The Collector Drift Accessory With Blocker Device Set-Up and Alignment Instructions
Desc: The Spectra-Tech The Collector Drift Accessory With Blocker Device is designed for use in FTIR spectrophotometers.  The design employs 4 flat and 2 aspherical reflectors, plus an alignment mirror.  The aspherics are off-axis ellipsoids which focus and collect infrared energy with a 6X condensation of the beam. (see also M-001130304)

Title: Spectra-Tech IR-Plan Instruction Manual
Desc: The Spectra-Tech IR-Plan is a research grade visible light microscope and a high performance infrared sampling accessory for use with FT-IR spectrometers.  The IR-Plan will use either the FT-IR's detector or can be equipped with an optional dedicated MCT (Mercury Cadmium Telluride) detector.  Performance of the microscope is directly related to the detection system.

Title: Spectrex In-Situ Liquid Particle Counter Model ILI 1000 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Spectrex In-Situ Liquid Particle Counter Model ILI 1000 Inspection Station is designed to permit thorough inspection of bottled liquids without breaking any seal or removing any of the contained liquid.  Visual observation of large tramp solids is assisted by diffuse vertical illumination.  A laser beam is provided to permit observation of small particles by near-forward light scatter.  In addition, a scanning and detection system is provided to automatically quantify the number of small particles in one milliliter of the contained liquid.

Title: Spectrolab Model XT-10 Spectrosun Solar Simulator Operation and Maintenance Manual
Desc: The Spectrolab Model XT-10 Spectrosun Solar Simulator is a versatile laboratory light source developed and manufactured by Spectrolab, Inc., a subsidiary of Hughes Aircraft Company, Sylmar, Calif.  The Model XT-10 produces a stable, uniform light beam that simulates sunlight in both intensity and spectra content over a specified area.  Each XT-10 is designed and tested to achieve individual operational requirements of beam size, shape, intensity, and spectral characteristics.  Developed as an offshoot of the Spectrosun X-25, the portability of the XT-10 gives it a wide range of application where a precise, calibrated light source is required.

Title: Spiricon Laser Beam Diagnostics LBA2TIF Version 1.00
Desc: The Spiricon Laser Beam Diagnostics LBA2TIF Version 1.00 is a software utility program for converting Spiricon Laser Beam Analyzer data files to Tag Image File Format (TIFF) image files.

Title: SSI Model 232 Gradient Controller For Liquid Chromatography Operating Manual
Desc: The SSI Model 232 Gradient Controller For Liquid Chromatography creates solvent mixtures by using either one or two pumps.  In the one pump mode, binary or ternary mixtures are made based on operator-created methods that are saved in the Model 232's non-volatile memory.  One pump gradient solvent compositions are generated using high speed inert proportioning valves, usually without the need of external mixers.  Two pump gradient solvent compositions are generated by controlling the flow rates of frequency and analog controlled pumps connected to the Model 232.

Title: Stanford Research Model SR630 16 Channel Thermocouple Reader
Desc: The Stanford Research Model SR630 16 Channel Thermocouple Reader is a 16 channel "computing" microvoltmeter.  The unit can digitize 16 rear panel differential inputs with a resolution of 15 bits plus sign.  Gains and offsets are controlled to microvolt levels.  The dual slope integrating converter is synchronized to the line frequency for high noise immunity.  The unit completes 10/12 conversions per second when used on a 50/60 Hz line.

Title: Stanford Research Model SR200 Gate Scanner Module Operation and Service Manual
Desc: The Stanford Research Model SR200 Gate Scanner Module was designed to automate the procedure of recording a waveform from scanning the Delay Multiplier by plotting the Average Output vs. the Delay Multiplier setting on the SR250 Gated Integrator.  The SR200 provides the signals needed to scan the SR250's delay multiplier (to scan the sample gate through the waveform) and to control an X-Y chart recorder or strip chart recorder or oscilloscope.

Title: Stocker & Yale Model 9 Illuminator Operating Instructions
Desc: The Stocker & Yale Model 9 Illuminator offers 360 degrees of uniform shadow free light.  The polycarbonate plastic housing stays cool to the touch and does not radiate heat that could effect objects in the illumination field.  This unit comes complete with an adapter.  There are adapters available for virtually any microscope or camera lens.

Title: Stokes Model 900-518-1 "E" Single Punch Tablet Machine Operating Instructions and Parts List
Desc: Stokes Model 900-518-1 "E" Single Punch Tablet Machine is an eccentric cam type single punch tablet press.  Movement of the upper punch is controlled by an eccentric and that of the lower punch by a cam.  The pressure is applied from above.  A stationary core rod may be installed to allow the production of cored pieces.

Title: Stokes Model 187A Devaporizer Solvent Vaporizer for use with Oil-Sealed High Vacuum Pumps
Desc: The Stokes Model 187A Devaporizer Solvent Vaporizer for use with Oil-Sealed High Vacuum Pumps is used when operating an oil sealed high vacuum pump on a system containing vapors of a material which will dissolve in oil.  This apparatus will remove continuously the solvent which condenses in the oil in order to maintain a high vacuum.

Title: Stokes Tablet Hardness Tester Bulletin
Desc: The Stokes Tablet Hardness Tester measures tablet hardness directly, expressing this in terms of the kilograms of pressure required to crush the tablet.  This reading may then be correlated with the desired physical characteristics of the tablet, its composition and method of manufacture.

Title: Stokes Model (A3) Tablet Machine # 900-511-1 Installation and Operating Instructions
Desc: The Stokes Model (A3) Tablet Machine # 900-511-1 is a hand operated single punch tabletting press of the bench mounting type.  Movements of the upper and lower punches are controlled by eccentrics.

Title: Stokes Model 900-511-1, 2, 3 and 5 Tablet Machine
Desc: The Stokes Model 900-511-1, 2, 3 and 5 Tablet Machine is a hand operated single punch tabletting press of the bench mounting type.  Movements of the upper and lower punches are controlled by eccentrics.

Title: Sterling Sterlco Temperature Control Unit Models R6412-A & R6422-A Service and Instruction Manual
Desc: The Sterling Sterlco R-Series Sterl-Tronic Temperature Control Unit Models R6412-A & R6422-A are noteworthy for their extreme simplicity of operation.  Other than one extremely important operation, that of venting the unit, there is nothing more to do than turn the unit on and set the desired temperature on the potentiometer dial.

Title: Stratagene Gigapack II Plus Packaging Extract Instruction Manual
Desc: The Stratagene Gigapack II Plus Packaging Extract has been developed to increase the efficiency and representation of libraries constructed from highly methylated DNA.  The packaging extracts are hsd-, mcrA-, mcrB-, and mrr-.  When used in conjunction with restriction deficient plating cultures, Gigapack II packaging extract should improve the quality of DNA libraries constructed from methylated DNA.

Title: Stratagene Epicurian Coli AG1 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Stratagene Epicurian Coli AG1 Instruction Manual

Title: Stratagene Epicurian Coli JM101 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Stratagene Epicurian Coli JM101 Instruction Manual.

Title: Structural Behavior Engineering Laboratories RM 101 & RM 102 Direct Shear Machines Instructions
Desc: The Structural Behavior Engineering Laboratories RM 101 & RM 102 Direct Shear Machines Instructions

Title: Structural Behavior Engineering Laboratories DR-44, RM101, & RM102 Direct Shear Machines
Desc: The Structural Behavior Engineering Laboratories DR-44, RM101, & RM102 Direct Shear Machines Operating Instructions.

Title: SumX SX-405 Data Acquisition System
Desc: The SumX SX-405 Data Acquisition System is a state-of-the-art microprocessor-based data acquisition system designed as a cost-effective solution for air quality and meteorological monitoring applications.  The unit is designed to collect, process, and telemeter data.  The SX-405 is a completely self-contained device that can be operated in a variety of configurations.  Data can be retrieved from the SX-405 via real-time printers at the site, magnetic tape devices, or telemetry links to central computers.  The SX-405 is a powerful tool that allows an operator to interrogate and interact directly with it.

Title: Supelco HPLC Troubleshooting Guide: How to identify, isolate, and correct many HPLC problems
Desc: The Supelco HPLC Troubleshooting Guide: How to identify, isolate, and correct many HPLC problems offers a systematic means of isolating, identifying, and correcting many typical problems that continue to arise even though HPLC separations have been improved by recent advances in column technology and instrumentation.

Title: Supelco Capillary Troubleshooting Guide: How to Locate Problems and Solve Them
Desc: The Supelco Capillary Troubleshooting Guide: How to Locate Problems and Solve Them is a systematic approach to troubleshooting problems with a capillary GC system by identifying the cause of the problem without wasting time.  The guide also contains suggestions for maintaining the system, including the column, at optimal performance levels.  By following these recommendations, repair costs and instrument down time can be reduced.

Title: Sybron Maxi-Mix Vortex Mixer LT268X1 Operating Instructions and Parts List
Desc: The Sybron Maxi-Mix Vortex Mixer Model M-16715 & Model M-16710-12 Series 268 Operating Instructions and Parts List

Title: Sybron Type 1000 Stir Plate LT273X1 Series 273 Operating Instructions and Parts List
Desc: The Sybron Type 1000 Stir Plate LT273X1 Models SP-A1024B, SP-1025B, and SP-A1020B Series 273 are magnetic stirring hot plates designed to provide a uniform source of heat from ambient temperature to 700°F and stirring capability from 60 to 1000 rpm.  A bimetal control keeps the surface temperature constant to ± 5°F over the entire operating range.  Excellent speed control, especially at low speeds, is achieved by a unique system of eddy current breaking.

Title: Sybron Maxi-Mix Vortex Mixer LT241X1 Operating Instructions and Parts List
Desc: The Sybron Maxi-Mix Vortex Mixer Model M-16715 & Model M-16710-12 Series 241 Operating Instructions and Parts List

Title: Sybron Furnatrol I Series 212 Models CP-18215, CP-18218, CP-18210 Series 212 Operating Instructions
Desc: The Sybron Furnatrol I Series 212 Models CP-18215, CP-18218, CP-18210 Series 212 LT212X4 is a completely solid-state non-indicating temperature control system.  Fully automatic, this controller eliminates variations in temperature due to line voltage variations and ambient temperature fluctuations and provides very stable operating temperatures down to 200-300°F.  Thermocouple break protections is inherent in the circuit design.  This prevents element burnout if the sensor should open.  Elimination of relays and contractors permits extremely rapid cycling as is evidenced by the flicker of the cycle light.  This effects very close temperature control without the attendent troubles of short contractor life and noisy operation.

Title: Sybron Portable Oxygen Analyzer with Digital Output Meter 570A Servomex OA.570
Desc: The Sybron Servomex Portable Oxygen Analyzer with Digital Output Meter 570A OA.570 determines the oxygen content of a gas sample in the range 0 to 100% O2.  It is fully portable, being powered by self contained batteries.  The Analyzer, like all other Servomex oxygen analyzers, measuers the paramagnetic susceptibility of the sample gas by means of a proven magneto-dynamic type measuring cell.  It is one of a new range of Servomex oxygen analyzers, which incorporates the OA.500 Basic Oxygen Analyzer.

Title: Sybron PMC-51B Purity Meter/Controller Catalog Numbers E3423 & E3424, with B-51 Cell Number E3412
Model: PMC-51B E3423 & E3424, with B-51 Cell Number E3412
Desc: The Sybron PMC-51B Purity Meter/Controller Catalog Numbers E3423 and E3424, with B-51 Cell Number E3412 provides continuous resistivity (purity) readings of water leaving the water purifying unit, and includes internal set-point, circuitry for controlling a diverter valve, a remote alarm, or other type control.  This circuitry is programmed by a front panel control to trigger at any level within the range of the monitor.  Red and green lamps (LEDs) on the front panel of the meter constantly indicate if the measured value is above or below the set-point level.

Title: Systron Donner Concord Instrument Division Model 7004 Digital Multimeter Instruction Manual
Desc: The Systron Donner Concord Instrument Division Model 7004 Digital Multimeter is a full four-digit precision instrument.  It offers the five selectable functions of dc voltage, dc current, ac voltage, ac current and resistance.  The instrument utilizes an advanced Dual-Slope Integration design with an extremely low-noise input amplifier and a fully guarded, isolated input circuit.  These features combine to provide high accuracy and stability, plus exceptional immunity to the effects of both common mode and normal mode noise.

Title: Tecator 1023 Filtration Module Manual
Desc: The Tecator 1023 Filtration Module is a component of the Fibertec E, an apparatus to rationally perform enzymatic procedures such as the AOAC, Asp's, and Furda's for such applications as measuring the dietary fiber content of food products.

Title: Tecator 1024 Water Shaking Bath Manual
Desc: Tecator 1024 Water Shaking Bath Manual is specially designed for use together with the 1023 Filtration Unit for enzymatic Dietary Fibre determinations, but with trays for various Erlenmeyer flasks it works as well as an ordinary laboratory thermostatic bath.  The 1024 Shaking Water Bath is an electronically controlled thermostatic bath with a temperature range from ambient to 80° C.  It is possible to preset three temperatures.  The shaking speed and amplitude are continuously adjustable.  The capacity of the bath is 12 Fibertec E flasks or 250 ml Erlenmehyer flasks / batch.  (two copies)

Title: Tecator Powdertec 3090 Sample Mill Instruction Manual
Desc: The Tecator Powdertec 3090 Sample Mill is designed for grinding a wide variety of medium hard to soft dry materials.  Application examples include chemicals, drugs, roots, wood, leather, food stuffs, grain, feed, spices, cellulose, textiles, coals, synthetic resins, soils and certain plastics.

Title: Techne SBL-1, SBL-2, and SBL-2D Fluidized Bath User's Manual
Desc: The Techne SBL-1, SBL-2, and SBL-2D Fluidized Bath User's Manual.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Techne SBS-2, SBL-1, SBS-4, SBL-2D Fluidized Bath Operating Instructions
Desc: The Techne SBS-2, SBL-1, SBS-4, SBL-2D Fluidized Bath Operating Instructions

Title: Techne RB-5 Refrigerated Bath Operating Instructions
Desc: The Techne RB-5 Refrigerated Bath is designed to work with Techne thermoregulators.  Heat is extracted continuously and in the 5 litre internal bath will cool to -20°C.  This apparatus is a compact economical unit quiet in operation.  Cooling air is drawn in through the front of the unit by a powerful fan which exhausts out of the rear of the unit.  The system is charged with R12 refrigerant which is circulated through a heat exchanger which is provided with pipes at the rear of the unit, connecting the system to the appropriate thermoregulator.

Title: Techne PHC-2 Dri-Block Operating Instructions
Desc: The Techne PHC-2 Dri-Block Operating Instructions

Title: Techne Model IFB-111 Industrial Fluidized Bath Operating Instructions
Desc: The Techne Model IFB-111 Industrial Fluidized Bath employs the principle of fluidization of a mass of finely divided inert particles by means of an upward flow of gas.  A state of fluidization is achieved when the individual particles become microscopically separated from each other by the moving gas.  This "fluidized bed" of particles has unusual properties which differ markedly from either those of the gas or of the solid particles.  Instead, the fluidized bed behaves remarkably like a liquid, exhibiting characteristics which are generally attributable to a liquid state.  For example, the fluidized bed can be agitated and bubbled; it always seeks a common level; materials of less density will float while those with densities greater than the equivalent fluidized bed density will sink; and, most important, the heat transfer characteristics between the fluidized bed and a solid interface can have an efficiency approaching that of an agitated liquid.

Title: Techne TC-8D Temperature Controller User's Manual
Desc: The Techne TC-8D Temperature Controller User's Manual

Title: Teledyne Taber Model 503 Abraser Operating Instructions
Desc: The Teledyne Taber Model 503 Abraser is a durable, precision built test instrument designed to evaluate the resistance of surfaces to rubbing abrasion.  Its field of application includes tests of solid materials, painted, lacquered, electroplated surfaces and plastic coated materials, textile fabrics ranging from sheer silks to heavy upholstery, metals, leather, rubber, and linoleum.  In the hands of a competent research technician it is capable of performing reproducible tests, accurate within the variations of quality inherent in the material itself.

Title: Teledyne Hastings Linear Mass Flowmeter NALL-100PG Instruction Manual
Desc: The Teledyne Hastings Linear Mass Flowmeter NALL-100PG in conjunction with using Hastings Mass Flow Transducer HS-100MSPX is designed to accurately measure mass flow without corrections or compensations for gas pressure and temperature.  Due to a linear electrical output signal, the flowmeters are ideal for use with totalizers and recorders.  Hastings Linear Mass Flowmeters do not require any periodic maintenance under normal operating conditions with clean gases.  No damage will occur from the use of moderate over-pressures, overflows, or liquid solvents.

Title: Teledyne Hastings Vacuum Gauge DNNV-800 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Teledyne Hastings Vacuum Gauge DNNV-800 is comprised of an indicator-power supply and a remote gauge tube.  This instrument is factory calibrated and ready fo ruse as received.  Merely plug the gauge tube type DV-800 into its cable, the power cord into 115 VAC, and the instrument is in operation.  It should read barometric pressure when exposed to the atmosphere.

Title: Teledyne Hastings Vacuum Gauge DNNV-800 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Teledyne Hastings Vacuum Gauge DNNV-800 is comprised of an indicator-power supply and a remote gauge tube.  This instrument is factory calibrated and ready for use as received.  Merely plug the gauge tube type DV-800 into its cable, the power cord into 115 VAC, and the instrument is in operation.  It should read barometric pressure when exposed to the atmosphere.

Title: Teledyne Hastings Mass Flowmeter NALL-500PG Instruction Manual
Desc: The Teledyne Hastings Mass Flowmeter NALL-500PG in conjunction with using Hastings Mass Flow Transducer HS-500MSPX is designed to accurately measure mass flow without corrections or compensations for gas pressure and temperature.  Due to a linear electrical output signal, the flowmeters are ideal for use with totalizers and recorders.  Hastings Linear Mass Flowmeters do not require any periodic maintenance under normal operating conditions with clean gases.  No damage will occur from the use of moderate over-pressures, overflows, or liquid solvents.

Title: Teledyne Tac PR-8100 Automatic Wafer Prober Version 1.0 User's Manual
Desc: The Teledyne Tac PR-8100 Automatic Wafer Prober is an advanced automatic prober incorporating a number of unique mechanical and software features.

Title: Tekmar Super Dispax Model SD45k and SD45N Instruction Manual
Desc: The Tekmar Super Dispax Model SD45k and SD45N units are efficient, high capacity dispersion and emulsifying devices for processing of samples between 100 ml. and 4 liters, depending on viscosity and type of generator used.  Both models use the same motor or drive unit and generators, only the shafts are different, but interchangeable.

Title: Tekmar Automatic Laboratory Sampler Model ALS Instruction Manual
Desc: The Tekmar Automatic Laboratory Sampler Model ALS is a ten position automatic sampler designed for use with the Tekmar LSC-2.

Title: Tekmar Gas Chromatograph Liquid Sample Concentrator Model LSC-2 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Tekmar Gas Chromatograph Liquid Sample Concentrator Model LSC-2 is an automatic purge and trap concentrator of a type first developed by Bellar and Lichtenberg.  It is designed to remove volatile and semi-volatile organic compounds from aqueous and solid matrices for subsequent analysis by gas chromatography.

Title: Tekmar SDT Tissumizer Laboratory Homogenizers with Shafts Instruction Manual
Desc: The Tekmar SDT Tissumizer Laboratory Homogenizers with Shafts SDT080EN, SDT100EN, SDT182E, and SDT182EN are proven efficient dispersion instruments for the processing of small amounts of material in a liquid volume of 0.3-5ml, 1-10ml, and 5-500ml.  The shafts and generators are interchangeable for use with the same motor.  The letter suffix "E" indicates the shaft and generators are appropriate for aqueous mediums only.  The "EN" suffix indicates usage in both aqueous and organic solvents is allowable.

Title: Tetrahedron PneuamPress P-300 Operating Manual
Desc: The Tetrahedron PneuamPress P-300 is an air-operated laboratory press having heated platens; continuous regulation of pressure; low and high pressure gauges, with automatic shutoff for the low pressure gauge and built-in air cooling.

Title: Thermo Automation Systems AS2000/TA200 Models 100450 and 100455 Automated Liquid Handling Stations
Desc: The Thermo Automation Systems Orion AS2000/TA200 Models 100450 and 100455 Automated Liquid Handling Stations are liquid handling automation workstations for the automation of laboratory applications such as sample preparation, sample introductions, and fraction collecting.

Title: Texas Instruments Multi-Range Model 157 Pressure Standard
Desc: The Texas Instruments Multi-Range Model 157 Pressure Standard combines highly accurate pressure measurement and pressure control in one convenient, compact instrument.  The Model 157 consists basically of interchangeable pressure capsules, a null-sensing optical readout unit, and a servo valve.  This combination produces a precision pressure instrument that combines accuracy with versatility and unexcelled convenience of operation.

Title: Texas Instruments Precision Pressure Gage Model 145 Accessories and Bourdon Capsules
Desc: The Texas Instruments Precision Pressure Gage Model 145 is a secondary or transfer standard for the calibration of pressure instruments or transducers, or for making very accurate pressure measurements.  This unit has accuracy comparable to the best primary standards, and is much easier and faster to use.  With interchangeable measuring capsules, it covers the range of 35 kPa (5 psi) full scale to 3450 kPa (500 psi) full scale using quartz tubes; to 69,000 kPa (10,000 psi) using metallic tubes.  All calibrations are traceable through standards which are directly traceable to the National Bureau of Standards.

Title: Texas Instruments Model 156 Precision Pressure Test Set Accessories and Bourdon Capsules
Desc: The Texas Instruments Model 156 Precision Pressure Test Set combines high-accuracy pressure measurement and pressure control in one convenient, compact instrument.  This apparatus consists basically of the Bourdon capsule, a null-sensing optical readout unit, and a servo controlled pressure regulator.  This combination results in an instrument that combines extreme accuracy with versatility and unexcelled convenience of operation.

Title: Texas Instruments Precision Pressure Gage Model 145 With Direct Pressure Readout Operating
Desc: The Texas Instruments Precision Pressure Gage Model 145 is designed to accurately measure absolute pressure, gage pressures, or differential pressures, depending on the Bourdon Capsule used.  The use of interchangeable Bourdon Capsules makes this wide range of pressure measurements possible.

Title: Thermo Electric Indicating Thermocouple Controller Models 32421 & 32422 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Thermo Electric Indicating Thermocouple Controller Models 32421 & 32422 are highly stable and accurate solid state instrumentation that provides automatic temperature control of a single electrically heated process.  The controller measures the millivolt output of a thermocouple positioned in the process and controls power output with a Silicon Controlled Rectifier to maintain process temperature.  The temperature control level is determined by the operator who adjusts the setpoint thumb wheel on the front panel.  Process temperatures within 50°F (25°C) of the setpoint are continuously read out on an indicating deviation meter above the setpoint scale.  The meter is calibrated directly in degrees Fahrenheit (or Centigrade).  To prevent overshoot and cycling at setpoint the controller provides proportional power output over a span or band which extends above and below the setpoint.  The width of this proportional band is adjustable.  The proportional band adjustment is mounted on the front panel.

Title: Thermo Electron MIRAN 205B Series SapphIRe Portable Ambient Air Analyzers Instruction Manual
Desc: The Thermo Electron MIRAN 205B Series SapphIRe Portable Ambient Air Analyzers consist of a group of infrared instruments that can monitor ambient air in workplace environments for the purpose of detecting the presence of gases.  Each analyzer contains a single-beam infrared spectrophotometer.  A microcontroller automatically controls the analysis, processes the measurement signal, and calculates the absorbance values.  Analysis results can be displayed in parts per billion, parts per million, percent, mg/m3, or absorbance units.  A rechargeable battery pack provides power for up to four hours of continuous operation.  The system includes a separate charger/power supply that allows the analyzer to be powered from an ac supply.  It is also used to recharge the battery pack either in an offline mode or while the analyzer is running in normal operating mode.

Title: Thermo Electron ThermoMatch Spectrum Correlation Software Instruction Manual
Desc: The Thermo Electron ThermoMatch Spectrum Correlation Software runs on an IBM PC compatible computer running Windows.  Most of the control is performed in, or via, a single Main screen.  ThermoMatch compares low ppm levels of IR spectra of unknown compounds against a library of known spectrum.  Additional functions of the program include the user's ability to view individual spectra for calibration and advanced analysis purposes.  The software includes a standard library which consists of more than 100 common compounds.  However, the number of potential compounds that can exist in the environment being monitored can far exceed this number.  Therefore, the SapphIRe and ThermoMatch should be considered tools which may need to be used in conjunction with other analytical tools and a working knowledge of IR spectra.  Includes CD-ROMs ThermoMatch Specrum Correlation Software for the MIRAN SapphIRe and ThermoConnect Software for the MRAN SapphIRe and the CENTURY TVA-1000B, as well as a 3.5" floppy diskette application setup disk Version 3.05 for Miran SapphIRe CR014NV-B.

Title: Thermo Savant VPOF110 Vacuum Pump Oil Filter/Recirculator Instruction Manual
Desc: The Thermo Savant VPOF110 Vacuum Pump Oil Filter/Recirculator continuously recirculates and filters the lubricating oil in an attached vacuum pump.  It effectively removes harmful acids, moisture, and particulate matter from the oil, prolonging the life of the vacuum pump.  The VPOF110 oil filter features a magnetically-driven, seal-less oil pump, an activated alumina cartridge housed in a polypropylene filter canister, and valved quick-disconnect hoses for the interconnection to the vacuum pump.  An on/off switch is provided, as well as an elapsed time meter.

Title: Thermo Savant RVT100, RVT400, RVT4104 Refrigerated Vapor Traps Instruction Manual
Desc: The Thermo Savant RVT100, RVT400, and RVT4104 Refrigerated Vapor Traps are reliable, easy-to-use, compact benchtop traps for solvent vapor condensation and collection.  Mechanically refrigerated vapor traps replace dry ice/methanol traps, and are the easiest, most practical, and safest way to protect high-vacuum, rotary vane oil pumps in a vacuum system.

Title: Thermo Savant VLP Series Vacuum Pump VLP80, VLP120, VLP200, VLP285 Instruction Manual
Desc: The Thermo Savant VLP Series Vacuum Pumps VLP80, VLP120, VLP200, and VLP285 are two-stage, oil-sealed, rotary vane vacuum pumps.  The pump has NW25 inlet and outlet ports, and a gas-ballast control.  When the pump is switched off, an inlet-valve seals the inlet and prevents the suck-back of air and oil into the vacuum system.

Title: Thermo Savant SC110 / SC110A / SC210A SpeedVac Concentrators Instruction Manual
Desc: The Thermo Savant SC110 / SC110A / SC210A SpeedVac centrifugal vacuum concentrators rapidly evaporate liquids to concentrate or dry solutes, analytes, and residues in aqueous and organic solvents.  Vacuum, applied to the sample chamber from an external source, promotes solvent evaporation.  As the rotor in the concentrator spins, centrifugal force keeps samples from foaming or bumping, preventing sample loss and resulting in superior analyte recovery.

Title: Thermolyne Types 461 & 462 General Purpose Laboratory Furnaces Operation & Instruction Manual
Desc: The Thermolyne Types 461 & 462 General Purpose Laboratory Furnaces F46110C, F46118C, F46120C, F46128C, F46130, F46138, F46230C, F46238C, F46240C, F46248C, F46250, and F46258 are general purpose laboratory furnaces intended for applications requiring temperatures from 200 to 1700 degrees C.

Title: Thermolyne Type 19300 Automatic Controller Furnatrol III Series 414 Operating Instructions
Desc: The Thermolyne Type 19300 Automatic Controller Furnatrol III Series 414 Models CP19320C, CP19320F, CP19325C, CP19325F, CP19340C, and CP19340F are microprocessor-based 3 mode controller.  They are intended for use on single or three phase electric muffle furnaces drawing up to 35A. rms. such as the Thermolyne type 1600, 1700, and 1800 furnaces.

Title: Thermolyne Type 6000 Series 408 Furnaces Owner's Manual
Desc: The Thermolyne Type 6000 Series 408 Furnaces Models F6010, F6018, F6020C, F6020F, F6028C, F6028F, F6030C, F6030F, F6038C, and F6038F are general purpose laboratory furnaces intended for applications requiring temperatures up to 2000°F (1093°C).
