Manual, automatic, and programmable models are available to meet the exact control requirements of most any laboratory procedure.  Each unit basically consists of a heating chamber, and temperature controller integrated into a single furnace system.  All that is required for operation is a compatible AC power source.

Title: Thermolyne Type SP13000 Multiple Unit Stirring Hot Plates Series 276 / 277 Operation Manual & Parts
Desc: The Thermolyne Type SP13000 Multiple Unit Stirring Hot Plates Series 276 / 277 are multiple unit stirring hot plates having individual temperature controls and synchronous stirring action.  Feedback-type electronic speed control makes the stirrer speed virtually independent of line voltage variations and the viscosity of the stirred liquid; there is no stirring "run away" as viscous liquids become thinner while being heated.

Title: Thermolyne Type 53600 Furnatrol II Temperature Controller Operation Manual and Parts List
Desc: The Thermolyne Type 53600 Furnatrol II Temperature Controller Models CP53610, CP53610-70, CP53640, CP53615, 53615-70, and CP53645 are microprocessor-based, 3 mode controllers.  They are intended for use on single phase, electric muffle furnaces drawing up to 35A. rms. such as the Thermolyne Type 1600 and 1700 furnaces.

Title: Thomas Technological Service Thomas-Wiley Mill, Model ED-5 Directions for Use
Desc: The Thomas Technological Service Thomas-Wiley Mill, Model ED-5 Directions for Use

Title: Thermo Separation Products SpectraSYSTEM Solvent Helium Module Reference Manual
Desc: The Thermo Separation Products SpectraSYSTEM Solvent Helium Module Reference Manual pertains to SHM2: Two-solvent Helium Degassing Kit with Solvent Bottle Holder (p/n A4122-010), SHM4: Four-solvent Helium Degassing Kit with Solvent Bottle Holder (p/n A4144-010), and Two-solvent Helium Degassing Kit (p/n A4125-010).  Contains 4 identical copies in stock.

Title: Thermo Separation Products SpectraSYSTEM UV/VIS Detectors Reference Manual
Desc: The Thermo Separation Products SpectraSYSTEM UV/VIS Detectors Reference Manual pertains to the UV1000 and UV2000 detectors.  The UV1000 detector is a time-programmable, variable-wavelength UV/Vis (ultraviolet/visible) absorbance detector.  It operates in single-wavelength mode in either the UV range (using a deuterium lamp), or in the visible range (with an optional tungsten lamp).  The UV1000's optical system has a novel, high light-throughput design that provides high sensitivity detection along with maximal application versatility.  The UV1000 detector can be upgraded to a UV2000.  The UV2000 detector is a full-featured, time-programmable, dual-wavelength UV/Vis absorbance detector.  It operates in both single- and dual-wavelength modes in the UV and visible ranges.  The UV2000 offers the same optical system design as the UV1000.  In addition, the UV2000 also offers spectral scanning, a Develop File (for method development), multiple file storage, a Queue feature (that allows you to link files), and more. -----------------------------21827182014502 Content-Disposition: form-data; name="WhereManualCameFromID"

Title: Thermo Separation Products SpectraSYSTEM Gradient Pumps Reference Manual
Desc: The Thermo Separation Products SpectraSYSTEM Gradient Pumps have been designed for ease of use and unsurpassed performance.  Any one of them can be used as a stand-alone pump or as a module in a totally automated LC system.  The P4000 pump provides low-pressure quaternary mixing for accurate proportioning of binary, ternary, or quaternary gradient mobile-phase compositions and solvent switching when used for isocratic applications.  The p4000 pump contains as many as two hundred time lines in as many as ten method files (forty lines per file maximum).  The P2000 pump provides low-pressure binary mixing for accurate proportioning of binary gradient mobile-phase compositions and solvent switching when used for isocratic applications.  The P2000 pump contains a total of fifty time lines in as many as five method files (ten lines per file maximum).

Title: Thompson-Chemtrex Portable Transfer Pump Operating Instructions and Parts List
Desc: The Thompson-Chemtrex Portable Transfer Pump Operating Instructions and Parts List for PF, TB, AP, BP, TT, BT, TM, and SC Series.  Contains 2 identical copies in stock.

Title: Topaz Line 2 Power Conditioner with PowerLogic Control Operating Manual
Desc: The Topaz Line 2 Power Conditioner with PowerLogic Control models 61505-02, 61507-02, 61510-02, 61515-02, 61605-02, 61607-02, 61610-02, and 61615-02 supply noise-free, regulated power to computers and sensitive electronic equipment.  Varistors on the input circuitry attenuate high voltage surges on the AC input line.  A unique shielding system in the Ultra-Isolator Noise Suppressor provides excellent noise attenuation and complete electrical isolation between the power line and the load.  A microcomputer system continually monitors the output voltage and regulates it to within a range of +4% to -8% of nominal by switching taps in the input winding of the transformer.

Title: Topaz Dacos Installation Procedure for Topaz Line 2 Power Conditioner
Desc: The Topaz Dacos Installation Procedure for Topaz Line 2 Power Conditioner details the installation and operational procedure for the Topaz Line 2 Power Conditioner.

Title: Tracor Instruments 540 GC Flame Ionization, Thermal Conductivity, & Electron Capture Detectors
Desc: The Tracor Instruments 540 GC Flame Ionization, Thermal Conductivity, and High Temperature Electron Capture Detectors Operation Manual contains the operating procedures for these 3 types of detectors for the Tracor Gas Chromatograph.

Title: Tracor Instruments Control of 540 GC by Serial Data Input Commands Operation Manual
Desc: The Tracor Instruments Control of 540 GC by Serial Data Input Commands allows for a computer to "take charge" of the Tracor Model 540 Gas Chromatograph.

Title: Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph Volume I Operation and Service Manual
Desc: The Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph in its most basic configuration consists of a column oven, a control unit, an inlet for one packed column, a detector, which may be either a flame ionization detector (FID) or a thermal conductivity detector (TCD), a flow controller for carrier gas and fixed restrictors for FID gas.

Title: Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph Volume II Operation and Service Manual; April 1984
Desc: The Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph Volume II Operation and Service Manual is a continuation of Volume I.  The Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph in its most basic configuration consists of a column oven, a control unit, an inlet for one packed column, a detector, which may be either a flame ionization detector (FID) or a thermal conductivity detector (TCD), a flow controller for carrier gas and fixed restrictors for FID gas.  This manual was is the Revised Edition April 1984.

Title: Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph Volume II Operation and Service Manual; October 1983
Desc: The Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph Volume II Operation and Service Manual is a continuation of Volume I.  The Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph in its most basic configuration consists of a column oven, a control unit, an inlet for one packed column, a detector, which may be either a flame ionization detector (FID) or a thermal conductivity detector (TCD), a flow controller for carrier gas and fixed restrictors for FID gas.  This version is from October 1983.

Title: Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph Volume II Operation and Service Manual; April 1985
Desc: The Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph Volume II Operation and Service Manual is a continuation of Volume I.  The Tracor Instruments 540 Gas Chromatograph in its most basic configuration consists of a column oven, a control unit, an inlet for one packed column, a detector, which may be either a flame ionization detector (FID) or a thermal conductivity detector (TCD), a flow controller for carrier gas and fixed restrictors for FID gas.  This manual was is the Revised Edition April 1985.

Title: Tracor Northern TN-6100 Series DARSS Detector Head Operator's Manual
Desc: The Tracor Northern TN-6100 Series DARSS (Diode Array Rapid Scan Spectrometer) Detector Head converts spectral information (energy) into a series of analog pulses.  The source of these pulses is a linear, self-scanned, silicon photodiode array having either 512 or 1024 elements.  In the normal mode of operation, the spectrum to be examined is projected onto the photodiode array by a spectrograph.  The individual photodiodes of the array are read out sequentially producing a train of pulses.  The height of a pulse is proportional to the amount of light falling on the corresponding array element.  Wavelength information is determined by the position of pulses in the readout sequence.  The spectral response of the TN-6111 and TN-6112 arrays covers the range from 200 to 1100 nm with a maximum sensitivity at about 850 nm, the typical silicon photodiode response.

Title: Tracor Northern TN-6500 Rapid Scan Optical Spectrum Analyzer Preliminary Operator's Manual
Desc: The Tracor Northern TN-6500 optical multichannel spectrum analyzer is designed to be used in conjunction with TN-6100 series DARSS detectors and appropriate optical components for the acquisition and analysis of optical energy between the wavelength of below 200 nm and up to 1100 nm.

Title: Tracor Northern TN-6051 Spectrometer Instruction Manual Revision A
Desc: The Tracor Northern TN-6051 Spectrophotometer allows absorbance measurements in the range form 200 nm to 1100nm.  Measurements in the range from 200 nm to 400 nm are done with a Deuterium light source.  In the range 400 nm to 1100 nm, a Tungsten lamp is used.

Title: Trebor Model 100 Teflon Pneumatically Operated Chemical Pump Operation Manual
Desc: The Trebor Model 100 Teflon Pneumatically Operated Chemical Pump has been designed to eliminate concerns associated with the nastiest chemical handling applications.  Because all wetted parts are composed of virgin Teflon materials, the Model 100 is contamination free and inert to virtually all process chemical fluids.  This makes the Model 100 ideal for handling such processes as recirculation, filtration, spray processing and sampling.  In addition, the Model 100 is a pneumatically operated, dual diaphragm pump that can deliver up to 5 gpm of process fluid at 60 psi air pressure.  This translates into an explosion-proof pump with a longer diaphragm life than is usually associated with diaphragm pumps; and, a pump that can deliver a maximum flow for its compact size.

Title: Trebor Magnum 600 High Capacity Teflon Pneumatically Operated Chemical Pump Operation Manual
Desc: The Trebor Magnum 600 High Capacity Teflon Pneumatically Operated Chemical Pump has been designed to eliminate concerns associated with the nastiest chemical handling applications.  Because all wetted parts are composed of virgin Teflon materials, the Magnum 600 is contamination free and inert to virtually all process chemical fluids.  This makes the Magnum 600 ideal for handling such processes as recirculation, filtration, spray processing and sampling.  In addition, the Magnum 600 is a pneumatically operated, dual diaphragm pump that can deliver up to 8 gpm of process fluid at 60 psi air pressure.  This translates into an explosion-proof pump with a longer diaphragm life than is usually associated with diaphragm pumps; and, a pump that can deliver a maximum flow for its compact size.

Title: Trio-Tech Model 481-F Filtration System Operation Manual
Desc: The Trio-Tech Model 481-F Filtration System is designed to filter fluorocarbon fluid to an absolute one micron purity level at temperatures from ambient to 130°C.  Fluid flows from the inlet hose through the filter element to the pump inlet, through pump to the outlet hose.  The time span of filtration operation is controlled by a mechanical timer, adjustable from 0-15 minutes.

Title: Trio-Tech 481 Series Bubble Tester Model G-203 Operations Manual
Desc: The Trio-Tech 481 Series Bubble Tester Model G-203 is a manual Bubble Tester designed to test microelectronic parts to MIL-STD-883.  The Bubble Tester consists of a tank containing a fluorocarbon liquid with a Pyrex plate glass front that allows undistorted viewing of the devices under test.  An externally-mounted lamp assembly illuminates devices under test.

Title: Turner Model 111 Fluorometer Printed Circuit Type Operating and Service Manual
Desc: The Turner Model 111 Fluorometer has been created to add the dimension of time or position to fluorescent measurements.  With this instrument and its accessories an operator will be able to record fluorescence or turbidity on any sample.

Title: Tylan Tymer 16 Programmable Sequencer Instruction Manual
Desc: The Tylan Tymer 16 Programmable Sequencer is a memory programmable sequential event timer.  The memory will hold a maximum of 96 sequential steps with rollover.  Each step can be programmed for a maximum of 999.9 minutes with any combination of 16 independent contact closures available on the rear terminal strip.  During both programming and automatic operation, the Tymer 16 front panel display provides the step number, time to go until the next step, and indicates which of the 16 outputs is energized.

Title: Tylan Mass Flowmeters, Mass Flow Controllers, Readout Boxes, Power Supplies Instruction Manual
Desc: The Tylan Mass Flowmeters, FM 360, FM 361, and FM 362, Mass Flow Controllers, and FC 260, FC 261, and FC 262, Readout Boxes, RO20A and RO21A, Power Supplies, PS14 and PS17A accurately and reliably measure and/or control the mass flow rate of gases up to 300 standard liters per minute (200 slm for controllers).  The principles of heat transfer are used to develop a linear output signal of 0 to 5vdc over the selected flow range.  Flow controllers incorporate a valve and appropriate electronics to automatically regulate flow in response to an external command.

Title: Tylan Mass Flow Readout/Control and Totalizer Models RT 7 and RT 8 Specifications and Schematics
Desc: The Tylan Mass Flow Readout/Control and Totalizer Models RT 7 and RT 8 are designed to operate with Tylan Mass Flowmeters, Flow Controllers and Vaporizer Controllers to provide the setpoint control and digital display of both flow rate and totalized flow.  The units integrate the flow signal from the flowmeter or controller and display or reading of the total amount of gas or liquid vapor that has passed through the unit.  This information is useful for both process control and accounting applications.

Title: Ultratech Model 504 Process Station with Frigidheat Temperature Control Unit
Desc: The Ultratech Model 504 Process Station with Frigidheat Temperature Control Unit is designed for use with Positive Photoresist Developer and D.I. rinse water.  The unit has two primary functions.  Developing and rinsing of positive photoresist on photomasks or wafers.  The heat pump recirculation system continuously tempers and filters the developer every 2 minutes through the dual filters and heat exchanger, then back to the holding tank until the develop process is started.  A Nitrogen blanket covers the holding tank.  A thermistor probe in the recirculation loop monitors the chemistry temperature.  A pressure switch in the pump discharge line shuts off the temperature controller and pump should fluid flow cease.

Title: Ungar Electronic Soldering System 9900 Power Base Models 9910, 9920, 9930, 9940, 9990 Owners Manual
Desc: The Ungar Electronic Soldering System 9900 Power Base Models 9910, 9920, 9930, 9940, 9990 is a variable temperature and electronically controlled unit which comes in twenty models.

Title: UPA Circuit Board Guide Model CB-3 Instruction Manual
Desc: The UPA Circuit Board Guide Model CB-3 is for the precise positioning of the HH-3 probe on printed circuit boards.  The Circuit Board Measuring System consists of a Probe Guide, and a Miniature Probe containing the source, Geiger Tube, and specimen mask.  The weight of the guide holds it securely in place on a circuit board while a spring in the probe clamp presses the probe firmly against the area being measured.

Title: UPA Probe System Model PS-10 Instruction Manual
Desc: The UPA Probe System Model PS-10 is an accessory that may be used with any Micro-Derm non-destructive thickness gauge.  It is ideally suited for measuring coating thickness on small parts such as transistor leads and headers, connectors, pins, flat packs, etc.  Aperture plates used with the Model PS-10 expose an area of the parts under test for accurate measurement on flat, cylindrical, spherical, or odd-shaped surfaces.

Title: UPA Technical Symposium on Advances in Beta-Backscatter Technology for Plating Thickness Measurement
Desc: The UPA Technical Symposium on Advances in Beta-Backscatter Technology for Plating Thickness Measurements details the beta-backscatter phenomenon as used in coating thickness measurements which can be described by an exponential equation.  The coating thickness depends on 2 constants and the normalized counts of the sample being measured.

Title: UPA Micro-Derm Model MD-3 Instruction Manual
Desc: The UPA Micro-Derm Model MD-3 is an electronic non-destructive coating thickness gauge that provides direct digital readout of coating thickness in millionths-inch, mils, or microns.  Incorporating solid state IC construction, this precision instrument measures the thickness of all types of coatings on almost any base material.  It is fast and accurate and, in combination with specially-designed probes, is ideal for measuring plating and coatings on connectors, flat packs, printed circuit board surfaces and through-holes, terminals, transistor headers and leads, diodes, watchbands, watch cases, jewelry, etc.

Title: UDT Model S351 Hand-Held Radiometer/Photometer Operating Manual
Desc: The UDT Model S351 Hand-Held Radiometer/Photometers are a series of easy-to-use precision light measuring instruments designed for field use.  Five individual models provide detector/indicator combinations dedicated to specific light measurements.

Title: UDT Model 350 Radiometer/Photometer Optometer Operating Instruction Manual
Desc: The UDT Model 350 Radiometer/Photometer Optometer is a field and benchtop radiometer/photometer that incorporates all of the quality synonymous with UDT instrumentation.  Human engineering and innovative features permit an operator, with minimum skills and control, to make a diversity of precision optical measurements.

Title: United Technologies Packard Multi-Prias Gamma Counting System Operation Manual
Desc: The United Technologies Packard Multi-Prias Gamma Counting System is designed for quantitative detection of gamma radiation.  The Multi-Prias System provides a printed record of all such measurements with automated sample changing, batch definition, data accumulation, and a real time display of all counting results.

Title: UTI SS-20T Low Pressure Sampling System and 02154 Backing System Instruction Manual
Desc: The UTI SS-20T Low Pressure Sampling System and 02154 Backing System were designed to be used with the 100C Precision Mass Analyzer to monitor sputtering or etching processes when gas sample pressures range from 0.1 millitorr to 4 Torr for operating in the molecular flow regime.  However, gas flow through the orifice will be transitional.  Careful calibration must be performed to achieve accuracy.  A high conductance vacuum valve is provided for making residual gas background measurements when operating the test system at high vacuum.

Title: University of Iowa Bioengineering 558C-5 Voltage Clamp System Operating and Service Manual
Desc: The University of Iowa Bioengineering College of Medicine 558C-5 Voltage Clamp System is a modular "plug-in" system that replaces earlier models 558C-4, 616C-3, 710C-1 and 742C Dual Voltage Clamps.  The Chassis of the system will accommodate one to three Voltage Clamp Channel Modules; or one or two Voltage Clamp Channels Modules, one Pulse Generator Module and one Pulse Height Analyzer Module.  The Chassis also features international power supplies for operation at 100,120,220,230 or 240 Volts, 47 - 63 Hertz.

Title: Unitek Ultra-Mat Furnace Installation, Operation, Instruction Manual
Desc: The Unitek Ultra-Mat Furnace is a precision furnace incorporating advanced, solid-state electronics which allow, by simple program selection, the consistent and automatic firing of all types of porcelain restoration.

Title: Unitron Understanding and Using the Phase Microscope
Desc: The Unitron Understanding and Using the Phase Microscope including "Experiments with the Phase Microscope" is an educational primer in the world of phase micoscopy

Title: U.S. Stoneware 755RMV Jar Mills Installation, Use, and Maintenance Instructions
Desc: The U.S. Stoneware 755RMV Jar Mills Installation, Use, and Maintenance Instructions

Title: U.S. Stoneware 753RMV Unitized Jar Mills Installation, Use, and Maintenance Instructions
Desc: The U.S. Stoneware 753RMV Unitized Jar Mills Installation, Use, and Maintenance Instructions

Title: UVP PR-100 UV-Ozone Photoreactor Ultraviolet since 1932 Operating Instruction Manual
Desc: The UVP PR-100 UV-Ozone Photoreactor cabinet provides an ultraviolet light and ozone environment for removing organic contaminates from surfaces.  This removal of organics from a surface is also known as micro-cleaning.  It occurs down to monolayer levels, thereby providing an extremely fine level of cleanliness.  It is accomplished at ambient temperature without special ovens or heaters; and is a dry process requiring no special baths or chemicals.

Title: UVP Mineralight UVG-54, UVGL-55, UVGL-58 and Blak-Ray UVL-56 Ultraviolet Lamps Operating Instruction
Desc: The UVP Mineralight UVG-54, UVGL-55, UVGL-58 and Blak-Ray UVL-56 Ultraviolet Lamps represent the highest achievement in ultraviolet lamp history.  The result of extensive research and craftsmanship, this lamp will give the operator years of trouble-free service.  Ultraviolet energy cannot be detected by the human eye.  A bluish light will be visible through the filter of the lamp.  This is due to the emission of visible light from the tube.  The special filter eliminates most of this visible light interference.  Ultraviolet energy is just shorter in wavelength than visible violet light, and can be divided into longwave and shortwave groups.

Title: UVP Model B-100A Blak-Ray Ultraviolet Lamp
Desc: The UVP Model B-100A Blak-Ray Ultraviolet Lamp is a high energy source of long wave ultraviolet energy.  It is especially recommended for non-destructive testing.  The concentrated beam of the B-100A centers black light in a controlled area.  Many special additives are available to fluoresce materials that are not normally fluorescent.  These include non-fluorescent oils, lacquers, varnishes and other liquids or solids of all types.

Title: VAC HE-43 Series Dri Lab Glove Box Operations Manual
Desc: The Vacuum/Atmospheres HE-43 Series, Dri-Lab is designed for use with Vacuum/Atmoshpheres Dri-Trains and Ni-Trains to establish and maintain an atmosphere of less than 1 ppm contaminants. The unit contains an evacuable chamber (Ante-Chamber) for transfer of parts without contamination of the environment. The Dri-Lab is designed for convenience, efficiency, and operator comfort.

Title: VAC HE-43 Series Dri Lab Glove Box Operations Manual
Desc: The Vacuum/Atmospheres DL Series, Dri-Lab is designed for use with Vacuum/Atmoshpheres Dri-Trains and Ni-Trains to establish and maintain an atmosphere of less than 1 ppm contaminants. The unit contains an evacuable chamber (Ante-Chamber) for transfer of parts without contamination of the environment. The Dri-Lab is designed for convenience, efficiency, and operator comfort. Two manuals in stock.

Title: VAC Model Model M040-2 Dri-Train Inert Gas Purification System Technical Manual
Desc: The purpose of the Dri-Train system is to provide a moisture and oxygen-free atmoshpere inside a glove-box by recirculating an inert gas. This permits handling of materials sensitive to moisture and oxygen contamination. The gas circulated by the Dri-Train may be argon or helium, but nitrogen (although not totally inert) may also be used.

Title: Vacuubrand Diaphragm Pumps Instruction Manual
Desc: The Vacuubrand Diaphragm Pumps Instruction Manual. Models ME2,ME4,MZ2 and MZ2D.

Title: Vac Torr Vacuum Pump Instruction Manual
Desc: The Vac Torr Vacuum Pump Instruction Manual.

Title: Vacuum General Model 80-5 Flow Display Module Instruction Manual
Desc: The Model 80-5 Flow Display Module is designed to provide true mass-flow information about a single gas in standard cubic centimeters per minute, SCCM. The flow display system consists of the 80-5 Flow Display Module and a thermal-mass flow sensor. The 80-5 can be used to display information concerning gas flow for and 80-4 Flow/Ratio Controller. This enables you to achieve a wide range of pure gas ratios (reaching as high as 200,000 to 1) through the use of flow sensors with different ranges.

Title: Vacuum General Model 80-4 Flow/Ratio Controller Instruction Manual
Desc: The Model 80-4 Flow/Ratio Controller is designed to maintain the flow of a single gas at a preset level by closed-loop servo control. The control system consists of the 80-4 Controller, a thermalmass flow sensor, and a magnetically actuated proportional control valve. It will control gas flow from .5% to 100% of the flow sensors full scale.

Title: Valco Digital Valve Sequence Programmer Manual
Desc: The Digital Valve Sequence Programmer is a sequential timer/programmer with 2, 3, or 4 intervals. Each interval has a pair of digital time switches, a three position toggle switch, an LED and an output relay.

Title: Valco 2 Position Electric Actuator Instruction Manual
Desc: Valco 2 Position valves are widely used in a variety of sample injection and switching applications. Rotating them to the desired position can be done manually but is best done automatically with either the Valco 2 Position Air Actuator or the Valco 2 Position Electric Actuator described in this manual.

Title: Valco Digital Valve Sequence Programmer Instruction Manual
Desc: The Digital Valve Sequence Programmer is an add-on or stand-alone timer/programmer available with either 2 or 4 intervals, settable in ranges of 0-99 seconds, 0-9.9 minutes or 0-99 minutes. The DVSP is most commonly used for remote operation of electrical devices such as solenoid valves, Valco two position or multiposition electric actuators, and the Valco Digital Valve Interface, which converts contact closures into pneumatic pulses for switching Valco two position air actuators.

Title: Valco Two Position Electric Valve Actuator for Liquid & Gas Chromotography Operation Manual
Desc: In gas and liquid chromatography it is desirable to rotate two position Valco valves automatically. The Valco two position electric actuator now complements the Valco Helical Drive Air Actuator for valve rotation. For hazardous situations the non-electrical air actuator must be used.

Title: Valco Multiposition Electric Actuator Operation Manual
Desc: Valco multipostion valves are used in liquid and gas chromatography to select a sample from a number of different streams or to divert a stream to a desired location. These multiposition valves can be swtiched to the desired valve position using either the Valco helical drive sequential actuator or a random access Valco multipostion electrical actuator.

Title: Varian SpectrAA Systems
Desc: Varian SpectrAA Systems are complete atomic absorption analysis systems. This publication contains general information in relation to the preparation of an installation site, and details the facilities that must be provided to ensure that the installation can be completed.

Title: Valco Multiposition Control Module Manual
Desc: Valco's Multiposition Control Module is designed for use with Valco multiposition air operated valves. It provides the means for controlling the position of the valve while at the same time displaying and transmitting the valve position to external equipment. The valve can be advanced manually or by a signal from an external device.

Title: Vanzetti Model TM-2 Infrared Thermal Monitor Instruction Manual
Desc: The Infrared Thermal Monitor, Model TM-2, is a non-contact temperature measuring system making use of infrared radiation which is recieved from the target.

Title: Varex Evaporative Light-Scattering Detector for HPLC Operating Manual
Desc: The Varex Evaporative Light-Scattering Detector is designed to be used as a universal evaporative mass detector for HPLC. It employs an operating principle that is simple and trouble-free in its design, yet superior in its performance. It may be used wherever sample components are of significantly lower volatility than the HPLC mobile phase.

Title: Varian Aerograph Thermal Conductivity Detector Manual for Series 3700 GC
Desc: Varian Aerograph Thermal Conductivity Detector Manual for Thermal Conductivity Detector and Controller in the Series 3700 Gas Chromatograph

Title: Varian Chromatography Data System Operations Manual
Desc: The Varian Chromatography Data System Operations Manual.

Title: Varian Aerograph Installation Manual
Desc: Varian Aerograph Installation Manual is for the installation of the Series 3700 Gas Chromatograph

Title: Varian Aerograph Operations Manual for Series 3700 GC
Desc: This manual describes operation of the Aerograph Series 3700 Gas Chromatograph and provides operating and maintenance information about the basic unit of the GC.

Title: Varian Split/Splitless Capillary Injector Manual
Desc: The Split/Splitless Capillary Injector System is designed for use with wide or narrow bore fused silica capillary columns in Varian 3700 Series and Vista Series gas chromatographs.

Title: Varian Aerograph Series 3700 Gas Chromatographs Installation Manual
Desc: The Varian Aerograph Series 3700 Gas Chromatograph Installation Manual.

Title: Varian Aerograph Injectors Manual for Series 3700 GC
Desc: Varian Aerograph Injectors Manual for Series 3700 GC

Title: Varian 3000 Series Gas Chromatograph Documentation Manual
Desc: Varian 3000 Series Gas Chromatograph Assembly Drawings, Parts Lists, Printed Circuit Boards and Schematics.

Title: Varian 3000 Series Gas Chromatograph Self-Installation Guide
Desc: The Varian 3000 Series Gas Chromatograph Self-Installation Guide.

Title: Varian Aerograph Flame Ionization Detector Manual for Series 3700 GC
Desc: Varian Aerograph Flame Ionization Detector Manual for Series 3700 GC

Title: Varian Aerograph Pneumatics Manual for Series 3700 GC
Desc: Varian Aerograph Pneumatics Manual for Series 3700 GC includes standard and AFC versions

Title: Virtis Virsonic 475 Ultrasonic Cell Disrupter Operating Instructions
Desc: The Versonic 475 is a high intensity ultrasonic cell disrupter designed for the sciences research. Compact and easy to operated the Virsonic 475 is capable of efficiently performing a wide variety of ultrasonic processing applications including: disruption of bacterial cells, viruses and spores, dispersion of solids in liquid, acceleration of enzymatic and chemical reactions, emulsification, degassing of liquids, cleaning and many more.

Title: Varian Supplemental Drawing Package for Series 3700 Gas Chromatographs
Desc: Varian Supplemental Drawing Package for Series 3700 Gas Chromatographs.

Title: Varian Aerograph Readout/Temperature Controller Manual for Series 3700 GC
Desc: Varian Aerograph Readout/Temperature Controller Manual for Series 3700 GC

Title: Varian Aerograph Auto Linear Temperature Programmer Manual for Series 3700 GC
Desc: Varian Aerograph Auto Linear Temperature Programmer Manual for Series 3700 GC. The ALTP module provides precise linear temperature programming or isothermal control of the column oven in the Series 3700 Gas Chromatograph.

Title: Varian Model 1000 ELCD Detector Manual
Desc: Varian 3000 Series GC's are designed to accomodate the Model 1000 Electrolytic Conductivity Detector. The ELCD interface cable connects to the outboard electronic control module to the GC's ELCD PC board for both signal and control functions. This allows keyboard control of the vent solenoid and the interfacing of the ELCD detector output signal to the optional printer/plotter.

Title: Varian 3000 CX Series Gas Chromatograph Self-Installation Guide
Desc: Varian 3000 CX Series Gas Chromatograph Self-Installation Guide.

Title: Varian 1041 Universal Injector Operator's Manual
Desc: The 1041 Universal Injector may be installed on the Varian Model 3000 Gas Chromatographs.

Title: Varian 1061 Universal Flash Injector Operator's Manual
Desc: The Varian 1061 Universal Flash Injector for large bore columns consists of three parts; a Model 1060 flash injector body, a column guide, and a glass insert specifically designed for use with large bore columns. This injector is designed for general use with all sample types and particularly for use with samples contaminated with non-volatile impurities.

Title: Varian 1040/1060 Packed Column Injectors Operator's Manual
Desc: This section describes the Model 1040 On-Column injector and the Model 1060 Flash Vaporization injector used with 1/4" and 1/8" glass or metal packed columns in the packed column 3000 Series Gas Chromatographs.

Title: Varian 3700 Gas Chromatograph Operator's  Preliminary Manual
Desc: The Series 3700 Gas Chromatograph is a modular, dual-column instrument comprised of the basic unit to which a broad range of optional modules may be added.

Title: Varian Flame Ionization Detector Manual
Desc: The Varian Flame Ionization Detector Manual.

Title: Varian 1040 Megabore Injector Installation and Operation Instructions
Desc: The 1040 Megabore injector is designed for use with fused silica columns of > 530 microns ID. The Megabore injector can be operated in two modes: the packed column mode, or the capillary column.

Title: Varian DMS 80 UV-Visible Spectrophotometers Service Manual
Desc: DMS 80/90 UV-Visible Spectrophotometers Service Manual. This manual covers all details required to preform filed service on the Varian Techtron Model DMS 80 spectrophotometer.

Title: Varian Ni Electron Capture Detector Manual
Desc: This section describes the procedures governing the handling, contamination testing, maintenence of records, repair, storage and shipping of the Ni Pulsed Electron Capture Detector as a radioactive source. Users of this detector are required by the Nuclear Regulatory Commision regulations to be familiar with these procedures.

Title: Varian Electron Capture Detector
Desc: Varian Electron Capture Detector to be used with GC

Title: Varian Digital Interface Port Accessory Operator's Manual
Desc: Varian Digital Interface Port Accessory with the Model 210 Spectrophotometer.

Title: Varian 1075 Split/Splitless Capillary Injector Operator's Manual
Desc: This manual describes the installation and operation of the Varian 1075 Split/Splitless Capillary Injector for use with the 3300 Gas Chromatograph, and the Star 3400 CX GC. Two manuals in stock.

Title: Varian Flame Photometric Detector Manual

Title: Temperature Controller
Desc: Atmosphere Controllers provide accurate display and control of the carbon level in carburizing furnaces or ceramic glazing kilns. There are three different controllers that connect to a zirconia probe which measures the % oxygen in the furnace. The carbon level is calculated from the % oxygen and temperature measured by the probe. An optional third analog input can accept the output signal from a CO or H2 analyzer thus providing a more precise carbon or dewpoint measurement. The controllers are compatible with probes from the following manufacturers: • Drayton • Accucarb • AACC/MSI • SSI • Macdui/Barber-Colman • Bosch Lambda In addition to carbon level the controllers can be configured to measure and control either: • % oxygen or log oxygen • Dewpoint in °C or °F • Probe millivolts Advanced control algorithms ensure accurate, stable control. A range of plug-in modules are used to provide control, retransmission and alarm outputs. The control outputs can be mA or volts; time proportioning relay, logic or triac; or raise/lower outputs to a motorized valve and slide wire. A probe clean output is available to force compressed air through the probe at regular intervals to burn-off soot deposits. A sooting alarm will warn if carbon deposits build up to a level that can cause false readings. Probe health is monitored by measuring the time it takes the probe MV reading to recover from a self-clean operation. High speed Modbus® or Profibus® communications, allow supervision by a computer or easy integration into Programmable Control Systems. (PLC’s) Furnace

Title: Balston Zero Air Generator
Desc: The Balston Zero Air Generator is a completely engineered system which will replace the use of inconvenient high pressure gas cylinders as a source of hydrocarbon free air. On-site compressed air is fed into the Zero air generator and is purrified to a total hydrocarbon level of less then 0.1 ppm (measured as methane). Zero Air from a Balston Zero Air Generator may be used as source of fuel air for flame Ionization Detectors(FID's)or as a zero reference for any insruments which measure hydrocarbon concentration.

Title: 2408i Indicator and Alarm Unit
Desc: Thank you for choosing the 2408i panel mounted indicator. It will provide accurate measurement and display of temperature and other process variables. A modular build accepts a wide range of plug-in modules allowing: up to four alarm outputs, two process variable (PV) inputs, direct strain gauge/pressure sensor measurements, custom linearisation, analogue retransmission, remote setpoint (SP) input and digital communications. The indicator is supplied configured in accordance with the order code. The order code and instrument serial number is shown on a label fixed to the top of the case, and this can be checked against the order code given in section 3 of these instructions. 1.1 CONTENTS OF PACKAGE 1. A peel-off label set - a convenient position is to fix a label to the top right of the display. 2. A 2.49W resistor used as the load resistor for mA inputs 3. Two panel retaining clips 1.2 DIMENSIONS AND INSTALLATION 1.2.1 To Install the Indicator Please read the safety information in section 4 before proceeding. The indicator is intended to be mounted on a panel within an enclosure such as a control cubicle. 1. Prepare the panel cut-out to the size shown. 2. Insert the indicator through the cut-out. 3. Spring the panel retaining clips into place. Secure the indicator in position by holding it level and pushing both retaining clips forward. 4. Peel off the plastic film protecting the front of the indicator. 1.2.2 Removing The Indicator From The Sleeve The indicator can be removed from its sleeve by easing the latching ears outwards and pulling it forward out of the sleeve. When plugging the indicator back into its sleeve, ensure that the latching ears click into place to maintain the moisture sealing protection. Title: FastPrep FP120 Cell Disrupter
Desc: DESCRIPTION The FastPrep® FP120 is a high-speed, benchtop reciprocating device for efficient disruption of cell membranes. The unit is designed for use with the FastPrep® Extraction Kits (Qbiogene, www.qbiogene.com). These kits are available for a wide variety of extraction and purification applications. The FastPrep® sample holder has the capacity to process 12 FastPrep® sample tubes simultaneously. We do not recommend using any tubes other than those supplied with the FastPrep® Kits. The front control panel of the FastPrep® Instrument includes a digital display and two control switches. Speed (4.0-6.5 m/sec) and run time (1-45 seconds) are fully programmable. Title: Bacharach FYRITE Gas Analyzer Operation/Maintenance Manual
Desc: The FYRITE amploys the well-known Orsat method of volumetric analysis involving chemical absorption of a sample gas, such as carbon dioxide or oxygen. The reagent used to absorb carbon dioxide (CO2) is potassium hydroxide (dyed red), and chromous chloride (blue) is the absorbent for oxygen (O2). The unique feature of the FYRITE is that the absorbing fluid is also used as the indicating fluid so that one vessel takes the place of both measuring burette and absorption pipette.
